\h Exodus
\toc1 Exodus
\toc2 Exodus
\toc3 Exo.
\mt1 Exodus
\is1 Introduction
\ip The word \bk Exodus\bk* comes from the Greek word meaning вҖҳdepartureвҖҷ or вҖҳleavingвҖҷ. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳShemЕҚtвҖҷ which is the second word in the Hebrew and means вҖҳNamesвҖҷ because it begins with a list of names. Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe second book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip It should be noted that вҖҳMoshehвҖҷ is the best English transliteration of the name of the hero of this account. Sadly, he's commonly known in the English world as вҖҳMosesвҖҷ, even though we have all the sounds in our language to be able to pronounce his name more accurately. Unfortunately, because the language of вҖҳthe New TestamentвҖҷ didn't have the вҖҳshвҖҷ sound and had no letter for вҖҳhвҖҷ, his Hebrew version of his Egyptian name is corrupted as it goes through Greek вҖҳMЕҚsaКёsвҖҷ and then Latin вҖҳMoysesвҖҷ and then first entered English in the 1300's as вҖҳMoisesвҖҷ. Now that we live in a modern era where we try to show more respect to the names of peoples from other cultures, the \em OET\em* encourages the same for Biblical characters (especially the major ones), hence вҖҳMoshehвҖҷ. (Maybe a little bit of relearning could demonstrate a lot of respect to the Jewish people whose ancestors are recorded in these accounts.)
\ip After God had used a famine to cause his people to go down into Egypt (Heb. Mitsrayim), this document records how they eventually become slaves, but then God works many miracles to enable them to leave again, and not only that, to be paid at the end for their work.
\ip This story can be divided into three main parts: 1. their slavery in Egypt, and how God called Mosheh (Moses), the child who had been adopted by an Egyptian princess, to lead them out of slavery; 2. how God assisted them when they were chased by the Egyptian army, then when they reached Mt. Sinai, how they were miraculously given food and drink there at the mountain; 3. how Yahweh revealed himself to Mosheh there at Mt. Sinai, and gave him instructions to guide their lives and their nation, and God's agreement with the people; 4. the ending is the construction of the sacred tent, complete with instructions about how they should worship.
\ip An overview would be how God rescued his people from slavery and established them as a nation that was hopeful of a good future.
\ip \em Mosheh\em* is the most important person in this account. He was chosen by God to lead his people out of slavery and right out of Egypt. The \em ten commands\em* are another well-known component of this document and can be found in chapter twenty.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Yisrael's descendants are driven out of Egypt \ior 1:1вҖ“15:21\ior*
\io2 a. The people are enslaved there in Egypt \ior 1:1-22\ior*
\io2 b. The birth and early life of Mosheh \ior 2:1вҖ“4:31\ior*
\io2 c. Far'oh (Pharaoh) king of Egypt stands strongly against Mosheh and Aharon taking the people out of Egypt \ior 5:1вҖ“11:10\ior*
\io2 d. God's messenger of death that вҖҳpassed-overвҖҷ, and the exit of Yisra'el's descendants from Egypt \ior 12:1вҖ“15:21\ior*
\io1 Leaving the Red Sea and going to Mt. Sinai \ior 15:22вҖ“18:27\ior*
\io1 God's instructions and the agreement \ior 19:1вҖ“24:18\ior*
\io1 The sacred tent and warnings concerning worshipping \ior 25:1вҖ“40:38\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Yisra'el's descendants are driven into slavery
\rem /s1 The Israelites Are Treated Cruelly in Egypt; The Israelites Oppressed; The Israelites in Egypt
\p
\v 1 These are the namesВҰ25402 of Yisra'el's descendants who accompanied YacobВҰ25408 (Jacob) when he moved his householdВҰ25410 to EgyptВҰ25406:\x + \xo 1:1-4: \xt Gen 46:8-27.\x*
\v 2 ReubenВҰ25413, SimeonВҰ25414, LeviВҰ25415, YehudahВҰ25416,
\v 3 YissakarВҰ25418 (Issachar), ZebulunВҰ25419, BenyaminВҰ25420,
\v 4 DanВҰ25423, NaftaliВҰ25424, GadВҰ25425, and AsherВҰ25426.
\v 5 \add At that time,\add* YacobВҰ25435 had a total of seventyВҰ25436 descendants (including YosefВҰ25438 \add andВҰ25438 his sons\add* who were \add already\add* in EgyptВҰ25440.)
\p
\v 6 \add As the years progressed,\add* YosefВҰ25443 andВҰ25442 his brothersВҰ25446 diedВҰ25442вҖ”all of that generationВҰ25448,
\v 7 \add but they'd had many children who went on to have their own children and grandchildren,\add* and so they became a large and powerful group \add there in EgyptВҰ25452\add*.\x + \xo 1:7: \xt Acts 7:17.\x*
\rem /s1 The Israelites Are Oppressed
\p
\v 8 \add Eventually\add* a new kingВҰ25465 came to power in EgyptВҰ25470 \add (Mitsrayim)\add* who had never known YosefВҰ25477\x + \xo 1:8: \xt Acts 7:18.\x*
\v 9 and he told his people, вҖңListen, those descendants of YisraelВҰ25486 \add (IsraelВҰ25486)\add* are becoming more numerousВҰ25487 and powerfulВҰ25488 than us.
\v 10 \add So\add*, let's deal wiselyВҰ25492 with them, in case they \add continue to\add* multiply. Then if war was to break out, they could easily take the other side and fightВҰ25509 against us, and then leave our country.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:10: \xt Acts 7:19.\x*
\v 11 ThenВҰ25517 they appointedВҰ25517 overseersВҰ25519 to work them in slaveВҰ25520 gangsВҰ25520, and using them as forcedВҰ25523 labourВҰ25523, they builtВҰ25524 the storeВҰ25526 citiesВҰ25525 at PithonВҰ25530 and RamesesВҰ25533 for Far'ohВҰ25527 (Pharaoh).
\v 12 \add However,\add* the more they oppressed them, the more they multiplied and spreadВҰ25541 out, and \add the more\add* the Egyptians cameВҰ25542 to dreadВҰ25542 the IsraelisВҰ25545.
\v 13 \add SoВҰ25547 they\add* made the IsraelisВҰ25552 work \add long, hard hours\add*,
\v 14 and they made their livesВҰ25558 bitterВҰ25555 with the hard slavery. \add They were forced to make\add* mortarВҰ25561 and bricksВҰ25562, as well as all kinds of slave labourВҰ25573 in the fieldsВҰ25566вҖ”all the workВҰ25570 they had to do was \add strenuous and tiring\add*.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ25577 the kingВҰ25578 of EgyptВҰ25579 spoke to ShiphrahВҰ25585 andВҰ25586 PuahВҰ25588, the two HebrewВҰ25581 midwivesВҰ25580,
\v 16 saying, вҖңWhen you assist the HebrewВҰ25594 women as midwivesВҰ25591, \add as you sit there on your\add* stool, if you seeВҰ25595 that it's a male, do \add something\add* so he'll die, but if it's a female, thenВҰ25590 let her liveВҰ25609.вҖқ
\v 17 ButВҰ25611 the midwivesВҰ25612 \add were godly women\add* and didn'tВҰ25616 do according to what the EgyptianВҰ25622 kingВҰ25621 \add had instructed\add* them, and theyВҰ25617 let the boys liveВҰ25623.
\v 18 \add SoВҰ25628\add* the kingВҰ25629 calledВҰ25628 the midwivesВҰ25632 \add back\add*, and he \add demanded\add*, вҖңWhyВҰ25631 have you done that and let \add their\add* sons liveВҰ25639?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңBecause the HebrewВҰ25653 women aren'tВҰ25650 like Egyptian women,вҖқ the midwives \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңThey're \add more active\add* andВҰ25644 give birthВҰ25662 beforeВҰ25658 the midwife \add even\add* gets to them.вҖқ
\v 20 \add SoВҰ25664\add* GodВҰ25665 rewarded the midwivesВҰ25666, and \add meanwhile,\add* the peopleВҰ25668 \add continued to increase in number\add* and become more powerful,
\v 21 andВҰ25672 because the midwivesВҰ25676 had \add demonstrated their desire to obey\add* GodВҰ25677, he gave them families \add of their own\add*.
\v 22 ThenВҰ25684 Far'ohВҰ25685 commandedВҰ25684 all of his peopleВҰ25688, вҖңYouВҰ25694 \add all need to\add* tossВҰ25695 everyВҰ25690 newborn boy into the river, but you can let the girls liveВҰ25699.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:22: \xt Acts 7:19.\x*
\c 2
\s1 The birth of Mosheh (Moses)
\rem /s1 Moses; The Birth of Moses; Birth and Youth of Moses
\p
\v 1 \add During this period,\add* a manВҰ25703 from the tribe of LeviВҰ25705 married a woman who was also a Levite,
\v 2 and she conceivedВҰ25713 and gaveВҰ25715 birthВҰ25715 to a son. WhenВҰ25718 she sawВҰ25717 that he was a \add healthy\add* boy, she hid him away for threeВҰ25724 monthsВҰ25725,\x + \xo 2:2: \xt Acts 7:20; Heb 11:23.\x*
\v 3 \add but\add* thenВҰ25727 she wasn't able to hide him any longer. \add SoВҰ25727\add* she got a basket made from \add woven\add* reeds and plastered it with bitumen and pitchВҰ25739. ThenВҰ25727 she put the baby in it, and floated \add the basket\add* in the reeds along the riverbank,
\v 4 \add leaving the baby's\add* sisterВҰ25753 to watch from a distanceВҰ25754 to seeВҰ25755 what would happen to him.
\p
\v 5 \add After a while,\add* Far'oh's daughterВҰ25762 came down to the riverВҰ25774 to wash \add herself\add*, and \add she and\add* her young \add attendantsВҰ25769\add* were walkingВҰ25770 along the \add riverbank\add*. She sawВҰ25775 the container among the reedsВҰ25780 and sentВҰ25781 \add one of\add* her slaveВҰ25784 women to get it.
\v 6 She openedВҰ25787 it and sawВҰ25788 the baby inside, and wow, he \add started\add* cryingВҰ25795. She felt sorryВҰ25796 for him and saidВҰ25798, вҖңThis baby \add must be\add* one of the HebrewВҰ25800 childrenВҰ25799.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ25803 his sisterВҰ25804 \add approached and\add* asked \add the princess\add*, вҖңWouldВҰ25809 you like me to goВҰ25810 and find a HebrewВҰ25816 womanВҰ25813 who'll be able to breastfeed the baby for you?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add Yes,\add* goВҰ25829,вҖқ answered Far'oh's daughterВҰ25826, and the girlВҰ25831 wentВҰ25830 and got the baby's motherВҰ25835.
\v 9 вҖңTake this baby,вҖқ saidВҰ25838 the \add princess\add*, вҖңand breastfeed him for me, and I'll pay you \add for doing it\add*.вҖқ \add SoВҰ25838\add* the womanВҰ25856 tookВҰ25855 the baby and \add looked after\add* him.
\v 10 \add When\add* the boy had grown \add enough\add*, she broughtВҰ25863 him \add back\add* to Far'oh's daughterВҰ25864 and he became her son. She named him вҖҳMoshehВҰ25873вҖҷ\f + \fr 2:10 \ft More familiar to most English readers as вҖҳMosesвҖҷ from the Greek вҖҳОңПүПғбҝҶПӮвҖҷ (MЕҚsaКёs) but Greek doesn't have an вҖҳhвҖҷ or a вҖҳshвҖҷ so by going through Greek we ended up with something quite different from his real name. However, English does have those sounds and letters, so there's no reason why we can't get this name correct.\f* \add (which means вҖҳpulled outвҖҷ)\add* because she saidВҰ25874 that she'd \add plucked\add* him out of the \add river\add*.\x + \xo 2:10: \xt Acts 7:21.\x*
\s1 Mosheh escapes to Midyan
\rem /s1 Moses Escapes to Midian; Moses Flees to Midian
\p
\v 11 \add Later on\add* when MoshehВҰ25886 was fully grownВҰ25885, he went out to visit \add the Hebrews\add* and saw theirВҰ25892 \add forcedВҰ25892 labourВҰ25892\add*, and he saw an Egyptian man beating a Hebrew manвҖ”one of his own people.\x + \xo 2:11-14: \xt Acts 7:23-28.\x*
\v 12 \add Mosheh\add* lookedВҰ25902 around to check that no one was watching, then he hit the Egyptian, \add killing him,\add* then he hid his body in the sand.
\v 13 The next dayВҰ25917, he wentВҰ25916 out again and wow, twoВҰ25920 Hebrew menВҰ25922 were fighting each other, and he saidВҰ25925 to the man in the wrongВҰ25926, вҖңWhy are you hitting your \add fellow Hebrew\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңWho made you the ruler andВҰ25931 judgeВҰ25936 over us?вҖқ \add the manВҰ25934 replied\add*. вҖңAre you \add planning\add* to killВҰ25938 me like you killedВҰ25942 \add that\add* Egyptian?вҖқ ThenВҰ25931 MoshehВҰ25947 was afraidВҰ25946 because he realised that what he'd done had \add probably become widely\add* knownВҰ25950.
\v 15 \add Indeed,\add* when Far'ohВҰ25954 heard about it, he \add ordered\add* Mosheh to be killed. \add SoВҰ25953\add* Mosheh had to flee from \add the king\add* and he \add took off east\add* to live in MidianВҰ25971 and he stayed near the well.\x + \xo 2:15: \xt Acts 7:29; Heb 11:27.\x*
\p
\v 16 TheВҰ25984 priestВҰ25977 there in MidianВҰ25978 had sevenВҰ25979 daughtersВҰ25980, and they would come to the well to draw water out and fill up the troughsВҰ25986 there so theirВҰ25989 father'sВҰ25989 \add sheep and goats\add* could drink.
\v 17 NowВҰ25998 some male shepherdsВҰ25992 came along and \add started to\add* shoo their flockВҰ26000 away, but MoshehВҰ25995 got involved and helped them so that their animals could drink.
\v 18 \add When\add* they \add got home\add* to theirВҰ26006 fatherВҰ26006 ReuelВҰ26005, he \add asked\add*, вҖңHow comeВҰ26010 youВҰ26009 \add got home\add* so early today?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңThere was an Egyptian manВҰ26014,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңwho stood up for us against those \add other\add* shepherdsВҰ26018. And he even drew \add water\add* for us andВҰ26013 gave our flockВҰ26027 water to drink.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңWhere is he \add now\add*?вҖқ he \add asked them\add*. вҖңWhat's thisвҖ”you mean you all just left him there? Go andВҰ26029 get him \add so we can give him a meal\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add Later it turned out that\add* Mosheh was prepared to live with the manВҰ26050, andВҰ26051 \add in due course\add* he gaveВҰ26051 his daughterВҰ26055 ZipporahВҰ26054 to Mosheh \add in marriage\add*.
\v 22 \add When\add* she gaveВҰ26058 birthВҰ26058 to a son, he named him вҖҳGershomВҰ26064вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳforeignerвҖҷ)\add* because he saidВҰ26066, вҖңI've becomeВҰ26068 a foreigner \add living\add* in a foreignВҰ26070 land.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \add Eventually\add* Egypt'sВҰ26079 kingВҰ26078 diedВҰ26077, \add but\add* the IsraelisВҰ26083 groanedВҰ26080 from the slavery \add they were still under\add* and they criedВҰ26087 out, and theirВҰ26089 cryВҰ26089 \add for freedom\add* from slavery wentВҰ26088 up to GodВҰ26092.
\v 24 \add He\add* heard theirВҰ26101 groaningВҰ26101 and rememberedВҰ26102 his agreement with AbrahamВҰ26109, with Yitshak, and with YacobВҰ26115,\x + \xo 2:24: \xt Gen 15:13-14.\x*
\v 25 and he \add looked down on\add* the IsraelisВҰ26122 and he \add was concerned about them\add*.
\c 3
\s1 God calls Mosheh from a burning bush
\rem /s1 God Calls Moses; Moses at the Burning Bush; Moses and the Burning Bush
\p
\v 1 \add One time\add* MoshehВҰ26127 (Moses) was shepherding the flock of his father-in-lawВҰ26134 Yetro (or Jethro, the priestВҰ26135 at MidianВҰ26136), and he led the flock beyond the wildernessВҰ26142 and cameВҰ26143 to a hill. (\add This was later known as\add* the mountainВҰ26146 of GodВҰ26147 at HorevВҰ26148).
\v 2 \add While he was there.\add* Yahweh'sВҰ26152 messengerВҰ26151 appearedВҰ26150 to him in a flameВҰ26154 coming from the middle of a bush, andВҰ26150 as \add Mosheh\add* looked, to his surprise \add he saw that\add* the bush was burningВҰ26162 in the fire yet not \add actually\add* being burnt up.\x + \xo 3:2-10: \xt Acts 7:30-34.\x*
\v 3 вҖңI've got to go andВҰ26173 seeВҰ26173 this amazing sightВҰ26176,вҖқ MoshehВҰ26169 saidВҰ26168 \add to himself\add*. вҖңHow come that bush isn'tВҰ26180 burningВҰ26182 up?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 When YahwehВҰ26186 sawВҰ26185 that he'd left his path in order to look, GodВҰ26192 calledВҰ26190 to him from the middle of the bush, вҖңMosheh, Mosheh.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm here,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 5 вҖңDon't come any closer,вҖқ \add Yahweh\add* saidВҰ26201. вҖңTake off your sandalsВҰ26208 because the placeВҰ26212 where you'reВҰ26214 standingВҰ26215 is HOLY groundВҰ26217.
\v 6 I'm the god of your father and the god of AbrahamВҰ26227, Yitshak, and YacobВҰ26231.вҖқ \add SoВҰ26222\add* MoshehВҰ26233 covered hid his face because he was scared to lookВҰ26237 at GodВҰ26224.
\p
\v 7 вҖңI've certainly noticed the sufferingВҰ26262 of my peopleВҰ26249 in EgyptВҰ26251,вҖқ YahwehВҰ26243 \add continuedВҰ26242\add*, вҖңI've heardВҰ26255 their cries as the \add slave drivers\add* oppress themвҖ”I'm unmistakingly aware of their pain.
\v 8 \add SoВҰ26264\add* I've comeВҰ26264 down to set them free from Egyptian control and to bringВҰ26269 them up from \add there\add* to a goodВҰ26277 and wide landвҖ”a land flowingВҰ26282 with milk and honeyВҰ26284. \add It's currently\add* the placeВҰ26287 of the CanaanitesВҰ26288, the HittitesВҰ26289, the AmoritesВҰ26290, the PerizzitesВҰ26291, the HivitesВҰ26292, and the YebusitesВҰ26293.
\v 9 \add Yes,\add* the cryВҰ26297 of the IsraelisВҰ26300 has now \add reached\add* me andВҰ26303 what's more, I've seenВҰ26305 \add how much\add* the Egyptians are oppressingВҰ26308 them.
\v 10 \add SoВҰ26314\add* go now and I'll send you to Far'ohВҰ26319 (Pharaoh) and bringВҰ26320 my peopleвҖ”Yisra'el's descendantsвҖ”out from EgyptВҰ26327.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңWho am I, that I should goВҰ26337 to Far'ohВҰ26340,вҖқ MoshehВҰ26330 \add asked\add* GodВҰ26333, вҖңandВҰ26341 that I should \add be the one to\add* bringВҰ26342 out the IsraelisВҰ26346 out from EgyptВҰ26347?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңI'll certainly be with you,вҖқ \add God replied,\add* вҖңandВҰ26349 this will be your signВҰ26357 \add so that you'll know\add* that I have sentВҰ26360 you: when you bring the peopleВҰ26364 out from EgyptВҰ26365, you all will serve God on this \add very\add* hill.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Divine Name Revealed
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add ButВҰ26374 listen\add*,вҖқ MoshehВҰ26375 told God, вҖң\add If\add* I'm aboutВҰ26381 to goВҰ26381 to the IsraelisВҰ26385 andВҰ26374 if I told them, вҖҳThe God of yourВҰ26389 ancestorsВҰ26389 has sentВҰ26390 me to youВҰ26391.вҖҷ then they'd \add askВҰ26392\add* me, вҖҳ\add Oh yeah,\add* what's his nameВҰ26397?вҖҷ then what would I tell them?вҖқ\x + \xo 3:13: \xt Exo 6:2-3.\x*
\p
\v 14 вҖңI AM WHO I AM,вҖқ GodВҰ26403 told MoshehВҰ26406. вҖңYou'll \add tell them this\add*: вҖҳI AM (Yahweh) sentВҰ26416 me to youВҰ26412.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 3:14: \xt Rev 1:4,8.\x*
\v 15 ThenВҰ26419 he \add continuedВҰ26419\add*, вҖңThis is what you \add need\add* to tell the IsraelisВҰ26431: вҖҳYahwehВҰ26432, the god of your ancestorsВҰ26434, the god of AbrahamВҰ26436, Yitshak, and YacobВҰ26440, sent me to you. This is my name forever, and this is my memorial from generation to generation.вҖҷ
\v 16 Go and gather the IsraeliВҰ26456 eldersВҰ26456, and tell them, вҖҳYahwehВҰ26460, the god of your ancestorsВҰ26462, appearedВҰ26463 to me, the god of AbrahamВҰ26466, Yitshak, and YacobВҰ26468, to say, вҖңI've certainly noticed you all and \add how you're all being treated\add* in EgyptВҰ26477,
\v 17 and I'veВҰ26480 promisedВҰ26479 to take youВҰ26481 all from your mistreatment in EgyptВҰ26483, away to the land where the CanaanitesВҰ26487, HittitesВҰ26488, AmoritesВҰ26489, PerizzitesВҰ26490, HivitesВҰ26491, and the YebusitesВҰ26492 \add are currently living\add*вҖ”to a land flowingВҰ26496 with milk and honeyВҰ26498.вҖқ вҖҷ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ26500 \add the people\add* will listenВҰ26500 to what you tell them, and you and the IsraeliВҰ26504 eldersВҰ26504 will go to the Egyptian kingВҰ26508 and you'll all tell him, вҖҳYahweh, the god of the HebrewsВҰ26514, has met with us. \add SoВҰ26500\add* now, pleaseВҰ26520 let us go threeВҰ26522 days' journeyВҰ26521 into the wildernessВҰ26524, so we can sacrificeВҰ26525 to Yahweh, our god.вҖҷ
\v 19 \add ButВҰ26529\add* I knowВҰ26530 that the Egyptian kingВҰ26536 won'tВҰ26532 let youВҰ26535 goВҰ26538 \add until he's forced to\add*.
\v 20 \add SoВҰ26543 I will use force\add* and I'll strikeВҰ26547 EgyptВҰ26550 with \add several supernatural acts\add*, and afterВҰ26556 those, he'll let youВҰ26560 all goВҰ26559.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ26562 I'll \add make\add* the Egyptian \add peopleВҰ26566 favourВҰ26565 you all in such a way that \add* when you go, you \add won'tВҰ26574 leave empty-handedВҰ26576\add*.\x + \xo 3:21-22: \xt Exo 12:35-36.\x*
\v 22 \add For example,\add* an \add Israeli\add* womanВҰ26579 will askВҰ26578 herВҰ26580 \add Egyptian\add* neighbourВҰ26580 (or from someone staying \add where she livesВҰ26581\add*) for goldВҰ26587 and silverВҰ26585 items and for clothingВҰ26588. ThenВҰ26578 you'll put them on your sonsВҰ26592 and daughtersВҰ26595, and \add in this way\add* you'll all plunderВҰ26596 the Egyptians.вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 God gives Mosheh three miracles
\rem /s1 Signs for Moses; Moses' Miraculous Power; Signs of the Lord's Power; God Gives Moses Miraculous Power
\p
\v 1 вҖңButВҰ26601 listen,вҖқ MoshehВҰ26602 respondedВҰ26603, вҖңthey won't believeВҰ26607 me andВҰ26601 won't listen to \add what I say\add*, because they'll say, вҖҳYahwehВҰ26618 never showed himself to you.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 2 вҖң\add Well,\add* what's that in your handВҰ26626?вҖқ YahwehВҰ26622 \add asked\add*.
\p вҖң\add My shepherd's\add* staffВҰ26628,вҖқ he said.
\v 3 вҖңThrow it on the ground,вҖқ \add Yahweh\add* saidВҰ26630. \add SoВҰ26630 MoshehВҰ26638\add* he threwВҰ26633 it onto the ground and it became a snakeВҰ26636, and \add he quickly moved back away from it\add*.
\v 4 вҖңPick it up by its tail.вҖқ YahwehВҰ26642 told him. \add SoВҰ26641 MoshehВҰ26645\add* picked it up by the tail andВҰ26641 it became a staffВҰ26655 in his hand \add again\add*.
\v 5 вҖңThat's so that they'll believeВҰ26659 that \add I\add* appearedВҰ26662 to youВҰ26663: YahwehВҰ26664вҖ”the god of theirВҰ26666 ancestorsВҰ26666вҖ”the god of AbrahamВҰ26668, Yitshak, andВҰ26671 YacobВҰ26672.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖң\add Now\add* put your hand \add on your chestвҖ”\add*inside your robe.вҖқ YahwehВҰ26675 added. \add SoВҰ26674 Mosheh did that\add*, andВҰ26674 when he pulled it out againВҰ26677, his hand had gone \add totally\add* white with disease.
\v 7 ThenВҰ26692 Yahweh said, вҖң\add Now, put\add* your hand \add back in again\add*.вҖқ \add SoВҰ26692 Mosheh did it again,\add* andВҰ26692 when he pulled it out, wow, it had \add returnedВҰ26693 to normal\add*.
\v 8 вҖң\add SoВҰ26710,\add* if they don'tВҰ26713 believe you, andВҰ26710 \add if the firstВҰ26720 miracle doesn't convince them\add*, thenВҰ26710 they'll believe \add that secondВҰ26724 miracle\add*.
\v 9 And then, even if they don'tВҰ26729 believe those two miracles and \add won'tВҰ26729 believe what you tell them\add*, then you should take some water from the river and pour it onto the dry land. ThenВҰ26726 the water whichВҰ26745 came from the river will \add turn into\add* bloodВҰ26751 \add there\add* on the dry land.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңOh my masterВҰ26760,вҖқ MoshehВҰ26755 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ26754\add*, вҖңI'm not \add very good at speaking to othersвҖ”I never have been andВҰ26780 still aren'tВҰ26761. I seem to get tongue-tiedВҰ26781 easily\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңWho \add was it that made people's mouthsВҰ26789\add*?вҖқ Yahweh saidВҰ26784. вҖңWho makes \add someone\add* mute or deaf, or seeingВҰ26799 or blindВҰ26801? Isn't it me, Yahweh?
\v 12 \add SoВҰ26806\add* get going now, and I'll \add look after\add* your mouthВҰ26812 and \add show\add* you what you to sayВҰ26815.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add ButВҰ26817 Mosheh replied\add*, вҖңOh masterВҰ26819, pleaseВҰ26822 send \add someoneВҰ26823 else\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ26827 YahwehВҰ26830 got angry with MoshehВҰ26831 and told him, вҖңIsn't AharonВҰ26834 (Aaron) a fellow LeviteВҰ26836 and your brotherВҰ26835? I knowВҰ26837 that he can speakВҰ26840 well, and \add what's\add* more, he'll comeВҰ26847 \add from Egypt\add* to meet you, and \add when he does, he'll be very happy\add*.
\v 15 \add He'll become yourВҰ26864 speaker\add* and you'll be able to talk to him and \add tell him what to say\add*. I'll be \add helping both of you speakВҰ26853\add* and I'll teachВҰ26868 you both what you should do.
\v 16 \add SoВҰ26874 in that way,\add* he'll be like a mouthВҰ26886 for you and speakВҰ26874 to the peopleВҰ26880 for you, and you'll be like GodВҰ26891 to him.
\v 17 \add In addition,\add* you'll have thatВҰ26899 staffВҰ26895 with you in order to do those miracles.вҖқ
\s1 Mosheh returns to Egypt
\rem /s1 Moses Returns to Egypt
\p
\v 18 Then Mosheh wentВҰ26908 back to his father-in-lawВҰ26915 Yetro (Jethro), and told him, вҖңCan I pleaseВҰ26919 leave so I can returnВҰ26920 to my \add relatives\add* in EgyptВҰ26926 and seeВҰ26927 whether they're stillВҰ26928 alive.вҖқ
\p вҖңGo in peaceВҰ26934,вҖқ Yetro \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 19 \add Meanwhile\add* YahwehВҰ26937 had told MoshehВҰ26940 in MidianВҰ26941, вҖңLeave here andВҰ26936 returnВҰ26943 to EgyptВҰ26944 because all those who \add wanted to kill you\add* are \add now\add* dead.вҖқ
\v 20 ThenВҰ26956 Mosheh took his wife and sonsВҰ26963 and put them on a donkeyВҰ26967 and returnedВҰ26968 towardsВҰ26969 EgyptВҰ26970 \add with them\add*, and Mosheh took the staffВҰ26975 \add that GodВҰ26976 had turned into a snake\add*.
\p
\v 21 \add On the way,\add* YahwehВҰ26980 saidВҰ26979 to MoshehВҰ26983, вҖңWhen you return to EgyptВҰ26986, all those miracles that I gave you, you'll be able to \add demonstrate\add* them in frontВҰ26996 of Far'ohВҰ26997 (Pharaoh), but as for me, I'm going to \add make him stubborn so that\add* he won'tВҰ27003 let \add your\add* peopleВҰ27007 leave.
\v 22 \add ButВҰ27009\add* tell Far'ohВҰ27012, вҖҳYahwehВҰ27015 has stated that Yisra'elВҰ27018 is \add like\add* his oldest son
\v 23 andВҰ27020 he asked you to let that son go so that he can serve him. ButВҰ27020 you refusedВҰ27027 to let \add Yisra'el\add* go, so \add Yahweh\add* will kill \em your\em* oldest son.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 4:23: \xt Exo 12:29.\x*
\p
\v 24 \add One night\add* as they were \add overnighting at\add* a lodgingВҰ27039 placeВҰ27039 near the road, YahwehВҰ27041 \add confronted Mosheh\add* andВҰ27037 would have killed him,
\v 25 \add but his wife\add* ZipporahВҰ27046 tookВҰ27045 a flintВҰ27047 \add knife\add* and cut off herВҰ27052 son'sВҰ27052 foreskinВҰ27051 and \add threw\add* it at \add Mosheh's\add* feetВҰ27054 saying, вҖңYou're definitely a bloodyВҰ27059 \add husband\add* to me.вҖқ
\v 26 (That was referring to circumcisionВҰ27069.) \add SoВҰ27063\add* thenВҰ27063 \add Yahweh left them aloneВҰ27063\add*.
\p
\v 27 \add Meanwhile\add* YahwehВҰ27073 had told AharonВҰ27076, вҖңGo \add out\add* into the wildernessВҰ27080 to meet MoshehВҰ27079.вҖқ \add So\add* he wentВҰ27081 and met him at the hill of GodВҰ27084, and he kissedВҰ27085 him.
\v 28 ThenВҰ27089 MoshehВҰ27090 told AharonВҰ27091 \add everything\add* that YahwehВҰ27096 had told him and how he had sentВҰ27098 him, and all the miracles that he commandedВҰ27104 him \add to demonstrate\add*.
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ27106 MoshehВҰ27107 and AharonВҰ27108 wentВҰ27106 \add to EgyptВҰ27116\add* and they assembledВҰ27109 all the \add IsraeliВҰ27115\add* eldersВҰ27114
\v 30 andВҰ27131 AharonВҰ27119 told them \add everything\add* thatВҰ27124 YahwehВҰ27127 had spokenВҰ27126 to Mosheh. ThenВҰ27118 \add Mosheh\add* did the miracles in front of \add them\add*,
\v 31 and the people believedВҰ27136. ThenВҰ27136 they heardВҰ27138 how YahwehВҰ27142 had paid attention to the IsraelisВҰ27146 and that he had seen theirВҰ27151 suffering, and they bowedВҰ27152 and prostrated themselves \add in thankfulness\add*.
\c 5
\s1 Mosheh challenges the Egyptian king
\rem /s1 Bricks Without Straw; Moses and Aaron Speak to Pharaoh; Moses and Aaron before the King of Egypt; Bricks without Straw
\p
\v 1 After that, MoshehВҰ27158 and AharonВҰ27159 wentВҰ27157 in and saidВҰ27160 to Far'ohВҰ27163, вҖңThis is what Yisrael'sВҰ27169 godВҰ27168 YahwehВҰ27167 saysВҰ27166: вҖҳLet my peopleВҰ27173 goВҰ27170, \add so\add* they can celebrate me \add out\add* in the wildernessВҰ27176.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 2 \add ButВҰ27178 the king\add* said, вҖңWho's \add this\add* вҖҳYahwehвҖҷ that I shouldВҰ27185 listenВҰ27183 to \add him telling me\add* to let YisraelВҰ27188 go? I don'tВҰ27189 know Yahweh, andВҰ27178 what's more, I won'tВҰ27189 let \add the Israelis\add* go \add anywhere\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңThe GodВҰ27202 of \add us\add* HebrewsВҰ27203 has met with us,вҖқ theyВҰ27201 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңPlease, let us goВҰ27206 threeВҰ27209 daysВҰ27210 into the wildernessВҰ27211 so we can sacrificeВҰ27212 to ourВҰ27214 god YahwehВҰ27213, \add because we don't want him to strikeВҰ27217\add* us with the plague or with \add war\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖңMoshehВҰ27227 andВҰ27228 AharonВҰ27228,вҖқ the kingВҰ27224 of EgyptВҰ27225 answered, вҖңwhy are youВҰ27229 causingВҰ27229 the peopleВҰ27232 to \add slacken\add* off from theirВҰ27233 tasks? \add GetВҰ27230 back\add* to yourВҰ27235 \add workВҰ27233\add*.вҖқ
\v 5 And Far'ohВҰ27238 \add continuedВҰ27237\add*, вҖңListen, there's many \add of you\add* andВҰ27237 you \add two\add* have caused them to rest from theirВҰ27247 \add duties\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Making Bricks without Straw
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ27249 on that \add very same\add* dayВҰ27251, Far'ohВҰ27250 orderedВҰ27249 the people'sВҰ27256 slave masters andВҰ27257 supervisors,
\v 7 вҖңDon't giveВҰ27264 straw to the peopleВҰ27266 to make bricksВҰ27268 with as \add you've done up till now\add*. They can go and gatherВҰ27273 straw for themselves.
\v 8 ButВҰ27277 \add keep\add* the \add same\add* quota of bricksВҰ27280 \add as before\add*вҖ”don'tВҰ27288 decrease it because they \add must be\add* idle \add if they have time to say\add*, вҖҳLet us goвҖ”let us sacrificeВҰ27302 to our godВҰ27303.вҖҷ
\v 9 \add Give the menВҰ27309 more workВҰ27306 so they'll be too busy to worry about deceptive wordsВҰ27316\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add SoВҰ27320\add* the slave masters and supervisors of the people went out and told \add them all\add*, вҖң\add The king\add* has said that he won'tВҰ27332 give you any more strawВҰ27335,
\v 11 \add so\add* you'll \add all have to\add* goВҰ27338 and get your own strawВҰ27341 from wherever you can find it, because there'llВҰ27345 be no reduction to your \add quota\add*.вҖқ
\v 12 SoВҰ27350 the peopleВҰ27351 dispersed throughout all of EgyptВҰ27355 to gatherВҰ27356 stubbleВҰ27357 for strawВҰ27358,
\v 13 and the taskmastersВҰ27360 were \add hassling\add* them, saying, вҖң\add Hurry up and\add* finish yourВҰ27364 day's workВҰ27364, the same as when \add you were given\add* strawВҰ27371.вҖқ
\v 14 ThenВҰ27373 the IsraeliВҰ27375 foremenВҰ27374 that Far'oh's slave masters had appointedВҰ27379 were beatenВҰ27373 andВҰ27373 told, вҖңWhy haven't youВҰ27386 met yourВҰ27387 requiredВҰ27387 brickВҰ27388 making \add quota\add* yesterday or today? \add It's just the same as in the past\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add SoВҰ27398\add* the IsraeliВҰ27400 foremenВҰ27399 wentВҰ27398 andВҰ27402 complained to Far'ohВҰ27405, вҖңWhyВҰ27401 are youВҰ27408 treating yourВҰ27410 servantsВҰ27410 like this?
\v 16 We haven't been givenВҰ27414 any straw and yet they're telling us to keep making bricksВҰ27416. And see, we your servants get beaten, but it's your people'sВҰ27424 mistake.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңYou're all lazyвҖ”plain lazy!вҖқ \add the king respondedВҰ27426\add*. вҖңThat's why you're sayingВҰ27434, вҖҳLet us goВҰ27435 sacrificeВҰ27436 to YahwehВҰ27437.вҖҷ
\v 18 \add SoВҰ27439\add* goВҰ27440 now! \add Back to\add* workВҰ27441! And you won'tВҰ27443 be givenВҰ27445 strawВҰ27442, but you \add still have to meet the quotaВҰ27447\add* of bricksВҰ27448.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add WhenВҰ27455\add* the IsraeliВҰ27453 foremenВҰ27452 heard that the quota wasn't going to be reduced, theyВҰ27451 \add realised how serious their problem was\add*,
\v 20 \add so\add* when they left Far'ohВҰ27479 they \add confronted\add* MoshehВҰ27471 andВҰ27468 AharonВҰ27474 who were waiting to meet them,
\v 21 вҖңMay YahwehВҰ27484 \add see what you've done and judgeВҰ27486 you for it\add* because you've \add raised a big stinkВҰ27488 in Far'oh's mind\add* and with his servants. \add Now theyВҰ27481 have theirВҰ27499 excuse\add* to killВҰ27500 us!вҖқ
\s1 Mosheh complains to God
\rem /s1 Moses Complains to the Lord; God Promises Deliverance
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ27502 MoshehВҰ27503 went back to YahwehВҰ27506 andВҰ27502 \add asked\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ27508, why have you \add taken it out on our\add* peopleВҰ27511? Was this why you sent me?
\v 23 \add Ever\add* sinceВҰ27517 I went to Far'ohВҰ27521 to \add deliverВҰ27530 your message\add*, he's \add made\add* these people \add suffer\add* andВҰ27517 you \add clearly\add* haven't rescued \add them\add*.вҖқ
\c 6
\rem /s1 Israel's Deliverance Assured; Promises of Deliverance
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ27535 YahwehВҰ27536 saidВҰ27535 to MoshehВҰ27539, вҖңNow you'll seeВҰ27541 what I'll do to Far'ohВҰ27544. \add I'll use my power to force him to\add* let them goВҰ27548, andВҰ27535 thenВҰ27535 \add using my power again\add* he'll \add actually\add* driveВҰ27551 them out of his \add country\add*.вҖқ
\s1 God promises to rescue the people
\rem /s1 God Calls Moses
\p
\v 2 Then GodВҰ27556 spokeВҰ27555 to MoshehВҰ27559 \add again\add*, вҖңI am YahwehВҰ27563\x + \xo 6:2-3: \xt Gen 17:1; 28:3; 35:11; Exo 3:13-15.\x*
\v 3 and I \add revealed myselfВҰ27580\add* to AbrahamВҰ27568, to IsaacВҰ27571, and to YacobВҰ27574 as El Shaddai (GodВҰ27575 the provider) but they didn'tВҰ27579 know me by my nameВҰ27577 YahwehВҰ27578.
\v 4 \add What's more,\add* I made an agreement with them: to giveВҰ27589 them the CanaanВҰ27594 regionвҖ”the area whichВҰ27598 theyВҰ27600 had been staying in.
\v 5 \add Furthermore,\add* I've heardВҰ27606 the complaints from the IsraelisВҰ27611 who have been enslaved by the Egyptians, andВҰ27616 I have rememberedВҰ27616 my agreement.
\v 6 Therefore, tell the IsraelisВҰ27625, вҖҳI am YahwehВҰ27628 and I will \add help you escape from\add* the \add control\add* of the Egyptians and rescue you from theirВҰ27636 slavery. I'll buy you out of slavery using my power and by \add punishing the Egyptians for this injustice\add*.
\v 7 I'll takeВҰ27644 you all to be my own peopleВҰ27647, andВҰ27644 I'll be your god. ThenВҰ27644 you'll knowВҰ27651 that I am YahwehВҰ27654 your godвҖ”the one rescuing you all from the Egyptian oppression.
\v 8 ThenВҰ27662 I'll \add take\add* you all to the land thatВҰ27667 I \add promised\add* to give to AbrahamВҰ27674, to Yitshak, and to YacobВҰ27676, and I'll give it to you as \add your own\add*. I am YahwehВҰ27682.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 9 \add SoВҰ27684\add* Mosheh \add passed all that on\add* to the IsraelisВҰ27690, but they wouldn't listenВҰ27692 to Mosheh, because they were \add both discouraged andВҰ27684 worn out from the slavery\add*.
\p
\v 10 Then YahwehВҰ27703 told MoshehВҰ27706,
\v 11 вҖңGo and speakВҰ27710 to the Egyptian kingВҰ27714 Far'ohВҰ27713 and \add tell him\add* that he needsВҰ27716 to let the IsraelisВҰ27721 leave his country.вҖқ
\v 12 And MoshehВҰ27725 said in frontВҰ27726 of YahwehВҰ27727, вҖңLook, the IsraelisВҰ27732 haven't listenedВҰ27735 to me, so why would Far'ohВҰ27739 listenВҰ27738? And I have \add difficulty speaking\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Family Record of Moses and Aaron
\v 13 Then YahwehВҰ27746 spokeВҰ27745 to MoshehВҰ27749 and AharonВҰ27752, and he gave them a commandВҰ27753 to \add pass on to\add* the Israelis and to the Egyptian kingВҰ27761 Far'ohВҰ27760: to \add take\add* the Israelis out of EgyptВҰ27762.
\s1 The ancestors of Mosheh and Aharon
\rem /s1 The Ancestors of Moses and Aaron; The Family Record of Moses and Aaron; The Genealogy of Moses and Aaron
\p
\v 14 The following were the leaders of the clans:
\p The sonsВҰ27778 of \bd Reuben\bd* (Yisra'el's eldest son) were HanochВҰ27782, PalluВҰ27783, HezronВҰ27784, and Karmi, and \add they headed\add* the clans of Reuben.
\p
\v 15 \bd Simeon\bd*'s sonsВҰ27790 were Yemuel, YaminВҰ27793, Ohad, Yakin, ZoharВҰ27796, and ShaulВҰ27797вҖ”the son of a CanaaniteВҰ27800 woman, and \add they headed\add* the clansВҰ27802 of Simeon.
\p
\v 16 \bd Levi\bd*'s sonsВҰ27807 were GershonВҰ27811, KohathВҰ27812, andВҰ27805 MerariВҰ27813. Levi was 137 yearsВҰ27814 old when he died.\x + \xo 6:16-19: \xt Num 3:17-20; 26:57-58; 1Ch 6:16-19.\x*
\v 17 Gershon'sВҰ27823 sonsВҰ27822 were LibniВҰ27824 and ShimeiВҰ27825, and \add they headed\add* theirВҰ27826 clansВҰ27826.
\v 18 Kohath'sВҰ27829 sonsВҰ27828 were AmramВҰ27830, IzharВҰ27831, HebronВҰ27832, andВҰ27828 UzzielВҰ27833. Kohath was 133 yearsВҰ27834 old when he died.
\v 19 Merari'sВҰ27843 sonsВҰ27842 were MahliВҰ27844 and MushiВҰ27845, and \add all of those headed\add* the clansВҰ27847 of LeviВҰ27848.
\v 20 Amram married his aunt YochebedВҰ27855, and she gaveВҰ27859 birthВҰ27859 to AharonВҰ27863 and MoshehВҰ27866. Amram lived to be 137 yearsВҰ27867 old.
\v 21 Izhar'sВҰ27876 sonsВҰ27875 were KorahВҰ27877, NefegВҰ27878, andВҰ27875 ZichriВҰ27879.
\v 22 Uzziel'sВҰ27882 sonsВҰ27881 were MishaelВҰ27883, ElzafanВҰ27884, andВҰ27881 SithriВҰ27885.
\p
\v 23 AharonВҰ27888 \add married\add* ElishebaВҰ27891, Amminadab'sВҰ27894 daughterВҰ27892 and the sisterВҰ27895 of NahshonВҰ27896, and she gaveВҰ27899 birthВҰ27899 to NadabВҰ27903, AbihuВҰ27906, EleazarВҰ27909, and IthamarВҰ27912.
\v 24 Korah'sВҰ27915 sonsВҰ27914 were AssirВҰ27916, ElkanahВҰ27917, and AbiasaphВҰ27918, and \add they headed\add* the clansВҰ27920 of Korah.
\v 25 Aharon's son Eleazar tookВҰ27927 a wife for himself from the daughtersВҰ27930 of PutielВҰ27931 andВҰ27934 she gaveВҰ27934 birthВҰ27934 to Finehas.
\p \add All of\add* those \add headed\add* the clansВҰ27943 of Levi.
\p
\v 26 It was to AharonВҰ27946 and MoshehВҰ27947 that YahwehВҰ27950 had saidВҰ27949, вҖңBring the IsraelisВҰ27956 out of EgyptВҰ27958 by theirВҰ27961 \add tribes\add*.вҖқ
\v 27 They were the ones who spokeВҰ27964 to the Egyptian kingВҰ27968 Far'ohВҰ27967, to bringВҰ27971 the IsraelisВҰ27976 out of EgyptВҰ27970.
\s1 God's reassurances to Mosheh and Aharon
\rem /s1 Moses and Aaron Obey God's Commands; Aaron to Speak for Moses; The Lord's Command to Moses and Aaron; The struggle with Pharaoh
\p
\v 28 On the dayВҰ27983 that YahwehВҰ27985 spokeВҰ27984 to MoshehВҰ27988 in EgyptВҰ27990,
\v 29 he said, вҖңI am YahwehВҰ27994. Tell the Egyptian king Far'ohВҰ28004 everything that I tell you.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖңPlease listen to me,вҖқ MoshehВҰ28016 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ28015\add*. вҖңI'm \add not a good speaker\add*, so why should Far'ohВҰ28026 listen to me?вҖқ
\c 7
\rem /s1 Aaron's Staff Becomes a Snake
\p
\v 1 YahwehВҰ28030 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңListen, I've made youВҰ28035 \add like\add* GodВҰ28036 to Far'ohВҰ28037, and your brotherВҰ28039 AharonВҰ28038 will be your prophetВҰ28041.
\v 2 You'll \add quietly\add* say everything that I tell you to and then your brotherВҰ28051 AharonВҰ28050 will \add relay it\add* to Far'ohВҰ28055 \add and tell him\add* that he must let the IsraelisВҰ28061 leave his country.
\v 3 \add ButВҰ28064\add* I'll \add make\add* Far'ohВҰ28069 \add stubbornВҰ28065\add* and \add so\add* I'll increase the signsВҰ28073 and miracles \add that I'll do\add* in EgyptВҰ28078.\x + \xo 7:3: \xt Acts 7:36.\x*
\v 4 Far'ohВҰ28084 won'tВҰ28080 listenВҰ28082 to you so I'll \add pressure\add* Egypt, andВҰ28080 I'll use severe judgementsВҰ28102 \add to ensure that I\add* bringВҰ28090 my armiesвҖ”my people the IsraelisВҰ28099вҖ”out Egypt.
\v 5 The Egyptians will knowВҰ28105 that I am YahwehВҰ28110 when I \add demonstrate my power to\add* EgyptВҰ28117 \add by taking\add* the IsraelisВҰ28123 out from the middle of them.вҖқ
\v 6 \add SoВҰ28132\add* MoshehВҰ28127 andВҰ28128 AharonВҰ28128 did everything that YahwehВҰ28131 told them to do.
\v 7 (MoshehВҰ28136 was eighty andВҰ28136 AharonВҰ28141 was eighty-three when they were \add interacting with\add* Far'ohВҰ28150.)
\s1 Staffs and snakes
\rem /s1 Aaron's Staff Becomes a Snake; Aaron's Walking Stick; Aaron's Miraculous Rod
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ28154 told MoshehВҰ28157 and AharonВҰ28160,
\v 9 вҖң\add When\add* Far'oh tells you to perform a miracle \add as a sign\add*, then \add just\add* tell Aharon to takeВҰ28175 his\f + \fr 7:9 \ft It's not clear here in this account, or even in the following events, if Mosheh and Aharon had separate miraculous sticks, or if Mosheh had (temporarily?) entrusted his original staff/rod/stick to his brother and spokesman Aharon.\f*staff and throwВҰ28179 it down in frontВҰ28180 of Far'oh so it turns into a snakeВҰ28184.вҖқ
\v 10 \add SoВҰ28186\add* MoshehВҰ28187 and Aharon wentВҰ28186 in to Far'oh's \add court\add* and did what YahwehВҰ28197 had told them: Aharon threwВҰ28198 his staffВҰ28202 down in frontВҰ28203 of Far'oh and his servants and it turned into a snakeВҰ28208.
\v 11 ThenВҰ28210 Far'ohВҰ28213 also calledВҰ28210 for \add his\add* wise men and sorcerersВҰ28215, and the Egyptian magicians did \add the same thing\add* using theirВҰ28222 magicвҖ”
\v 12 each \add of them\add* threwВҰ28225 down his staff andВҰ28225 theyВҰ28228 became snakesВҰ28229, \add except that\add* Aharon'sВҰ28234 staff swallowedВҰ28230 up theirВҰ28236 staffs.
\v 13 \add ButВҰ28238\add* Far'oh'sВҰ28240 \add mindВҰ28239 was made up\add* andВҰ28238 he \add took no notice of them\add* as YahwehВҰ28246 had saidВҰ28245 \add earlier\add*.
\s1 Plague 1: Water to blood
\rem /s1 A Plague of Blood; The Plague of Blood; The First Plague: Water Turned to Blood; Disasters Strike Egypt
\p
\v 14 Then YahwehВҰ28250 told MoshehВҰ28253, вҖңFar'ohВҰ28256 \add is very stubborn andВҰ28249\add* he's refusedВҰ28257 to let the peopleВҰ28259 goВҰ28258.
\v 15 \add So\add* go to Far'ohВҰ28264. Listen, \add every\add* morningВҰ28265 he goes \add down\add* to the \add river\add*, so station yourself to meet him on the bank. Take the staffВҰ28275 with you thatВҰ28276 turned into a snakeВҰ28279,
\v 16 andВҰ28283 tell him, вҖҳYahwehВҰ28285, the godВҰ28286 of the HebrewsВҰ28287, \add previously\add* sent me to you to say, вҖңLetВҰ28292 my peopleВҰ28294 goВҰ28291 \add so\add* they can serve me in the wildernessВҰ28296.вҖқ ButВҰ28283 listenВҰ28300, untilВҰ28301 now you haven't \add done it\add*
\v 17 so Yahweh saysВҰ28306, вҖң\add Now\add* youВҰ28309 will knowВҰ28309 thatВҰ28318 I am Yahweh because of this: See, I'm aboutВҰ28315 to use my staffВҰ28317 to strikeВҰ28315 the waterВҰ28323 in the Nile and it will turn to bloodВҰ28327\x + \xo 7:17: \xt Rev 16:4.\x*
\v 18 and the fishВҰ28329 in the river will die and the river will stinkВҰ28334. ThenВҰ28329 \add your people\add* will \add gag\add* to drinkВҰ28338 \add the\add* waterВҰ28339 from the river.вҖқ вҖҷ
\p
\v 19 вҖңTell AharonВҰ28353 to take his staffВҰ28355 and stretchВҰ28356 out his hand over the waters of EgyptВҰ28362: over their streams, their canalsВҰ28369, and their pools, and over everyВҰ28374 reservoir of their water, and \add the water\add* will becomeВҰ28378 blood. Then there'll be blood in \add the entireВҰ28383 country\add*вҖ”even in wooden or stoneВҰ28388 containers \add of water\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add SoВҰ28390\add* And MoshehВҰ28393 and Aharon did \add exactly\add* what YahwehВҰ28398 had commandedВҰ28397: \add Aharon\add* raisedВҰ28399 the staffВҰ28400 and struckВҰ28401 the river, while Far'ohВҰ28408 and his servants \add watched\add*, and the \add entireВҰ28412\add* river turnedВҰ28411 to bloodВҰ28418.
\v 21 ThenВҰ28420 the fishВҰ28420 in the river died and the river stankВҰ28425, so the Egyptians couldn't drinkВҰ28431 waterВҰ28432 from the river, and the bloodВҰ28437 was all \add over\add* EgyptВҰ28430.
\v 22 \add ButВҰ28443\add* the EgyptianВҰ28447 sorcerers did the same with theirВҰ28448 magic, and \add so\add* Far'ohВҰ28452 \add stayed stubborn\add* and wouldn't listenВҰ28455 to them, just as YahwehВҰ28459 had saidВҰ28458 \add earlier\add*.
\v 23 The Far'ohВҰ28462 turnedВҰ28461 around and wentВҰ28463 \add back to\add* his houseВҰ28466, and heВҰ28469 \add put all of that out of his mindВҰ28470\add*.
\v 24 \add Meanwhile,\add* all the Egyptians dug holes aroundВҰ28479 the river to get water to drink, because river water was undrinkable.
\s1 Plague 2: Frogs everywhere
\p
\v 25 \add SoВҰ28490\add* a week went by since YahwehВҰ28496 had struckВҰ28494 the river
\c 8
\rem /s2 Frogs
\rem /s1 The Second Plague: Frogs; A Plague of Frogs
\v 1 and \add he\add* saidВҰ28567 to MoshehВҰ28571, вҖңGo to Far'oh and tell him, вҖҳYahwehВҰ28568 says that you \add must\add* let my people go \add so \add* they can serve me.\f + \fr 8:1 \ft This is 7:26 in some versifications (and the following three verses are 7:27, 28, & 29).\f*
\v 2 \add But\add* if you refuse to let \add them\add* go, then look, I'm about to pound your entire territory with frogsВҰ28609.
\v 3 The frogsВҰ28625 will swarm in the river, then they'll climb out and go into your house and in your bedroom and onto your bed. They'll go into your servants' houses and among your people, and in your \add cooking\add* bowls and into your ovens.
\v 4 They'll climb on you and on your people and on all your servants.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 5 Then Yahweh saidВҰ28653 to MoshehВҰ28654, вҖңTell Aharon: Hold your staff out over the canals, the streams, and the pools, and cause the frogsВҰ28665 to come up onto the land of Egypt.вҖқ
\v 6 \add So\add* Aharon reached out his hand over the Egyptian water \add supplies\add* and frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt.
\v 7 \add But\add* the sorcerers did the same with their magic, and theyВҰ28694 \add too\add* brought up frogsВҰ28687 over the land of Egypt.
\p
\v 8 Then Far'ohВҰ28701 called for Mosheh and AharonВҰ28699, and told \add them\add*, вҖңAsk Yahweh to take the frogsВҰ28710 away from me and from my people. Then I'll let \add your\add* people go, and they can sacrifice to Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 MoshehВҰ28720 answered, вҖңI'll pray for you and your servants and your people, \add praying that\add* the frogsВҰ28722 will keep away from you and your homes and only be left in the river. \add And I'll give you the honour of specifying when it'll happen\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңTomorrow \add morning\add*,вҖқ \add the king replied\add*.
\p вҖңJust as you say,вҖқ \add Mosheh responded\add*, вҖңso that you'll know that there's no one \add else\add* like our god Yahweh.
\v 11 \add Tomorrow\add* the frogs will leave you and go away from your houses, and from your servants and your people. They'll only be left in the river.вҖқ
\v 12 Then Mosheh and AharonВҰ28768 left Far'oh and Mosheh called out to YahwehВҰ28761 concerning the \add retraction\add* of the frogs that he'd sent against \add the king\add*.
\v 13 \add So\add* Yahweh did what Mosheh had requested and the frogs died off from the houses and the courtyards, and from the fields.
\v 14 \add TheВҰ28822 people\add* collected them into many piles and the \add whole country\add* stank.
\v 15 \add But when\add* Far'ohВҰ28837 saw that there was \add relief from the frogs\add*, he \add firmed his resolve\add* and didn'tВҰ28845 listenВҰ28847 to \add Mosheh and Aharon\add*, just as YahwehВҰ28851 had said \add previously\add*.
\s1 Plague 3: Lice
\rem /s1 A Plague of Gnats; The Third Plague: Gnats; The Plague of Gnats
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ28856 saidВҰ28855 to MoshehВҰ28859, вҖңTell Aharon: Stretch out your staff and strike the dust on the ground, and it will turn into lice\f + \fr 8:16 \ft The Hebrew word вҖҳЧӣЦөЦјЧҹ/ЧӣЦҙЦјЧ ЦҙЦјЧқвҖҷ (kД“n/kinnim) could refer to either lice, gnats, or fleas. However, unlike lice, gnats don't usually \em reside\em* on people and animals (which seems to be implied by the text).\f* all over Egypt.вҖқ
\v 17 So Aharon held out his staff and struck the dust \add with it\add*, and \add the dust\add* became lice on the people and on the animals. All over EgyptВҰ28897, the dust turned into lice
\v 18 and the sorcerers tried to do the same with their magic but they were unable to. \add So\add* thereВҰ28923 were lice on peopleВҰ28917 and animals
\v 19 and the magicians said to Far'oh, вҖңThis is God's finger.вҖқ \add But Far'oh was stubborn\add* and he didn't listen to them, just as Yahweh had said \add previously\add*.\x + \xo 8:19: \xt Luk 11:20.\x*
\s1 Plague 4: The swarm
\rem /s1 The Fourth Plague: Flies; A Plague of Flies; The Plague of Flies
\p
\v 20 Then Yahweh said to Mosheh, вҖңGet up early in the morning and \add when you see Far'ohВҰ28953\add* coming down to the river, station yourself in frontВҰ28962 of \add him\add* and tell him, вҖҳYahweh saw that you \add must\add* let my people go \add so \add* they can serve me.
\v 21 Certainly if you don't release my people immediately, then take note: I'm about to send the swarm\f + \fr 8:21 \ft The Hebrew word вҖҳЧўЦёЧЁЦ№Ч‘вҖҷ (ЛҠДҒrov) probably meaning вҖҳmixtureвҖҷ is sometimes translated as вҖҳswarmвҖҷ. This plague could have been anything from flies to other insects (hornets or mosquitoes???) all the way to a mixture of wild animals.\f* at you and your servants and at your people and into your houses. The Egyptians' houses will be full of the swarm and even the ground that they're on.
\v 22 \add But when it happens,\add* I'll distinguish the Goshen region where my people live so the swarm won'tВҰ28981 be there, \add so that you'll be able to see\add* that I'm YahwehВҰ28989 \add and I'm right here\add* in this land.
\v 23 This sign will happen tomorrow andВҰ29007 \add you'll see how I plan to set my people free\add* from your people.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 24 \add So\add* YahwehВҰ29021 did \add what he'd saidВҰ29015\add* and a heavy swarm came to Far'oh's house and the houses of his servants and all the EgyptiansвҖ”the country was ruined by the \add arrival\add* of the swarm.
\p
\v 25 Then Far'ohВҰ29046 called for MoshehВҰ29035 and to Aharon and told \add them\add*, вҖңGo and sacrificeВҰ29061 to the god of youВҰ29039 all, \add but here in Egypt\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңIt wouldn't be right to do that,вҖқ MoshehВҰ29066 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңbecause our sacrifices to YahwehВҰ29072 our god \add would be offensive\add* to Egyptians. Listen, if we made sacrifices in front of the Egyptians \add that are repulsive to them\add*, wouldn't they \add throw rocks at us to try to kill us\add*?
\v 27 We need to travel into the wilderness for three days, then we'll sacrifice to our god YahwehВҰ29076 \add there\add*, just like he's telling us to.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \add So\add* Far'ohВҰ29090 \add relented\add*, вҖңI'll let you all go into the wilderness and sacrifice to Yahweh your godвҖ”except you definitely can'tВҰ29097 go very far. \add Now,\add* ask God for me \add for the plague to stop\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖңListen, I'm about to \add leave now\add*,вҖқ Mosheh \add вүҲresponded\add*, вҖңand I'll pray to Yahweh and he'll withdraw the swarm from Far'oh tomorrow, and from his servants and his people. \add But\add* may Far'oh not be dishonest \add again and\add* fail to let our people go to sacrifice to Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 Then Mosheh left Far'oh and prayed to Yahweh
\v 31 and Yahweh did \add what\add* Mosheh \add asked him\add* and he withdrew the swarm from Far'oh, and from his servants and his people. Not one remained.
\v 32 \add But\add* Far'oh \add changed his mind and remained stubborn and he wouldn't let the Israelis leave\add*.
\c 9
\s1 Plague 5: The stock disease
\rem /s2 Death of the Animals
\rem /s1 The Fifth Plague: Livestock Diseased; The Plague on Livestock; A Plague against Livestock
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh said to MoshehВҰ29108, вҖңGo in to Far'ohВҰ29112 and tell him: вҖҳThis is what the godВҰ29119 of the HebrewsВҰ29120. Yahweh, says: Let my peopleВҰ29124 go \add so\add* they can serve me.
\v 2 Certainly if you'reВҰ29133 unwilling to release them and if you keep holding onto them,
\v 3 then listen. YahwehВҰ29140 is aboutВҰ29141 to \add inflict\add* a very serious plague on yourВҰ29142 livestockВҰ29142 whichВҰ29143 are in the fieldsВҰ29144вҖ”on the horsesВҰ29145, the donkeysВҰ29146, the camelsВҰ29147, the cattle, and on the flockВҰ29149.
\v 4 \add ButВҰ29154\add* YahwehВҰ29155 will distinguishВҰ29154 between the livestock of the Israelis andВҰ29154 the EgyptiansвҖ”none of the Israelis' animals will dieВҰ29163.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ29170 Yahweh \add said when it would happen\add*, вҖңYahweh will do this \add to Egypt\add* tomorrowВҰ29174.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add SoВҰ29181\add* the next dayВҰ29187 YahwehВҰ29182 did \add what he'd said\add* andВҰ29181 all of the livestock of the EgyptiansВҰ29191 died, yet none at all from the livestock of the IsraelisВҰ29195 died.
\v 7 Far'oh sent \add people to investigate\add*, and wow, not even one of the livestockВҰ29207 of the IsraelisВҰ29208 had died. \add ButВҰ29201\add* Far'oh was strong-willed and wouldn't let the people go.
\s1 Plague 6: Boils
\rem /s1 The Plague of Boils; The Sixth Plague: Boils; A Plague of Boils
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ29223 told Mosheh and AharonВҰ29229, вҖңTake handfuls of ash out of a furnace, then Mosheh should \add toss it up in the air in front\add* of Far'ohВҰ29240.
\v 9 It will become a powder over all Egypt and thenВҰ29242 it will turn into boilsВҰ29256вҖ”bursting blistersВҰ29258вҖ”on people and on animals all over Egypt.вҖқ
\v 10 \add SoВҰ29264\add* they tookВҰ29264 some ash from a furnace, and standing in frontВҰ29270 of Far'ohВҰ29271, MoshehВҰ29274 \add tossed it up into the air\add* and it turned into boils with bursting blistersВҰ29278 on the people and the animals.\x + \xo 9:10: \xt Rev 16:2.\x*
\v 11 Because of the boils, the sorcerers weren't \add even\add* able to standВҰ29287 \add there with\add* MoshehВҰ29289 because the sorcerers \add suffered with them\add* along with all the Egyptians.
\v 12 \add ButВҰ29301\add* Yahweh caused Far'ohВҰ29306 to remain stubborn andВҰ29301 he didn'tВҰ29307 listenВҰ29308 to them, just as Yahweh had told MoshehВҰ29315 \add previously\add*.
\s1 Plague 7: Hail
\rem /s1 A Plague of Hail; The Seventh Plague: Thunder and Hail; The Plague of Hail
\p
\v 13 Then Yahweh told MoshehВҰ29322, вҖңGet up earlyВҰ29323 in the morningВҰ29324, and stand in frontВҰ29326 of Far'ohВҰ29327 and sayВҰ29328 to him, вҖҳThis is what Yahweh, the godВҰ29334 of the HebrewsВҰ29335, saysВҰ29332: Let my peopleВҰ29339 goВҰ29336 so they can serve me
\v 14 because this timeВҰ29344, I'm aboutВҰ29347 to sendВҰ29347 all my plaguesВҰ29352 to you and your servants, and your peopleВҰ29357. \add You'll all be deeply distressed by them\add*, in order that you might knowВҰ29359 that thereВҰ29361 is no \add one else\add* like me in all the world.
\v 15 \add By this time\add*, I could have reached out and struckВҰ29373 you and your peopleВҰ29377 with such a plagueВҰ29378 that you would all have been obliterated from the land.
\v 16 However, I've kept you for this reason: to show you my powerВҰ29392 andВҰ29384 in order to proclaim my nameВҰ29395 all over the world.\x + \xo 9:16: \xt Rom 9:17.\x*
\v 17 You're still considering yourselfВҰ29401 to be greater than my peopleВҰ29402 by failing to release them.
\v 18 \add Now\add* listen: I'm aboutВҰ29407 to cause extremely heavyВҰ29411 hail to rain \add down\add* at this timeВҰ29408 tomorrowВҰ29409. \add It'll be hail like\add* whichВҰ29413 has never been \add seen before\add* in EgyptВҰ29418 from the dayВҰ29421 it was foundedВҰ29422 until now.
\v 19 \add SoВҰ29427\add* sendВҰ29428 for your livestockВҰ29432 and everything you own in the country now, and bringВҰ29429 it in under cover because the hail will come down on every person and animalВҰ29442 thatВҰ29443 is foundВҰ29445 in the countrysideВҰ29438 and not \add sheltering under a roof\add*, and they will dieВҰ29453.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 20 Some of Far'oh's servantsВҰ29465 who believed what YahwehВҰ29459 said, quickly brought their slaves andВҰ29466 their livestockВҰ29468 back into their housesВҰ29471,
\v 21 but those \add people\add* who didn'tВҰ29474 believe YahwehВҰ29481 \add just\add* left their slaves andВҰ29473 their animals out in the countrysideВҰ29489.
\p
\v 22 вҖңRaise yourВҰ29500 arm up toward the sky,вҖқ YahwehВҰ29493 told MoshehВҰ29496, вҖңand hail \add will strike\add* all over EgyptВҰ29509вҖ”on the people and animals and on every plant in the Egyptian countrysideВҰ29520.вҖқ
\v 23 \add SoВҰ29524\add* MoshehВҰ29525 lifted his staffВҰ29528 to the sky, and Yahweh sent thunderВҰ29534 and hail, and \add lightning caused fires\add* on the land, and \add so\add* Yahweh rainedВҰ29539 hail \add down\add* onto EgyptВҰ29545.
\v 24 There was hail, andВҰ29547 \add also\add* fireВҰ29549 coming \add down\add* in the middleВҰ29551 of the hail. It was very heavyВҰ29553, such as had never been in all of EgyptВҰ29563 sinceВҰ29564 it became a nationВҰ29566.\x + \xo 9:24: \xt Rev 8:7; 16:21.\x*
\v 25 The hail struck everything in EgyptВҰ29573вҖ”everything that was in the countryside, from people to animals. \add It also\add* struck every plant andВҰ29568 broke every treeВҰ29594 \add out\add* in the countryside.
\v 26 Only in the GoshenВҰ29600 region whereВҰ29601 the IsraelisВҰ29605 were, was thereВҰ29603 no hail.
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ29610 Far'ohВҰ29611 sentВҰ29610 for MoshehВҰ29613 and AharonВҰ29614 and told them, вҖңI've sinnedВҰ29617 this timeВҰ29618. YahwehВҰ29619 is righteousВҰ29620, and me and my peopleВҰ29622 are guilty.
\v 28 Pray to YahwehВҰ29628 \add to stop it,\add* because the thunderВҰ29631 of GodВҰ29632 and hail are too much. Then I'll release you allвҖ”you won'tВҰ29636 have to remain \add here\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖңAs I'm leaving the cityВҰ29646,вҖқ MoshehВҰ29642 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI'll spreadВҰ29647 my palms \add out\add* to Yahweh. The thunderВҰ29654 will stop andВҰ29640 the hail won'tВҰ29657 continue so that youВҰ29662 \add will be able to see\add* that the earthВҰ29665 belongs to Yahweh.
\v 30 \add ButВҰ29667 as for\add* you andВҰ29668 yourВҰ29668 servants, IВҰ29669 knowВҰ29669 that you still don'tВҰ29671 fearВҰ29672 YahwehВҰ29674 GodВҰ29675.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 (\add NowВҰ29680\add* the flax and the barley were \add flattened by the hail\add* because the barley was \add full grown and starting to fill out\add* and the flax was in bloom.
\v 32 ButВҰ29690 the wheatВҰ29686 andВҰ29686 the speltВҰ29687 weren't \add destroyed because they come later in the season\add*.)
\p
\v 33 \add SoВҰ29698\add* MoshehВҰ29695 left Far'ohВҰ29697, and as he was leaving the cityВҰ29700, he spreadВҰ29701 his palms \add out\add* to YahwehВҰ29705 and the thunderВҰ29707 and hail ceasedВҰ29706, and the rain stopped pouring down on the land.
\v 34 \add ButВҰ29717 when\add* Far'ohВҰ29716 sawВҰ29715 that the rain and hail and thunderВҰ29722 had stopped, he added to his sins and he \add firmed his resolve\add*вҖ”he and his servants.
\v 35 AndВҰ29735 \add so\add* Far'ohВҰ29732 \add remained stubborn\add* andВҰ29730 didn'tВҰ29733 let the IsraelisВҰ29738 leave, just as YahwehВҰ29741 had saidВҰ29740 through MoshehВҰ29744 \add previously\add*.
\c 10
\s1 Plague 8: Locusts
\rem /s1 A Plague of Locusts; The Plague of Locusts; The Eighth Plague: Locusts
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ29748 told MoshehВҰ29751, вҖңGo in to Far'ohВҰ29755 because I've made him and his servants \add stubborn\add* in order to \add be able to\add* demonstrate theseВҰ29770 miracles of mine among them,
\v 2 and so that \add in the future you'll be able to tell your descendants\add* that I \add made\add* Egypt \add look foolish\add*, and my miracles whichВҰ29788 I demonstrated among themвҖ”and \add so that\add* you will knowВҰ29792 that I am YahwehВҰ29796.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add SoВҰ29798\add* MoshehВҰ29799 and AharonВҰ29800 wentВҰ29798 in to Far'ohВҰ29803 and told him, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ29809, GodВҰ29810 of the HebrewsВҰ29811 saysВҰ29808: \add how long beforeВҰ29817 you'll submit to me\add*? Let myВҰ29817 peopleВҰ29819 goВҰ29818 \add so\add* theyВҰ29804 can serve me,
\v 4 because if youВҰ29826 refuseВҰ29825 to release them, then listen, I'llВҰ29831 bringВҰ29832 locustsВҰ29834 into yourВҰ29835 territoryВҰ29835 tomorrowВҰ29833.
\v 5 They'll coverВҰ29837 the ground so that no one will \add even\add* be able to see it, andВҰ29837 they'll devour whatever remainsВҰ29852 after the hail. Plus they'll devour everyВҰ29862 treeВҰ29864 growingВҰ29865 in the countrysideВҰ29869.
\v 6 They'll fill your houses and the houses of all your servantsВҰ29876 and the houses of all the Egyptians. It'll be nothing like anything whichВҰ29881 your \add parents generation\add* ever saw, nor anything seen by the \add previous generations\add* from the day they came to be on the earth untilВҰ29893 today.вҖқ ThenВҰ29871 \add Mosheh\add* turnedВҰ29896 around and wentВҰ29889 out from Far'ohВҰ29899 \add with Aharon\add*.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ29901 Far'oh's servantsВҰ29902 \add asked\add* him, вҖңHow much longer is this \add going to cause trouble\add* for us? Let the menВҰ29915 goВҰ29912 andВҰ29916 they'll worshipВҰ29916 theirВҰ29920 godВҰ29920 YahwehВҰ29919. Don't youВҰ29922 understand yet that EgyptВҰ29925 \add is being destroyed\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add SoВҰ29927\add* MoshehВҰ29930 and AharonВҰ29933 were broughtВҰ29927 back to Far'ohВҰ29936, and he told them, вҖңGo and worship yourВҰ29944 godВҰ29944 YahwehВҰ29943. Who \add are the ones\add* who'll be goingВҰ29947?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңWe'll take our children and our old folks,вҖқ MoshehВҰ29950 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңWe'll go with our sonsВҰ29954 and daughtersВҰ29955, and with our flocksВҰ29956 and herdsВҰ29957, because the festivalВҰ29960 of YahwehВҰ29962 is for \add all of\add* us.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add You'd need YahwehВҰ29969 with you if I ever\add* let you andВҰ29974 yourВҰ29981 children goВҰ29972 \add together\add*,вҖқ Far'oh \add вүҲrespondedВҰ29965\add*. вҖңYou're clearly \add plotting an evilВҰ29979 trick\add*!
\v 11 \add Well that won't happen!\add* The menВҰ29988 may goВҰ29985 and worshipВҰ29989 YahwehВҰ29992 since that's what you've been wanting.вҖқ Then he droveВҰ29997 them \add out of the room\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ30005 told MoshehВҰ30008, вҖңExtend yourВҰ30010 handВҰ30010 over EgyptВҰ30014 and let \add the locustsВҰ30015\add* rise up over the land, and let \add them\add* devour all the plantsвҖ”everything which the hail had spared.вҖқ
\v 13 \add SoВҰ30035\add* MoshehВҰ30036 stretchedВҰ30035 his staffВҰ30039 out over EgyptВҰ30043, and YahwehВҰ30044 sent an east wind over the land all that dayВҰ30051 and all nightВҰ30055. ThenВҰ30035 morningВҰ30056 came, and the east wind had brought the locustsВҰ30063.
\v 14 The locusts covered across all the land of EgyptВҰ30071 and came to rest everywhere within the \add country's\add* borders. They were extremely numerousвҖ”never beforeВҰ30078 were there so many locusts, and it'll never be \add repeated againВҰ30085\add*.\x + \xo 10:14-15: \xt Rev 9:2-3.\x*
\v 15 \add The cloud of locusts blocked the sun\add* and \add prevented people from being able to see very far\add*. They devoured all the plants on the land and all of the fruitВҰ30110 on the trees thatВҰ30112 the hail had left, and \add no piece\add* of greeneryВҰ30120 remained on any tree or plant in the entireВҰ30095 Egyptian countrysideВҰ30123.
\p
\v 16 Far'ohВҰ30130 quickly summoned MoshehВҰ30132 and AharonВҰ30133 and saidВҰ30134, вҖңI'veВҰ30135 sinnedВҰ30135 against yourВҰ30137 godВҰ30137 YahwehВҰ30136 and against youВҰ30138.
\v 17 SoВҰ30140 now just this once, pleaseВҰ30142 \add overlook\add* my sinВҰ30143 and pray to yourВҰ30148 godВҰ30148 YahwehВҰ30147 and just let him take this \add deathlyВҰ30154 plague\add* away from me.вҖқ
\v 18 \add SoВҰ30157 Mosheh\add* left Far'ohВҰ30159 and wentВҰ30157 out and prayedВҰ30160 to YahwehВҰ30163,
\v 19 and YahwehВҰ30166 \add caused\add* a very strongВҰ30170 seaВҰ30177 wind. \add The wind\add* carried away the locustsВҰ30175 and droveВҰ30176 them into the Red SeaвҖ”not a single locustВҰ30181 remainedВҰ30180 anywhere in Egyptian territoryВҰ30184.
\v 20 \add ButВҰ30187\add* YahwehВҰ30188 caused Far'ohВҰ30192 \add to remain stubborn\add* andВҰ30187 he wouldn't release the IsraelisВҰ30198.
\s1 Plague 9: Darkness
\rem /s1 The Plague of Darkness; The Ninth Plague: Darkness; A Plague of Darkness
\p
\v 21 Then YahwehВҰ30202 told MoshehВҰ30205, вҖңRaise your hand up toward the sky and let it become dark over all EgyptВҰ30216вҖ”darkness \add that can be felt\add*.вҖқ
\v 22 \add SoВҰ30220\add* MoshehВҰ30221 stretchedВҰ30220 his handВҰ30224 out \add towards\add* the sky, andВҰ30220 a \add thick\add* darknessВҰ30229 was in all EgyptВҰ30235 for threeВҰ30236 daysВҰ30237.\x + \xo 10:22: \xt Psa 105:28; Rev 16:10.\x*
\v 23 NoВҰ30256 one could see \add anyoneВҰ30249 else\add*, and for threeВҰ30251 daysВҰ30252 no one was able to go anywhere, yet there was lightВҰ30258 in \add the region whereВҰ30259\add* the IsraelisВҰ30255 livedВҰ30259.
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ30261 Far'ohВҰ30262 summoned MoshehВҰ30265 and told him, вҖңGo serveВҰ30268 YahwehВҰ30271. Your children can go with you all, \add but\add* your flocksВҰ30273 and your herdsВҰ30274 must remain behind.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңOn top of that,вҖқ MoshehВҰ30283 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ30282\add*, вҖңyou must also giveВҰ30287 us the sacrifices andВҰ30282 offeringsВҰ30290 to be burntВҰ30290 when we will \add sacrifice to\add* YahwehВҰ30292 ourВҰ30288 godВҰ30293.
\v 26 And even our livestockВҰ30297 needs to goВҰ30298 with us. Not a hoof will be left behind because we'll \add choose\add* from them to serve Yahweh our godВҰ30310. \add You see\add*, we won'tВҰ30300 knowВҰ30314 what we must \add sacrifice to\add* Yahweh untilВҰ30321 we arriveВҰ30323 thereВҰ30324.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add ButВҰ30328\add* YahwehВҰ30327 caused Far'ohВҰ30331 to \add strengthen his resolve\add* andВҰ30326 he wouldn't agree to let them goВҰ30334.
\v 28 вҖңGet \add out of here\add*!вҖқ Far'ohВҰ30339 \add shouted\add*. вҖңAnd watch yourselfВҰ30343! You'll never see me again, because if I ever see you again, I'll \add have you executed\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖң\add Yes,\add*вҖқ MoshehВҰ30356 respondedВҰ30355. вҖңIt's just as you say: I'll never seeВҰ30363 you againВҰ30362!вҖқ
\c 11
\s1 Plague 10: Death of oldest sons
\rem /s1 Moses Announces the Death of the First-Born; The Plague on the Firstborn; Warning of the Final Plague; Death for Egypt's Firstborn
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ30368 told MoshehВҰ30371, вҖңI'll send one more plagueВҰ30373 to Far'ohВҰ30378 and EgyptВҰ30381. After that he'll let you all go from here. \add What's more,\add* when he does he'll actually chase you all right out of here.
\v 2 \add Go and\add* quietly tell the peopleВҰ30399 that both men and womenВҰ30405 should askВҰ30400 their \add Egyptian\add* neighboursВҰ30404 for items of goldВҰ30412 and silverВҰ30410.вҖқ
\v 3 ThenВҰ30414 YahwehВҰ30415 gave the \add @Israelis\add* favourВҰ30418 in the eyes of the Egyptians. What's more, MoshehВҰ30425 was very prestigious in the eyes of Far'oh's servantsВҰ30431 andВҰ30414 in the eyes of the Egyptian people.
\p
\v 4 Then MoshehВҰ30439 told \add Far'oh\add*, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ30442 saysВҰ30441: Sometime around the middle of the nightВҰ30444 I'll goВҰ30446 out \add around\add* EgyptВҰ30448,
\v 5 andВҰ30450 every oldest son in EgyptВҰ30455 will dieВҰ30450, from the oldest son of Far'ohВҰ30457 who sitsВҰ30458 on his throneВҰ30461, to the oldest son of the slaveВҰ30464 girlВҰ30464 who \add lives\add* behindВҰ30466 the mill, as well as every oldest male offspring of \add вүҲyour livestock\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ30472 there'llВҰ30472 be loud wailing right across EgyptВҰ30478 whichВҰ30479 will be nothing anything that's ever happened before, andВҰ30472 nothing like it will \add ever\add* happen again.
\v 7 ButВҰ30487 \add вүҲamongst the IsraelisВҰ30490\add*, \add вүҲthe dogs won'tВҰ30491 growl at any person or animals\add* so that you'll knowВҰ30501 that YahwehВҰ30504 distinguishesВҰ30503 between EgyptВҰ30506 andВҰ30487 YisraelВҰ30490.
\v 8 Then all yourВҰ30528 servantsВҰ30513 will comeВҰ30510 down to me, and they'll bow to me, \add вүҲpleading\add*, вҖҳGo, you and all the peopleВҰ30525 who \add вүҲfollow you\add*.вҖҷ And afterВҰ30529 thatВҰ30526 I'll \add вүҲleave Egypt\add*.вҖқ Then \add @Mosheh\add* \add вүҲleft\add* Far'ohВҰ30536 \add вүҲin a fiery rage\add*.
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ30543 told MoshehВҰ30546, вҖңFar'ohВҰ30551 \add refused to\add* listenВҰ30549 to youВҰ30550, so that I'm able to multiply my miracles in EgyptВҰ30556.вҖқ
\v 10 MoshehВҰ30558 andВҰ30558 AharonВҰ30559 had done all those miracles in frontВҰ30567 of Far'oh \add but\add* YahwehВҰ30570 \add had made Far'oh stubborn so\add* he hadn't let the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ30582 leave his country\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Meal preparations to avoid death
\rem /s1 The Passover; The First Passover Instituted; The First Passover; The institution of the Passover
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ30587 told MoshehВҰ30590 and AharonВҰ30593 in EgyptВҰ30595,\x + \xo 12:1-13: \xt Lev 23:5; Num 9:1-5; 28:16; Deu 16:1-2.\x*
\v 2 вҖңThis month is to become the beginningВҰ30601 of the months for you allвҖ”\add from now on\add* itВҰ30604 will be the firstВҰ30603 month of the \add new\add* yearВҰ30607.
\v 3 AssembleВҰ30615 the people andВҰ30620 tell them that on the tenth of this month, every manВҰ30622 who's the head of the household must select a lamb or young goat \add for his familyВҰ30624\add*.
\v 4 \add ButВҰ30630\add* if the household'sВҰ30633 too smallВҰ30632 \add to cook\add* a whole animal, thenВҰ30630 \add neighboursВҰ30638 can combine andВҰ30630 shareвҖ”budgeting\add* on how much each person eats.
\v 5 You all can choose either a sheepВҰ30663 or a goat, but itВҰ30659 must be a perfect, one-year-old maleВҰ30655вҖ”without any defects.
\v 6 YouВҰ30684 all must \add вүҲtake special care of those animals\add* untilВҰ30672 the fourteenth dayВҰ30675 of this monthВҰ30676, thenВҰ30669 \add вүҲevery IsraeliВҰ30682 household\add* will slaughterВҰ30678 \add @their animal early\add* that evening.
\v 7 ThenВҰ30705 they must takeВҰ30688 some of the bloodВҰ30691 and put it on both doorpostsВҰ30696 and on the lintelВҰ30699 of the housesВҰ30701 thatВҰ30702 they'll be in when they eatВҰ30704 it.
\v 8 TheyВҰ30709 must roastВҰ30714 them on the fireВҰ30716 and eat the meat that nightВҰ30712, along with flat breadВҰ30717 and bitterВҰ30720 herbsВҰ30720.
\v 9 Don'tВҰ30731 eatВҰ30725 any of the meat raw and don'tВҰ30723 boil it in waterВҰ30730вҖ”it must be roastedВҰ30734 over the fireВҰ30736 with its head, legs, and internal organs.
\v 10 Nothing must be left by morningвҖ”anything that's \add вүҲnot eaten\add* must be burnt in the fireВҰ30757.
\v 11 And this is how you all must eat it: with your belts fastened on your waists, your sandalsВҰ30765 on your feetВҰ30766, andВҰ30760 your staffsВҰ30767 in your hands. You all must eat it in a hurry. It is the Passover to YahwehВҰ30774.
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ30776 during that nightВҰ30780, I will move throughout Egypt and I will \add вүҲkill\add* all the \add вүҲoldest males\add*вҖ”\add вүҲboth people and animals\add*. I will \add вүҲexecute\add* judgementВҰ30797 on all the godsВҰ30794 of Egypt. I am YahwehВҰ30799.
\v 13 That blood \add on the doorposts and lintel\add* will be your sign on the housesВҰ30806 which you are all in. I will see the blood and will pass over above you all, and the plagueВҰ30820 won'tВҰ30816 \add affect\add* you all with destructionВҰ30821 as I strikeВҰ30822 against EgyptВҰ30824.
\v 14 ThenВҰ30826 this dayВҰ30827 will become a memorialВҰ30830 for you all, andВҰ30826 you'll celebrate it as a festivalВҰ30833 to YahwehВҰ30834 for \add future\add* generationsВҰ30835вҖ”a statuteВҰ30836 that you'll all celebrate forever.\x + \xo 12:14-20: \xt Exo 23:15; 34:18; Lev 23:6-8; Num 28:17-25; Deu 16:3-8.\x*
\s1 The вҖҳFlat Bread CelebrationвҖҷ
\rem /s1 The Festival of Unleavened Bread
\p
\v 15 For seven days you all must only eat flat bread \add made without yeast\add*. Yes, on the first day you all must removeВҰ30847 any yeast from your housesВҰ30849, because anyoneВҰ30854 who eats bread with yeast during those seven days, that person must be permanently driven out of YisraelВҰ30859.
\v 16 On the firstВҰ30868 day, you all must gather for a sacredВҰ30871 assemblyВҰ30869, andВҰ30867 \add вүҲsimilarly\add* on the seventhВҰ30873 day. No work can be done on those \add days\add* \add вүҲother than meal preparation\add*.
\v 17 You all must \add regularlyВҰ30917\add* observe the \it Flat Bread \add Celebration\add*\it*, because on this very day I will have broughtВҰ30905 your divisionsВҰ30908 out from EgyptВҰ30910. You all must observe this day throughoutВҰ30916 \add future\add* generationsВҰ30916вҖ”a statuteВҰ30917 that you'll all celebrate forever.
\v 18 Starting on 14th of the firstВҰ30920 month in the evening, you all must eat \add only\add* flat breadВҰ30927 untilВҰ30928 the 21st day of the month in the evening.
\v 19 ForВҰ30951 seven daysВҰ30936 you all must have no yeast in yourВҰ30940 homes, because anyoneВҰ30945 who eatsВҰ30945 bread with yeast in itВҰ30939, that person \add must be driven out\add* from the IsraeliВҰ30950 people whether they're a foreigner or a nativeВҰ30953.
\rem /s1 The First Passover
\v 20 You all mustn't eat \add anything made with\add* yeast. Wherever you live, you all must only eat flat breadВҰ30964.
\s1 The first ever вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration
\p
\v 21 Then MoshehВҰ30968 summoned the IsraeliВҰ30971 eldersВҰ30971 and told them, вҖңGo ahead and selectВҰ30976 a lamb or young goat for each familyВҰ30979 and slaughterВҰ30980 it.
\v 22 ThenВҰ30983 you all must take a bunchВҰ30984 of \add leafy\add* hyssopВҰ30985 \add stalks\add*, and dip it in the basin \add with the blood from the sacrifice\add* and paint the blood onto the lintelВҰ30994 and both doorpostsВҰ30998. \add After thatВҰ30988\add*, \add вүҲabsolutely no one\add* should go out the door of your housesВҰ31010 untilВҰ31011 morningВҰ31013.
\v 23 ThenВҰ31015 YahwehВҰ31016 will pass throughВҰ31015 \add out EgyptВҰ31020\add* to strike the EgyptiansВҰ31032 and \add when\add* he sees the bloodВҰ31024 on the lintelВҰ31027 and on the two doorpostsВҰ31030, \add *he'll\add* вҖҳpass overвҖҷ that doorway and won'tВҰ31036 permitВҰ31037 вҖҳthe destroyerВҰ31038вҖҷ to enter into your housesВҰ31042 to strike.\x + \xo 12:23: \xt Heb 11:28.\x*
\v 24 AllВҰ31046 of you and yourВҰ31053 descendants must maintain this as a law and celebrate it forever,
\v 25 \add so\add* when you all enter into the land thatВҰ31065 YahwehВҰ31067 will giveВҰ31066 to you just as he \add вүҲpromised\add*, thenВҰ31058 you must \add вүҲobserveВҰ31071\add* this ceremonyВҰ31074.
\v 26 ThenВҰ31077 when itВҰ31077 occurs, your childrenВҰ31082 will ask, вҖҳWhat does this ceremonyВҰ31084 \add mean\add* to you?вҖҷ
\v 27 you all must tell \add <them\add*, вҖҳIt's the sacrificeВҰ31089 of вҖҳpass-overВҰ31091вҖҷ to YahwehВҰ31093, who passedВҰ31095 over the housesВҰ31098 of the IsraelisВҰ31101 in EgyptВҰ31102 \add when he\add* struckВҰ31103 the Egyptians and rescued our families.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p And the people bowedВҰ31111 their heads and prostrated themselves,
\v 28 and the IsraelisВҰ31118 wentВҰ31115 and did \add just\add* as YahwehВҰ31121 had commandedВҰ31120 \add through\add* MoshehВҰ31124 and AharonВҰ31125.
\s1 The death of all the oldest male offspring
\rem /s1 The Tenth Plague: Death of the Firstborn; The Death of the First-Born
\p
\v 29 Then, in the middleВҰ31132 of the nightВҰ31133, YahwehВҰ31134 struckВҰ31135 all the oldest males in EgyptВҰ31140, from the oldest son of Far'ohВҰ31142 who satВҰ31143 on his throneВҰ31146, to the firstborn of the \add вүҲprisonerВҰ31149 in the dungeon\add* and all \add oldest male offspring\add* of the animals.\x + \xo 12:29: \xt Exo 4:22-23.\x*
\v 30 During the nightВҰ31159, all the Egyptians got up, including Far'ohВҰ31158 andВҰ31157 all his servants. There was \add вүҲtremendous wailing throughout\add* EgyptВҰ31166 because \add it was a very rare houseВҰ31174\add* whereВҰ31175 there wasn't someone deadВҰ31179.
\rem /s1 The Exodus; Israel's Exodus from Egypt
\v 31 \add @Far'oh\add* calledВҰ31181 for MoshehВҰ31182 and AharonВҰ31183 in the nightВҰ31184 and told \add <them\add*, вҖңPack up and get out from amongВҰ31188 my peopleвҖ”you \add two\add* and all the other IsraelisВҰ31196. Go and serveВҰ31198 YahwehВҰ31201 as you've said.
\v 32 Also takeВҰ31210 your flocksВҰ31206 and your herdsВҰ31209 as you've saidВҰ31212, and goВҰ31213. And blessВҰ31214 me as well.
\rem /s1 The Exodus: From Rameses to Succoth
\p
\v 33 The Egyptians urgedВҰ31219 the \add @Israelis\add*, hurryingВҰ31224 to let them go from the land because theyВҰ31230 saidВҰ31230, вҖңWe're all dying.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \add SoВҰ31234\add* the peopleВҰ31235 carried their \add bread\add* doughВҰ31238 beforeВҰ31239 itВҰ31240 \add вүҲcould rise\add*. TheirВҰ31236 bread-making bowlsВҰ31241 were wrapped in their clothes on their shouldersВҰ31246.
\p
\v 35 The IsraelisВҰ31250 did everything that MoshehВҰ31253 had instructed them, \add including\add* asking for items of goldВҰ31260 and silverВҰ31258, and clothingВҰ31261 from the Egyptians.\x + \xo 12:35-36: \xt Exo 3:21-22.\x*
\v 36 YahwehВҰ31263 gaveВҰ31264 the peopleВҰ31268 favourВҰ31267 in the eyesВҰ31269 of the Egyptians, \add so by\add* their requests, they were able to strip the Egyptians of their wealth.
\rem /s1 The Israelites Leave Egypt; The exodus from Egypt
\p
\v 37 Then the IsraelisВҰ31281 walked from RamesesВҰ31282 toward SuccothВҰ31283вҖ”aboutВҰ31284 600,000 strong menВҰ31289 on footВҰ31288, not counting \add women and\add* childrenВҰ31291.
\v 38 A large assortment of other people also wentВҰ31297 with them, along with large numbers of sheep and goats, and cattle.
\p
\v 39 They bakedВҰ31305 the doughВҰ31308 that they broughtВҰ31310 from Egypt into flat breadВҰ31312 since itВҰ31316 \add вүҲhadn't had time to rise\add*,\f + \fr 12:39 \ft Most modern readers probably visualise yeast bought from a supermarket when вҖҳleavenвҖҷ (or even вҖҳyeastвҖҷ) is mentioned in a Bible translation. However, it's much more likely that each day, a portion of the bread dough was set aside for the natural yeasts (think вҖҳsour doughвҖҷ bread) to accumulate, and then mixed into the new batch of dough the next day and left for the natural yeasts to work and rise the dough. The text here implies that it's possible that the Hebrew word translated вҖҳunleavenedвҖҷ really meant вҖҳunrisenвҖҷ on that first вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ night.\f* because they were drivenВҰ31319 out of Egypt \add вүҲin a hurry\add* and hadn't \add вүҲhad time to prepare food to take\add*.
\p
\v 40 The descendants of Yisra'el \add (Yacob)\add* had lived in EgyptВҰ31337 for 430 years\x + \xo 12:40: \xt Gen 15:13; Gal 3:17.\x*
\v 41 to the day, because that very day was when all the \add various\add* divisions of Yahweh'sВҰ31359 \add people\add* left EgyptВҰ31361.
\v 42 It was a \add time\add* when they stayed awake all night as YahwehВҰ31366 took them out of EgyptВҰ31369вҖ”a night to be observed in that same way by every future generationВҰ31380.
\s1 Instructions for observing the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ
\rem /s1 Instructions for the Passover; Passover Restrictions; Directions for the Passover; Regulations about Passover
\p
\v 43 Then YahwehВҰ31384 told MoshehВҰ31387 and AharonВҰ31388, вҖңThis is the statuteВҰ31390 of the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ: No foreignersВҰ31396 may \add share in\add* the meal \add that night\add*,
\v 44 unless it's a slaveВҰ31404 that you bought andВҰ31409 who's been circumcisedВҰ31409вҖ”
\v 45 no foreigner or hiredВҰ31416 helper can \add join in\add* the meal.
\v 46 \add Each animal\add* must be eatenВҰ31425 in only one houseвҖ”don't take any of the meat outsideВҰ31435. And don't breakВҰ31438 any of the animals bonesВҰ31436.\x + \xo 12:46: \xt Num 9:12; Yhn 19:36.\x*
\v 47 EveryВҰ31445 IsraeliВҰ31444 must observe it,
\v 48 and if someone is living among you and wants to join in Yahweh's вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ, then everyВҰ31459 maleВҰ31461 in their family must be circumcisedВҰ31457. Only then will they be allowed to observe it, and then they should be considered like a nativeВҰ31466 of the land. No uncircumcisedВҰ31470 person may eatВҰ31473 it.
\v 49 This one law will apply to both the nativesВҰ31479, andВҰ31480 those who live among youВҰ31482 all.вҖқ
\v 50 AllВҰ31492 the IsraelisВҰ31488 followed those instructions that YahwehВҰ31491 had given through MoshehВҰ31494 andВҰ31495 AharonВҰ31497,
\v 51 and \add so\add* on that very dayВҰ31504, YahwehВҰ31507 took all the IsraelisВҰ31511 out of EgyptВҰ31513 \add grouped\add* by theirВҰ31516 \add family\add* divisions.
\c 13
\s1 God owns the first child
\rem /s1 Dedication of the Firstborn; Dedication of the First-Born; Consecration of the Firstborn
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ31520 told MoshehВҰ31523,
\v 2 вҖңAllВҰ31537 firstborn \add offspring\add* are to be consecrated to meвҖ”the first product of every womb, whether human or animal, belongs to me.вҖқ\x + \xo 13:2: \xt Num 3:13; Luk 2:23.\x*
\s1 The вҖҳFlat Bread CelebrationвҖҷ
\rem /s1 The Festival of Unleavened Bread
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ31543 MoshehВҰ31544 told the peopleВҰ31547, вҖң\add Always\add* rememberВҰ31548 this dayВҰ31551, that you wentВҰ31554 out of EgyptВҰ31555, \add rescued\add* from slaveryВҰ31557, because YahwehВҰ31562 \add вүҲused his power\add* to bring you out from there. And \add вүҲnothing with yeast in it\add* can be eatenВҰ31566 \add when you celebrate this\add*.
\v 4 Today youВҰ31570 are leaving in the monthВҰ31572 of Aviv,
\v 5 and \add when\add* YahwehВҰ31579 bringsВҰ31578 you to the land of the CanaanitesВҰ31583, HittitesВҰ31584, AmoritesВҰ31585, HivitesВҰ31586, and the YebusitesВҰ31587 (whichВҰ31588 he sworeВҰ31589 to your fathersВҰ31590 to giveВҰ31591 to youвҖ”a land flowingВҰ31594 with milk and honeyВҰ31596) you must observeВҰ31597 this ceremonyВҰ31600 in this \add same\add* monthВҰ31602.
\v 6 You must eatВҰ31607 \add only\add* flat breadВҰ31608 for seven daysВҰ31606, andВҰ31609 then on the seventh dayВҰ31609, it will be a festivalВҰ31611 to \add honour\add* YahwehВҰ31612.
\v 7 \add AgainВҰ31616,\add* you must only eat flat bread for sevenВҰ31617 daysВҰ31618вҖ”\add not only that\add* you mustn't \add even have\add* any risen bread, nor must you have any yeast within any of yourВҰ31631 borders.
\v 8 On that \add festival\add* dayВҰ31635, you must tell yourВҰ31634 \add children\add*, вҖҳThis is because of what YahwehВҰ31641 did for \add us\add* when \add we leftВҰ31643\add* EgyptВҰ31644.вҖҷ
\v 9 It'll be \add вүҲlike a reminderВҰ31652 written\add* on your hand andВҰ31646 a \add вүҲprompt in front\add* ofВҰ31653 your eyesВҰ31654, so that \add вүҲyou'll remember to pass on\add* Yahweh's instructions because \add *he\add* \add вүҲused his power\add* to bring you out of EgyptВҰ31665.
\v 10 \add SoВҰ31668\add* you must \add вүҲfollow those instructions\add* at the appointedВҰ31672 timeВҰ31672 \add вүҲyear after year\add*.
\s1 Offering up the oldest children
\rem /s1 The Consecration of the Firstborn; The First-Born
\p
\v 11 LaterВҰ31678, when YahwehВҰ31681 bringsВҰ31680 you into the land of the CanaanitesВҰ31685 as he promised to you and your ancestorsВҰ31689, and he givesВҰ31690 it to you,
\v 12 thenВҰ31693 hand over to Yahweh all oldest children, andВҰ31700 all the oldest animal offspring thatВҰ31706 are yoursВҰ31708. The malesВҰ31709 are for Yahweh.\x + \xo 13:12: \xt Exo 34:19-20; Luk 2:23.\x*
\v 13 In the case of the oldest donkey foal, you must buy it back \add by killing a lamb\add* instead of it. If you don'tВҰ31720 buy it back, you must kill the donkey by breakingВҰ31722 its neck. You \em must\em* buy back every one of your oldest sons,
\v 14 andВҰ31729 \add вүҲin the futureВҰ31734\add* when your son asksВҰ31732 you, вҖҳWhat's that about?вҖҷ thenВҰ31729 you must tell him, вҖҳ\add вүҲWe were enslaved in EgyptВҰ31745, but YahwehВҰ31744 used his incredible power\add* to bring us out.
\v 15 And so it was that when Far'ohВҰ31753 was too stubbornВҰ31752 to let us go, thenВҰ31749 Yahweh struck all of the oldest sons and oldest male animals in EgyptВҰ31761. That's why \add we\add* offer all the oldest offspring to Yahweh, and why \add we need to buy back\add* all our oldest sons.вҖҷ
\v 16 \add SoВҰ31793\add* you must place a reminder on your hand andВҰ31785 hanging on your forehead that YahwehВҰ31797 used his incredible power to bring us out of EgyptВҰ31798.вҖқ
\s1 Led by cloud and fire
\rem /s1 Crossing the Sea; The Pillars of Cloud and Fire; The Pillar of Cloud and the Pillar of Fire; Israel's Wilderness Detour
\p
\v 17 When Far'ohВҰ31803 released the people, GodВҰ31810 didn'tВҰ31807 lead them through the land of the PhilistinesВҰ31813, although \add @that way\add* was shorter, because \add *he\add* said, вҖң\add вүҲIt's best if the people don'tВҰ31807 have to faceВҰ31825 war immediately, or they might change their minds\add* and \add then want to\add* returnВҰ31827 to EgyptВҰ31828.вҖқ
\v 18 \add SoВҰ31830\add* GodВҰ31831 caused the people to take the pathВҰ31836 going towards the wildernessВҰ31837 andВҰ31830 the Red Sea.\f + \fr 13:18 \ft Probably towards the \em Gulf of Suez\em*: see https://armstronginstitute.org/339-where-did-the-red-sea-crossing-take-place.\f* The IsraeliВҰ31845 left EgyptВҰ31847 \add вүҲin formation as if ready for battleВҰ31841\add*.
\p
\v 19 MoshehВҰ31850 \add ensured that\add* the bones of Yosef were taken with \add them\add*, because \add many years back\add* \add @Yosef\add* had made the IsraelisВҰ31862 vow, saying, вҖңGodВҰ31866 will certainly take notice of you all, andВҰ31868 you must take my bones up with you from here.вҖқ\x + \xo 13:19: \xt Gen 50:25; Josh 24:32.\x*
\p
\v 20 The people travelled on from SuccothВҰ31876 andВҰ31877 campedВҰ31877 at EthamВҰ31878 on the edge of the wildernessВҰ31880.
\v 21 During the day, YahwehВҰ31882 went ahead of them in a pillar of cloudВҰ31887 to lead them on the way, and at nighttime, he went in a pillar of fire to be lightВҰ31893 to them, \add so they could travel both\add* in the daytime and at night.
\v 22 The daytime pillar of cloudВҰ31903 andВҰ31905 the nighttimeВҰ31907 pillar of fireВҰ31906 didn't ever leave their place in frontВҰ31908 of the peopleВҰ31909.
\c 14
\s1 Crossing the Red Sea
\rem /s1 Crossing the Red Sea
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ31913 told MoshehВҰ31916,
\v 2 вҖңTell the IsraelisВҰ31923 that they should turn and camp in front of Pi Hahiroth, between MigdolВҰ31930 and the sea, in front of Baal-ZephonВҰ31935. You all are to camp by the sea oppositeВҰ31936 it.
\v 3 ThenВҰ31942 Far'ohВҰ31943 will say, вҖҳTheyВҰ31945 are confusedВҰ31946 \add andВҰ31942 lost\add*вҖ”the wildernessВҰ31951 has boxed them in.вҖҷ
\v 4 I'll strengthen Far'oh's \add вүҲresolve\add* and he'll chase afterВҰ31960 them. ThenВҰ31953 because of Far'oh and all his army, I'll be \add honoured\add* and the Egyptians will knowВҰ31966 that I am YahwehВҰ31971.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ31953 the Israelis camped where theyВҰ31972 were instructed\add*.
\rem /s1 The Egyptians Pursue Israel
\p
\v 5 When the kingВҰ31977 of EgyptВҰ31978 was told that the Israelis had fled, \add *he\add* and his servants \add started thinking about their own\add* people and they asked, вҖңWhat have we done by letting the Israeli slaves go free?вҖқ
\v 6 ThenВҰ32002 heВҰ32009 hitched up his chariotВҰ32005 andВҰ32006 tookВҰ32009 his \add army\add* with him.
\v 7 He tookВҰ32012 600 of the best chariots as well as all the other Egyptian chariots andВҰ32012 officersВҰ32021 \add to supervise\add* them.
\v 8 YahwehВҰ32027 strengthened the EgyptianВҰ32039 king's resolve andВҰ32026 so Far'ohВҰ32031 pursuedВҰ32034 after the IsraelisВҰ32037 after they had confidently marched out \add of EgyptВҰ32033\add*.
\v 9 The Egyptians pursued them and all of Far'oh's horsesВҰ32055 and chariotsВҰ32056, along with his mounted soldiers and his foot army, overtookВҰ32047 them camping above the seaВҰ32052 above Pi Hahiroth, across from Baal-ZephonВҰ32066.
\p
\v 10 As \add the Egyptians\add* approached, the IsraelisВҰ32073 looked back, and \add to theirВҰ32076 horror\add*, saw the army coming afterВҰ32081 them. They were extremely afraidВҰ32082 and criedВҰ32084 out to YahwehВҰ32090.
\v 11 They \add complained\add* to MoshehВҰ32095, вҖңIs it becauseВҰ32096 thereВҰ32097 weren't any gravesВҰ32099 in Egypt that you brought us here to dieВҰ32102 in the wildernessВҰ32103? What have you done to us? Why did you bringВҰ32109 us out from Egypt?
\v 12 Isn't this \add exactly what we told\add* youВҰ32118 in EgyptВҰ32119 when we said, вҖҳ\add вүҲJust leave us alone\add* and let us serveВҰ32123 the EgyptiansвҖҷ? Because servingВҰ32130 the Egyptians \add sounds a lot\add* better to us than dying \add out here\add* in the wildernessВҰ32135.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ32137 MoshehВҰ32138 told the peopleВҰ32141, вҖңYou mustn't be afraidВҰ32144. Stand still andВҰ32137 see how YahwehВҰ32150 saves you allвҖ”he's going to do it today, because any Egyptians thatВҰ32151 you see today, you'll never, ever see them againВҰ32166.
\v 14 YahwehВҰ32171 himself will fightВҰ32172 for you allвҖ”all you need to do is to remain calm.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Escape through the Red Sea
\v 15 Then YahwehВҰ32179 \add scolded\add* MoshehВҰ32182, вҖңWhy are youВҰ32185 \add still here\add* cryingВҰ32185 out to me? Talk to the IsraelisВҰ32192 and get them moving forwardВҰ32193.
\v 16 As for you, raiseВҰ32196 your staffВҰ32199 and stretchВҰ32200 your arm out over the sea and divideВҰ32207 it. ThenВҰ32195 the IsraelisВҰ32211 will go on onto dry groundВҰ32214 through the middleВҰ32212 of the sea.
\v 17 \add Yes, watch me!\add* I'll strengthen the resolve of the Egyptians and they'll enter \add between the sea\add* afterВҰ32224 them. ThenВҰ32216 I'll be honoured because of \add what will happen to\add* Far'ohВҰ32226 and all his army, and his chariotsВҰ32230 and his horsemenВҰ32231.
\v 18 \add Because of that,\add* the Egyptians will knowВҰ32233 that I'm YahwehВҰ32238.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ32244 God's messengerВҰ32245 who travelled ahead of the IsraelisВҰ32250, moved and wentВҰ32251 behind them. \add Also\add* the pillarВҰ32254 of cloudВҰ32255 moved from in frontВҰ32248 of them and stoodВҰ32257 behind them
\v 20 and \add so\add* it was thenВҰ32260 between the \add coming\add* Egyptians and the IsraelisВҰ32267. ThenВҰ32260 the cloudВҰ32269 became darknessВҰ32270 \add on the Egyptian side\add*, \add yet it lit up the other side\add*, and no one could approach it all night.
\v 21 ThenВҰ32286 MoshehВҰ32287 stretchedВҰ32286 his arm out over the sea and YahwehВҰ32295 sent a strongВҰ32302 east wind. It blew all nightВҰ32305 and dividedВҰ32311 the sea \add on each side\add* and dried the \add strip of\add* land in the middle.
\v 22 \add SoВҰ32314\add* thenВҰ32314 the IsraelisВҰ32317 entered through the middleВҰ32318 of the seaВҰ32319 on dry groundВҰ32320 with a wall of waterВҰ32321 on each side of them.\x + \xo 14:22: \xt 1Cor 10:1-2; Heb 11:29.\x*
\v 23 \add However,\add* the Egyptians pursuedВҰ32327 afterВҰ32330 them. Every one of Far'oh's horses and chariotsВҰ32334 and his horsemen \add also\add* entered into the middleВҰ32338 of the seaВҰ32339.
\v 24 \add By now morningВҰ32343 was coming\add* and YahwehВҰ32345 lookedВҰ32344 down through the pillarВҰ32350 of fireВҰ32351 and cloudВҰ32352, and he caused confusion for the Egyptian army.
\v 25 He causedВҰ32358 the wheelsВҰ32360 of theirВҰ32361 chariotsВҰ32361 to turn unevenly \add so they became difficultВҰ32363\add* to drive, and the Egyptians \add complained\add*, вҖңLet's retreat from \add following\add* the IsraelisВҰ32367, because YahwehВҰ32370 is fightingВҰ32371 against EgyptВҰ32365 and for them.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Pursuers Drowned
\p
\v 26 \add On the other side,\add* YahwehВҰ32377 told MoshehВҰ32380, вҖңStretch yourВҰ32384 arm out over the seaВҰ32387 and the watersВҰ32389 will \add flow back\add* onto the Egyptians and onto \add @Far'oh's\add* chariotsВҰ32395 and his horsemenВҰ32398.вҖқ
\v 27 \add SoВҰ32400\add* MoshehВҰ32401 stretchedВҰ32400 his arm out over the sea, and as the day broke, the sea began to returnВҰ32408 to its normalВҰ32412 place. The Egyptians \add turned and\add* fled beforeВҰ32415 its impact \add but\add* YahwehВҰ32417 shook the Egyptians \add off their horses and chariots\add* in the middleВҰ32421 of the sea.
\v 28 \add SoВҰ32424\add* the sea returnedВҰ32424 and coveredВҰ32426 the chariotsВҰ32429 and the horsemenВҰ32432вҖ”even Far'oh's entire army that had entered into the sea afterВҰ32437 \add @the Israelis\add*. Not even one of \add @the pursuers\add* remainedВҰ32441.
\v 29 \add ButВҰ32447\add* the IsraelisВҰ32448 had walkedВҰ32449 through the middleВҰ32451 of the seaВҰ32452 on dry land with a wall of waterВҰ32453 on each side of them.
\p
\v 30 \add So\add* YahwehВҰ32460 savedВҰ32459 YisraelВҰ32465 from Egypt'sВҰ32467 power that dayВҰ32461, and the Israelis sawВҰ32468 the Egyptians' bodies \add washed up\add* on the shoreВҰ32476.
\v 31 \add All of\add* YisraelВҰ32480 sawВҰ32479 the \add вүҲincredible powerВҰ32483\add* thatВҰ32485 Yahweh had used against the Egyptians, and the peopleВҰ32490 revered Yahweh, and put their trust in him and his servantВҰ32497 MoshehВҰ32496.
\c 15
\s1 Mosheh's song
\rem /s1 The Song of Moses; A Song of Deliverance; The Song of Moses and Miriam
\p
\v 1 Then MoshehВҰ32503 and the IsraelisВҰ32505 sang this song to Yahweh:\x + \xo 15:1: \xt Rev 15:3.\x*
\q1 вҖңI will sing to Yahweh because he's been so successfulвҖ”
\q1 he's thrownВҰ32521 both the horsesВҰ32519 and their ridersВҰ32520 into the seaВҰ32522.
\q1
\v 2 I will sing about YahwehВҰ32526, my source of strength,\x + \xo 15:2: \xt Psa 118:14; Isa 12:2.\x*
\q2 and the one who saves me.
\q1 I will praiseВҰ32533 him because he's my godвҖ”
\q1 вүҲhe's my father'sВҰ32535 godВҰ32532 and I will honour him.
\q1
\v 3 Yahweh is a warrior.
\q1 Yahweh is his nameВҰ32542.
\b
\q1
\v 4 He threw Far'oh's chariotsВҰ32544 and his army into the sea.
\q1 вүҲHis hand-picked officersВҰ32550 have been sunk in the sea.
\b
\q1
\v 5 The deep waters coverВҰ32557 them.
\q1 вүҲThey descended into the depthsВҰ32559 like a stoneВҰ32562.
\q1
\v 6 Yahweh's right arm is so powerfulВҰ32567.
\q1 вүҲYahweh's right arm shatteredВҰ32570 our enemyВҰ32571.
\q1
\v 7 You toss away your adversariesВҰ32576 with your greatВҰ32573 power.
\q1 YourВҰ32576 burningВҰ32578 angerВҰ32578 consumesВҰ32579 them like straw \add in a fire\add*.
\q1
\v 8 It was your breath that made the watersВҰ32585 pile up.
\q1 They stoodВҰ32586 up like a heap.
\q1 The deep water seemed like it was solid.
\q1
\v 9 Our enemies thought that they could chase after us and overtakeВҰ32600 us.
\q1 They had planned to satisfy themselves by sharing out the plunderВҰ32602.
\q1 They were ready to use their swordsВҰ32606 and swing their arms to destroyВҰ32607 us.
\q1
\v 10 \add But\add* you blew with yourВҰ32611 breathВҰ32611.
\q1 The seaВҰ32613 coveredВҰ32612 them.
\q1 They sank like lead in that \add вүҲterrible surge\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 11 Which other god is like you, YahwehВҰ32623?
\q1 Who else is so powerful and yet sinless,
\q2 receiving praisesВҰ32629 for doingВҰ32630 miracles?
\q1
\v 12 You stretchedВҰ32633 out yourВҰ32634 powerful arm.
\q1 The earthВҰ32636 swallowedВҰ32635 them up.
\q1
\v 13 You are leading the peopleВҰ32640 you bought back,
\q2 because you committed yourself to loveВҰ32639 them.
\q1 You used your strengthВҰ32645 to lead them to your \add вүҲsinless\add* home.
\q1
\v 14 Other countries have heardВҰ32651, and they trembleВҰ32653.
\q1 вүҲAnguish has struck the inhabitantsВҰ32656 of Filistia.
\q1
\v 15 The chiefsВҰ32661 of EdomВҰ32662 have panicked.
\q1 вүҲTrembling has seizedВҰ32665 the leadersВҰ32663 of MoabВҰ32664.
\q1 вүҲThe inhabitantsВҰ32669 of Kanaan have meltedВҰ32667 away.
\q1
\v 16 Terror and dreadВҰ32675 have fallenВҰ32672 on them.
\q1 \add After seeing\add* your greatВҰ32676 power, they've stayed as stillВҰ32678 as stoneВҰ32679
\q2 until your people have all marched past, YahwehВҰ32684.
\q1 Until the people you boughtВҰ32691 have all gone past \add them\add*.
\q1
\v 17 BringВҰ32693 them into \add the land\add*
\q2 and establishВҰ32703 them on the mountainВҰ32695 of your inheritanceВҰ32696.
\q1 The placeВҰ32697 you've chosen to become your home, YahwehВҰ32700вҖ”
\q2 a sanctuaryВҰ32701 built by your handsВҰ32704, masterВҰ32702.
\q1
\v 18 YahwehВҰ32706 will reignВҰ32708 \add as king\add* forever andВҰ32710 ever.
\q1
\v 19 Far'oh'sВҰ32715 horse wentВҰ32713 into the sea, along with his chariotsВҰ32716 and horsemen,\f + \fr 15:19 \ft Some interpreters include v19 as part of Mosheh's song (as we do, although it does seem less poetic in structure), while others don't. (There's no speech marks in the ancient Hebrew texts.)\f*
\q1 and YahwehВҰ32720 broughtВҰ32719 the waterВҰ32724 back over them,
\q1 \add after\add* the IsraelisВҰ32727 had walkedВҰ32728 through on dry groundВҰ32729 in the middleВҰ32730 of the sea.вҖқ
\s1 Miryam's song
\rem /s1 The Song of Miriam
\p
\v 20 Then Aharon's sisterВҰ32737 Miryam who was a prophetessВҰ32736, picked up a tambourineВҰ32741 and wentВҰ32743 outside. All the other womenВҰ32746 did likewise and followed herВҰ32742 out to dance together
\v 21 \add so\add* Miryam sang this response:
\q1 вҖңSing to YahwehВҰ32755 and tell of his amazing victoryвҖ”
\q1 He tossed the horsesВҰ32760 and their ridersВҰ32761 into the seaВҰ32763.вҖқ
\s1 The bitter water
\rem /s1 Bitter Water; In the wilderness; The Waters of Marah and Elim; Bitter Water Made Sweet; Bitter Water at Marah
\p
\v 22 Then MoshehВҰ32767 lead the Israelis away from the Red Sea and they moved into the wilderness at ShurВҰ32779. They went through the wilderness for threeВҰ32781 daysВҰ32783 and \add finally\add* foundВҰ32787 some waterВҰ32788,
\v 23 but it was so bitter that they couldn't drinkВҰ32794 it. SoВҰ32790 they named that place вҖҳMarahвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳbitterвҖҷ)\add*,
\v 24 andВҰ32808 the peopleВҰ32809 grumbledВҰ32808 about MoshehВҰ32812 sayingВҰ32813, вҖң\add SoВҰ32808\add* what will weВҰ32816 drinkВҰ32816 \add thenВҰ32808\add*?вҖқ
\v 25 \add SoВҰ32818\add* Mosheh criedВҰ32818 out to Yahweh, and Yahweh showedВҰ32822 him a treeВҰ32824. When he threwВҰ32825 it into the water, the water becameВҰ32829 \add safe to drink\add*.
\p \add @Yahweh\add* made a statue at that place, and a rule, and he testedВҰ32837 \add @Mosheh\add* there,
\v 26 saying, вҖңIf you carefullyВҰ32842 listen to the voice of Yahweh your godВҰ32847, and you do what's rightВҰ32848 in my eyes, and you listen to my commandsВҰ32852 and you keepВҰ32853 all of my laws, thenВҰ32839 I won'tВҰ32864 inflict you with any of the diseasesВҰ32859 thatВҰ32860 I put on the Egyptians, because I'm Yahweh your healer.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add Then they moved on\add* and cameВҰ32874 to ElimВҰ32875 where there were twelve springsВҰ32879 and seventyВҰ32881 palm treesВҰ32882, and they campedВҰ32883 there by the waterВҰ32880.
\c 16
\s1 The manna and the quail
\rem /s1 Manna and Quail; Manna and Quail from Heaven; Bread from Heaven; The Manna and the Quails
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ32890 they left Elim, and all the IsraelisВҰ32898 entered into the wildernessВҰ32901 at Siyn (between Elim and SinaiВҰ32909) \add вүҲaround six weeks\add* afterВҰ32915 leaving EgyptВҰ32917,
\v 2 and all the IsraelisВҰ32926 murmured againstВҰ32930 MoshehВҰ32929 and AharonВҰ32932 \add there\add* in the wildernessВҰ32933,
\v 3 saying, вҖңIfВҰ32938 only \add вүҲYahwehВҰ32945 had killed us\add* in EgyptВҰ32947, \add where we'd be\add* sitting by a pot of meat eating bread until we're full, because you've broughtВҰ32958 us out into this wildernessВҰ32962 to \add вүҲstarve us all to death\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Then YahwehВҰ32975 told MoshehВҰ32978, вҖң\add Just\add* watch me make food rain down from the sky for you all. Then the peopleВҰ32987 will be able to go out every day and gatherВҰ32988 enough for that day so that I can test them: Will they obey my law or not?\x + \xo 16:4: \xt Yhn 6:31.\x*
\v 5 \add вүҲButВҰ33001 every FridayВҰ33005\add* they can \add gather andВҰ33001\add* prepareВҰ33004 twice as much as what they gather on the other days.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add So\add* MoshehВҰ33021 and AharonВҰ33022 told all the IsraelisВҰ33028, вҖңThis eveningВҰ33029 you'll all knowВҰ33030 that YahwehВҰ33032 was the one who broughtВҰ33033 you out from EgyptВҰ33036.
\v 7 In the morningВҰ33038 you'll all seeВҰ33039 Yahweh's greatness as he's heardВҰ33044 yourВҰ33047 murmurings against \add *him\add*. \add I mean,\add* who are weВҰ33051 that you'd murmur against \em us\em*?вҖқ
\v 8 ThenВҰ33058 MoshehВҰ33059 continuedВҰ33058, вҖңSoВҰ33058 Yahweh will giveВҰ33060 you all meat to eat in the eveningВҰ33063 andВҰ33058 enough breadВҰ33066 in the morningВҰ33067 to make you all full. \add Yes,\add* Yahweh has heardВҰ33069 your murmurings against him. As for us, \add вүҲwe're insignificant\add*. Your murmuring isn'tВҰ33081 against us, but against Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ33090 MoshehВҰ33091 told AharonВҰ33094, вҖңSummonВҰ33102 everyoneВҰ33101 to come andВҰ33090 faceВҰ33104 YahwehВҰ33105, because he's heardВҰ33107 their murmurings.вҖқ
\v 10 And so while AharonВҰ33113 spoke to all the IsraelisВҰ33121, they turned toward the wildernessВҰ33125, andВҰ33111 wow, Yahweh'sВҰ33128 \add dazzling brightness\add* appearedВҰ33129 in the cloudВҰ33130!
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ33134 told MoshehВҰ33137,
\v 12 вҖңI've heardВҰ33140 the murmurings of the IsraelisВҰ33145. Speak to them saying, вҖҳIn the evenings, you'll all eat meat, and in the morningsВҰ33153 you'll all be satisfiedВҰ33154 with breadВҰ33156. Then you'll all know that I'm your godВҰ33161, YahwehВҰ33160.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 13 And so that eveningВҰ33164, quailВҰ33166 appeared andВҰ33163 coveredВҰ33167 the camp. And in the morningВҰ33171, \add something like\add* dew was lying all aroundВҰ33175 the camp,
\v 14 andВҰ33178 when it evaporated, wow, it left behind thin flakesВҰ33187вҖ”thin like frostВҰ33189 on the ground there in the wildernessВҰ33185.
\v 15 \add When\add* the IsraelisВҰ33197 sawВҰ33194 it, \add вүҲthey asked each other\add*, вҖҳWhat is it?вҖҷ because they didn'tВҰ33206 know what it was.
\p And MoshehВҰ33212 told them, вҖңIt's the food thatВҰ33216 YahwehВҰ33218 has givenВҰ33217 you all to eat.\x + \xo 16:15: \xt 1Cor 10:3.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲThese are Yahweh'sВҰ33226 instructions\add*: Gather enough of it according to how many people you're feedingвҖ”about two litres per personВҰ33235 who lives in yourВҰ33235 tents.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 \add SoВҰ33241\add* the IsraelisВҰ33245 went ahead and gatheredВҰ33246 itвҖ”some collecting a lot, and others, less,
\v 18 \add but\add* when they measuredВҰ33250 it out, those who'd collected a lot didn'tВҰ33252 have any extra, andВҰ33250 those who hadn't gathered so much still had enough to eatвҖ”each person had gathered just enough.\x + \xo 16:18: \xt 2Cor 8:15.\x*
\v 19 ThenВҰ33264 MoshehВҰ33265 told them, вҖңDon't save any of it for tomorrow,вҖқ
\v 20 \add but some of\add* them didn'tВҰ33276 take any notice of him and kept it untilВҰ33285 the next morningВҰ33287. However, by thenВҰ33276 it was full of maggots and smelt rotten, and Mosheh was very angryВҰ33291 at them.
\p
\v 21 \add SoВҰ33296 from that day onwards,\add* they gatheredВҰ33295 it everyВҰ33299 morning, depending on how many they were feeding, andВҰ33295 thenВҰ33295 when the sunВҰ33303 got hot, \add @the rest\add* meltedВҰ33304 \add away\add*.
\v 22 On the \add вүҲFriday\add*, they gatheredВҰ33310 twice as muchвҖ”around \add four litres\add* for each personвҖ”and all the leaders of the community cameВҰ33316 and informed Mosheh
\v 23 and he told them, вҖңThis is what Yahweh said: Tomorrow is a rest day to be set aside for Yahweh. \add вүҲSoВҰ33324 bake or cook your food, and keep the left-overs overnight to use in\add* the morningВҰ33355.вҖқ\x + \xo 16:23: \xt Exo 20:8-11.\x*
\v 24 \add SoВҰ33358\add* they did what MoshehВҰ33364 had told them and kept the left-overs untilВҰ33359 the morningВҰ33361, and it didn'tВҰ33365 stink or have any bugs in it.
\v 25 On that Saturday morning, MoshehВҰ33374 told them, вҖңGo ahead and eatВҰ33375 the previously cooked food because today is set aside for YahwehВҰ33381 and so you all won'tВҰ33383 find any more \add on the ground\add*вҖ”
\v 26 you'll gatherВҰ33389 it for six daysВҰ33388 \add each week\add*, but on the Saturday, there won'tВҰ33393 be any.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add However,\add* some peopleВҰ33404 did go out to collect it, but they couldn't find any,
\v 28 and YahwehВҰ33411 saidВҰ33410 to MoshehВҰ33414, вҖңFor how long will youВҰ33418 all keep refusingВҰ33418 to obey my commandsВҰ33420 and my laws?
\v 29 Listen, YahwehВҰ33426 has givenВҰ33427 you the Rest Day, so on the Friday he gives you food for twoВҰ33439 daysВҰ33439. On the Saturday, everyoneВҰ33442 shouldВҰ33446 stay where they areвҖ”there's no need for anyoneВҰ33447 to goВҰ33446 outside \add searching\add*.вҖқ
\v 30 SoВҰ33452 the peopleВҰ33453 didn't work on the Saturday.
\p
\v 31 The IsraelisВҰ33460 named it вҖҳmannaВҰ33464вҖҷ \add (which sounds like Hebrew вҖҳWhat is it?вҖҷ)\add*. It was whiteВҰ33468 like corianderВҰ33467 seed, andВҰ33457 it tastedВҰ33469 like wafersВҰ33470 with honeyВҰ33471.\x + \xo 16:31: \xt Num 11:7-8.\x*
\v 32 ThenВҰ33473 MoshehВҰ33474 saidВҰ33473, вҖңThis is the procedure that YahwehВҰ33479 has commandedВҰ33478: Keep a full measure of it for preservation for your descendants so that they can seeВҰ33487 the food which I fed you in the wildernessВҰ33494, when I broughtВҰ33495 you out from EgyptВҰ33498.вҖқ
\v 33 \add SoВҰ33500\add* MoshehВҰ33501 saidВҰ33500 to AharonВҰ33504, вҖңTake a jar andВҰ33500 fill it with the full two litres of mannaВҰ33514. Place it in frontВҰ33517 of YahwehВҰ33518 for preservation for your descendants.вҖқ\x + \xo 16:33: \xt Heb 9:4.\x*
\v 34 \add So\add* AharonВҰ33529 \add prepared the jar and keptВҰ33532 it\add* (and would \add eventually\add* placeВҰ33528 it \add in the box\add* with the \add stone tablets\add*.)
\v 35 The IsraelisВҰ33535 ate manna for fortyВҰ33540 years, until they \add eventually\add* \add вүҲleft the wilderness\add* andВҰ33534 came to the bordersВҰ33558 of the region of CanaanВҰ33560.\x + \xo 16:35: \xt Josh 5:12.\x*
\v 36 (Two litres is called an вҖҳomerвҖҷ which is a tenthВҰ33563 of a вҖҳefahвҖҷ.)
\c 17
\s1 Yahweh gives water from a rock
\rem /s1 Water From the Rock; Water from the Rock
\r (Num. 20:1-13)
\p
\v 1 Then all the IsraelisВҰ33574 moved on from Siyn in the wildernessВҰ33575, travelling following Yahweh'sВҰ33582 instructions. They campedВҰ33583 at RefidimВҰ33584 \add but\add* thereВҰ33585 was no waterВҰ33586 for the people to drinkВҰ33587.\x + \xo 17:1-7: \xt Num 20:2-13.\x*
\v 2 \add SoВҰ33590\add* the peopleВҰ33591 argued with Mosheh \add again\add*, saying, вҖңGive us waterВҰ33599 to drinkВҰ33600!вҖқ
\p вҖңWhy are you all quarrellingВҰ33590 with me?вҖқ Mosheh \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңWhy are you all testing YahwehВҰ33613?вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add ButВҰ33615\add* the people were \add very\add* thirsty thereВҰ33616 and \add *they\add* murmured against MoshehВҰ33623, \add so\add* he \add demanded\add*, вҖңIs this why you brought us out of EgyptВҰ33628? To kill me and my sons and my cattle with thirst?вҖқ ???
\p
\v 4 MoshehВҰ33640 criedВҰ33639 out to YahwehВҰ33643, \add asking\add*, вҖңWhat should I do for \add ^these\add* peopleВҰ33647? \add вүҲIt won't take much more\add* andВҰ33651 they'll \add вүҲkillВҰ33651\add* me.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңWalk on ahead of the peopleВҰ33660,вҖқ YahwehВҰ33654 told MoshehВҰ33657, вҖңand take some of the IsraeliВҰ33663 eldersВҰ33663 with you, and your staffВҰ33665вҖ”the one whichВҰ33666 you struckВҰ33667 the river with. Take it in your handВҰ33673 and goВҰ33674.
\v 6 Watch me. I will standВҰ33677 \add вүҲin front of you\add* thereВҰ33679 on the rock at Horev \add (Mt. Sinai)\add*. Then you will strikeВҰ33685 the rock and waterВҰ33689 will come out of it, and the peopleВҰ33691 will drinkВҰ33690.вҖқ \add So\add* MoshehВҰ33694 did that while the IsraeliВҰ33696 eldersВҰ33696 watched.
\p
\v 7 \add @Mosheh\add* named that placeВҰ33701 \add both\add* вҖҳMassahВҰ33702вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳtestingвҖҷ)\add* and вҖҳMeribahВҰ33703вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳcomplainingвҖҷ)\add*, because of the conflict among the IsraelisВҰ33709 and because of how theyВҰ33711 testedВҰ33711 of Yahweh by saying, вҖҳIs Yahweh among us or not?вҖҷ
\s1 Mosheh's arms held high to defeat Amalek
\rem /s1 The Amalekites Defeated; Israel Defeats the Amalekites; Amalek Attacks Israel and Is Defeated; War with the Amalekites
\p
\v 8 Then the AmalekВҰ33725 \add army\add* cameВҰ33724 and attacked YisraelВҰ33729 at RefidimВҰ33730,
\v 9 and MoshehВҰ33733 instructed Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*, вҖңChoose menВҰ33740 for us and goВҰ33741 out and fightВҰ33742 with AmalekВҰ33743. Tomorrow I'll be stationed on top of the hill with the staffВҰ33751 of GodВҰ33752 in my handВҰ33753.вҖқ
\v 10 \add SoВҰ33755\add* Yehoshua \add prepared\add* to fight AmalekВҰ33763 as Mosheh had told him, and Mosheh, AharonВҰ33765, and HurВҰ33766 climbed up to the top of the hill.
\v 11 And so it happened thatВҰ33778 when MoshehВҰ33774 raised his arm, then YisraelВҰ33777 would be winning, \add but\add* when he \add вүҲlowered his arm\add*, then AmalekВҰ33782 would start winning.
\v 12 \add However,\add* Mosheh'sВҰ33785 arms got tired, so they got a \add large\add* stoneВҰ33789 and satВҰ33792 him on it, and AharonВҰ33794 and HurВҰ33795 stood on each side of him holding up his arms, and holding him steadyВҰ33804 in that position untilВҰ33805 the sunВҰ33808 wentВҰ33807 down.
\v 13 \add SoВҰ33810 this was how\add* YehoshuaВҰ33811 defeatedВҰ33810 AmalekВҰ33814 andВҰ33815 his army with \add #their swordsВҰ33820\add*.
\v 14 Then YahwehВҰ33824 told MoshehВҰ33827, вҖңWrite this event in the book and \add вүҲread it aloud to\add* Yehoshua, because I will certainly blot out the memoryВҰ33830 of AmalekВҰ33842 from \add вүҲoff the earth\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 17:14: \xt Deu 25:17-19; 1Sam 15:2-9.\x*
\v 15 ThenВҰ33846 MoshehВҰ33847 builtВҰ33846 an altarВҰ33848 andВҰ33846 he named it вҖҳYahweh-nissiвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳYahweh is my bannerВҰ33853вҖҷ)\add*,
\v 16 saying, вҖңBecause \add вүҲthey battled\add* against Yah's throneВҰ33861, thenВҰ33855 YahwehВҰ33862 \add вүҲwill battle\add* against AmalekВҰ33865 from generation to generation.вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 Mosheh's father-in-law visits
\rem /s1 Jethro's Visit to Moses; Jethro's Advice; Jethro Visits Moses
\p
\v 1 \add Now\add* Yetro (Jethro), the priestВҰ33872 at MidianВҰ33873 and Mosheh's father-in-lawВҰ33874, heard about everything that GodВҰ33881 had done for Mosheh and for his peopleВҰ33884 the IsraelisвҖ”that YahwehВҰ33888 had broughtВҰ33887 \add #the Israelis\add* out of EgyptВҰ33892.
\v 2 (Yetro had \add been looking after\add* Mosheh's wifeВҰ33901 ZipporahВҰ33900 \add andВҰ33894 their two sons\add* after he had sentВҰ33904 herВҰ33904 back\x + \xo 18:2-3: \xt Exo 2:21-22.\x*
\v 3 along with \add #their\add* twoВҰ33907 sonsВҰ33908. One was named вҖҳGershomВҰ33912вҖҷ \add (which sounds like the Hebrew word for вҖҳforeignerвҖҷ)\add* because \add @Mosheh\add* had saidВҰ33914, вҖңI've been a foreigner living in another country.вҖқ\x + \xo 18:3: \xt Acts 7:29.\x*
\v 4 \add Their\add* other son's nameВҰ33920 was вҖҳEliezerВҰ33922вҖҷ \add (which sounds like the Hebrew word that means вҖҳGod helps meвҖҷ\add*, because Mosheh had said, вҖңGod, who my fatherВҰ33926 worshipped, has helped me andВҰ33928 \add вүҲstopped the Egyptian king Far'ohВҰ33930 from killing me\add*.вҖқ))
\p
\v 5 \add SoВҰ33932 now\add* Mosheh's father-in-lawВҰ33934 brought \add @Mosheh's\add* wife andВҰ33932 sonsВҰ33936 to the wildernessВҰ33943 whereВҰ33944 \add #the people\add* were camping \add near\add* the mountainВҰ33949 of GodВҰ33950.
\v 6 \add вүҲHe had sent a message ahead\add* saying, вҖңI, your father-in-lawВҰ33957 Yetro, am comingВҰ33959 to youВҰ33960, as well as your wifeВҰ33961 andВҰ33952 \add #your\add* twoВҰ33962 sonsВҰ33963.вҖқ
\v 7 \add SoВҰ33966\add* MoshehВҰ33967 went out to meet hisВҰ33977 father-in-lawВҰ33969, and he bowedВҰ33970 down and kissedВҰ33971 him. They askedВҰ33974 each otherВҰ33977 about their welfareВҰ33978, thenВҰ33966 they went into the tent,
\v 8 and MoshehВҰ33983 related to his father-in-lawВҰ33984 all that Yahweh had done to Far'ohВҰ33991 and to Egypt on account of YisraelВҰ33995, all the hardshipВҰ33999 that found them along the wayВҰ34002, and about how Yahweh had rescued them.
\v 9 Yetro \add вүҲwas very happy to hear about\add* all the goodВҰ34011 \add things\add* thatВҰ34012 YahwehВҰ34015 had done for YisraelВҰ34016 when he had rescued them out from Egyptian control,
\v 10 and \add *he\add* saidВҰ34022, вҖңBless YahwehВҰ34025, who rescued youВҰ34028 from \add slavery\add* in EgyptВҰ34030, and from Far'oh's power.
\v 11 Now I \add вүҲcan see\add* thatВҰ34054 YahwehВҰ34048 is greaterВҰ34047 than all the \add other\add* gods because of the \add this result after\add* \add @the Egyptians\add* had actedВҰ34055 proudly againstВҰ34056 \add @you all\add*.вҖқ
\v 12 ThenВҰ34058 Mosheh's father-in-law Yetro made a burntВҰ34062 offeringВҰ34062 as well as sacrificesВҰ34063 to God, and AharonВҰ34066 and all of the IsraeliВҰ34069 eldersВҰ34069 cameВҰ34065 to eatВҰ34071 bread with Mosheh's father-in-law \add вүҲin God's presence\add*.
\s1 Yetro's helpful administrative advice
\rem /s1 Jethro's Wise Advice; The Appointment of Judges
\r (Deu. 1:9-18)
\p
\v 13 The following dayВҰ34082, Mosheh sat down to judgeВҰ34085 the people, andВҰ34081 the people stoodВҰ34089 around \add *him\add* from morningВҰ34096 untilВҰ34097 eveningВҰ34099.
\v 14 When \add *his\add* father-in-lawВҰ34102 noticed everything that he \add personally\add* did for the people, he \add asked\add*, вҖңWhat's this that you'reВҰ34118 doing with the people? Why do you sit \add there\add* alone, andВҰ34101 all the people position themselves aroundВҰ34129 you from morningВҰ34132 untilВҰ34133 eveningВҰ34135?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңBecauseВҰ34140 the peopleВҰ34144 come to me to \add вүҲfind out what GodВҰ34146 wants for them\add*,вҖқ MoshehВҰ34138 replied to \add @Yetro\add*.
\v 16 вҖңWhen a \add difficult\add* situation comes up among them, someone comes to me and I make the judgement between a man and his neighbourВҰ34159. \add In addition,\add* I help them understand the god's statutesВҰ34163 and laws.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңIt's not a goodВҰ34175 \add idea\add* what you'reВҰ34178 doingВҰ34179,вҖқ saidВҰ34169 Yetro.
\v 18 вҖңYou'reВҰ34192 definitely \add on the road to\add* wear yourself out, plus you'll also wear out these peopleВҰ34188 who are with you, because the \add responsibility\add* is too heavyВҰ34194 for youвҖ”you can'tВҰ34197 \add just\add* do itВҰ34200 alone.
\v 19 Now, listenВҰ34204 to \add this\add*: I'll advise you and God will be with you. You be before God for the peopleВҰ34212, and you shouldВҰ34207 bringВҰ34215 their disputes to God yourself.
\v 20 You should \add also\add* teach them the statutesВҰ34228 and the laws, and you should \add teach\add* them the wayВҰ34236 they should \add live\add* and the workВҰ34241 thatВҰ34237 they should do.
\v 21 \add ButВҰ34245\add* you yourself should search through all the peopleВҰ34249 to find capable men who are godly and faithfulВҰ34256, and not \add greedy for\add* dishonest profit. ThenВҰ34245 appoint \add the best of them\add* to be over a thousandВҰ34262 \add >households\add*, and thenВҰ34245 others to be over groups of one hundredВҰ34264, fifty, and ten \add >households\add*.
\v 22 They'll \add be the ones to\add* judge the peopleВҰ34273, except that every serious situation they'll bringВҰ34282 to youвҖ”they'll judge every minor situation themselves. \add Yes,\add* you must lighten this load off yourself, andВҰ34270 they'll share the load with you.
\v 23 IfВҰ34297 you do that, and if GodВҰ34303 tells you \add to proceed\add*, then you'll be able to endureВҰ34305 \add in the long term\add*, plus all of these peopleВҰ34309 \add standing around\add* will be able to return to theirВҰ34313 tents peacefullyВҰ34315.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add SoВҰ34317\add* MoshehВҰ34318 \add вүҲtook his father-in-law'sВҰ34320 advice\add* andВҰ34321 \add вүҲimplemented all of his suggestions\add*.
\v 25 \add *He\add* choseВҰ34326 capable men from among all the Israelis, and he appointed them as heads over the peopleВҰ34339: leaders of thousandsВҰ34341, leaders of hundredsВҰ34343, leaders of fiftiesВҰ34345, and leaders of tens \add of households\add*.
\v 26 They became the ones who settled most disputes for the peopleВҰ34352. They brought the difficultВҰ34359 casesВҰ34358 to MoshehВҰ34363, \add but\add* they judged each minor situation themselves.
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ34373 MoshehВҰ34372 bid farewell to \add @Yetro\add* andВҰ34371 he returned to his own home.
\c 19
\s1 Camping by Mt. Sinai
\rem /s1 At Mount Sinai; The Lord Reveals Himself at Sinai; The Israelites at Mount Sinai; The Israelites Reach Mount Sinai; Israel at Mount Sinai
\p
\v 1 The IsraelisВҰ34388 entered the SinaiВҰ34395 wildernessВҰ34394 in the thirdВҰ34384 monthВҰ34383 afterВҰ34385 exiting EgyptВҰ34390.
\v 2 \add AfterВҰ34407\add* they had departed from RefidimВҰ34398, they had entered the SinaiВҰ34401 wilderness andВҰ34397 camped thereВҰ34406 \add вүҲat the base\add* of the mountainВҰ34409.
\v 3 YahwehВҰ34418 calledВҰ34416 MoshehВҰ34411 from the mountainВҰ34421, so he climbed up and GodВҰ34415 gave him this message and asked him to pass it on to Yacob'sВҰ34426 descendants, the IsraelisВҰ34429:
\p
\v 4 вҖңYou yourselves saw what I did to the EgyptiansвҖ”how I carried you on eagles' wingsВҰ34440 and broughtВҰ34442 you all \add here\add* to myselfВҰ34444.
\v 5 AndВҰ34453 now, if you all carefullyВҰ34449 listen to my \add вүҲwords\add* andВҰ34446 keepВҰ34452 my agreement, thenВҰ34446 \add вүҲyour nation\add* will be my possessionВҰ34458, \add separate\add* from all the \add others\add*, because all the earthВҰ34467 is mine,\x + \xo 19:5-6: \xt 1Pe 2:9.\x*
\v 6 \add SoВҰ34469\add* youВҰ34480 all will be my kingdomВҰ34473 of priestsВҰ34474 andВҰ34475 a nationВҰ34475 \add dedicated to me\add*.вҖқ (That's the messageВҰ34478 to pass on to the IsraelisВҰ34484.)\x + \xo 19:6: \xt Rev 1:6; 5:10.\x*
\v 7 \add SoВҰ34486\add* MoshehВҰ34487 descended \add again\add* andВҰ34486 summoned the IsraeliВҰ34493 eldersВҰ34489, thenВҰ34486 he passed on thatВҰ34498 messageВҰ34496 \add just\add* as YahwehВҰ34500 had commandedВҰ34499 him,
\v 8 andВҰ34502 all the people respondedВҰ34507 togetherВҰ34506, \add agreeing\add*, вҖңWe'll do everything that Yahweh has said.вҖқ ThenВҰ34502 MoshehВҰ34515 took the people's response back to Yahweh
\v 9 andВҰ34524 Yahweh told \add *him\add*, вҖңLook, I'll come to you in a thick cloudВҰ34534 so that the people will be able to hear when I speakВҰ34538 with you \add so they'll also continue to\add* trustВҰ34543 you.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The People Consecrated
\p ThenВҰ34524 Mosheh told Yahweh the people's wordsВҰ34549
\v 10 and YahwehВҰ34556 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ34555\add*, вҖңGo \add down\add* to the peopleВҰ34563 and purify them today and tomorrowВҰ34566. Have them wash theirВҰ34568 clothesВҰ34568
\v 11 andВҰ34570 be preparedВҰ34571 for the third day, because on the third day \add *I\add* will come down to MtВҰ34579. SinaiВҰ34587 while all the peopleВҰ34583 watch.
\v 12 Set boundaries for the peopleВҰ34592 all aroundВҰ34593, andВҰ34599 tell \add <them\add*, вҖҳDon't climb on the mountain or touchВҰ34599 itsВҰ34600 edge, because anyone who does will definitely be executed.\x + \xo 19:12-13: \xt Heb 12:18-20.\x*
\v 13 Anyone \add who touches the mountain\add* mustn't be touched by anyone elseвҖ”they must be \add вүҲexecuted by throwing rocks at them\add* or shooting them \add with a bow\add*. No person or animalВҰ34623 \add who touches the mountain\add* can stay alive.вҖҷ \add вүҲOnly after a longВҰ34629 trumpet blastВҰ34629\add* should they \add start to\add* climb the mountain.вҖқ
\v 14 \add SoВҰ34635\add* MoshehВҰ34636 went down the mountainВҰ34639 to the people. HeВҰ34644 purified them andВҰ34635 they \add all\add* washedВҰ34647 theirВҰ34648 clothesВҰ34648,
\v 15 and he told \add *them\add*, вҖңAbstain from sexual relations, and be ready by the thirdВҰ34656 day.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add SoВҰ34665\add* on the morningВҰ34669 of the thirdВҰ34667 dayВҰ34666, there was thunderВҰ34671 and lightningВҰ34672 and a thick cloudВҰ34673 on the mountainВҰ34677, and an extremely loud horn blast, and all the peopleВҰ34685 in the camp were tremblingВҰ34682.\x + \xo 19:16: \xt Rev 4:5.\x*
\v 17 ThenВҰ34689 MoshehВҰ34690 \add вүҲled\add* the peopleВҰ34693 out of the camp to \add go and\add* meet GodВҰ34691, and they stationed themselves at the \add вүҲfootВҰ34700\add* of the mountainВҰ34701.
\v 18 YahwehВҰ34711 descended onto MtВҰ34720. SinaiВҰ34704 \add surrounded\add* by fireВҰ34712 and the entireВҰ34706 mountain smoked. Its smoke went up like the smoke from a furnaceВҰ34716, and the whole mountain trembledВҰ34717 violently.
\v 19 ThenВҰ34723 it happened \add after\add* the soundВҰ34724 of the horn got extremely loud, that MoshehВҰ34729 was speaking andВҰ34723 GodВҰ34731 was answeringВҰ34732 himВҰ34732 in a voice.
\v 20 YahwehВҰ34736 had descendedВҰ34735 onto the top of MtВҰ34739. SinaiВҰ34740, andВҰ34735 \add *he\add* calledВҰ34745 Mosheh up to the top of the mountain, \add so\add* Mosheh ascendedВҰ34752.
\v 21 \add ButВҰ34755\add* YahwehВҰ34756 told \add *him\add*, вҖңGo \add back\add* down and warnВҰ34761 the peopleВҰ34762 in case theyВҰ34765 force their way throughВҰ34765 to look at \add *me\add* and many of them perishВҰ34770.
\v 22 Also, the priestsВҰ34775 who comeВҰ34776 nearer to \add *me\add*, theyВҰ34780 \add вүҲmust be very careful to purify themselvesВҰ34780\add* in case \add *I\add* \add вүҲsuddenly punish\add* them.вҖқ
\v 23 \add ButВҰ34787\add* MoshehВҰ34788 \add questioned\add* YahwehВҰ34791, вҖңThe peopleВҰ34795 aren'tВҰ34792 able to comeВҰ34796 up on MtВҰ34799. SinaiВҰ34800, because you yourself warnedВҰ34804 us,\x + \xo 19:23 \xt 19:12.\x* вҖҳSet boundariesВҰ34807 all around the mountain to keep it sacred.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 24 вҖңGo \add back\add* down,вҖқ YahwehВҰ34815 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ34813\add*, вҖңand bring AharonВҰ34821 back up with you. \add However,\add* the priestsВҰ34823 and the peopleВҰ34824 \add вүҲmust not cross the boundary\add* to come up to \add *me\add*, in case \add *I\add* \add вүҲsuddenly punish\add* them.вҖқ
\v 25 \add SoВҰ34838\add* MoshehВҰ34839 went down andВҰ34843 spoke to the peopleВҰ34842.
\c 20
\s1 The ten rules
\rem /s1 The Ten Commandments
\r (Deu. 5:1-22)
\p
\v 1 Then GodВҰ34848 \add вүҲgave theseВҰ34853 instructions\add* \add to the Israelis\add*:
\v 2 I'mВҰ34857 your godВҰ34860 YahwehВҰ34859, who \add вүҲrescued you\f + \fr 20:2 \ft Although modern English doesn't easily distinguish it, this discourse is addressed to singular вҖҳyouвҖҷ, i.e., to the Israelis as one group. While some of our modern, individualistic cultures might naturally interpret these rules as applying to individuals, they were given to Yisrael/Israel to implement at a national level.\f* from where you were enslaved in\add* EgyptВҰ34865.
\li1
\v 3 You mustn't own any otherВҰ34879 godsВҰ34877 \add вүҲin myВҰ34883 sight\add*.
\li1
\v 4 You mustn't make a carved figure for yourselfВҰ34890, nor \add carve a copy\add* of anything in the sky aboveВҰ34903 or in the earth below, or that's in the waterВҰ34914 underВҰ34916 the earth.\x + \xo 20:4-5: \xt Exo 34:17; Lev 19:4; 26:1; Deu 4:15-18; 27:15.\x*
\v 5 Don't bow down to \add @idols\add* and don'tВҰ34922 serveВҰ34930 them, because I, your god YahwehВҰ34934, am a jealousВҰ34937 GodВҰ34935. I remember the sins of the fathersВҰ34940 and \add punish\add* the childrenВҰ34943 of \add even\add* the thirdВҰ34946 and fourthВҰ34949 \add generation\add* of those who hate me,\x + \xo 20:5-6: \xt Exo 34:6-7; Num 14:18; Deu 7:9-10.\x*
\v 6 \add but\add* I \add вүҲfaithfully fulfil my promises\add* to \em thousandsВҰ34957\em* \add of generations\add* of those who loveВҰ34959 me andВҰ34960 who obey my instructions.
\li1
\v 7 YouВҰ34976 mustn't \add вүҲwrongly promote\add* the name of YahwehВҰ34970 your godВҰ34971, because \add *I\add* won'tВҰ34964 leaveВҰ34975 anyone unpunishedВҰ34975 who \add вүҲdoes that\add*.\x + \xo 20:7: \xt Lev 19:12.\x*
\li1
\v 8 \add вүҲKeep Saturday different from all the other days\add*\x + \xo 20:8: \xt Exo 16:23-30; 31:12-14.\x*вҖ”
\v 9 there's sixВҰ34999 daysВҰ35001 \add every week\add* for working.\x + \xo 20:9-10: \xt Exo 23:12; 31:15; 34:21; 35:2; Lev 23:3.\x*
\v 10 The seventhВҰ35014 day is a rest day for YahwehВҰ35018 your godВҰ35019: you mustn't do any workвҖ”not you, or your children, or your male or femaleВҰ35037 servants, or your cattle, or the foreigners \add вүҲliving among you\add*вҖ”
\v 11 because YahwehВҰ35054 made the heavensВҰ35057 and earthВҰ35060, the sea, and everything that's in them in six daysВҰ35052. ThenВҰ35078 he restedВҰ35071 on the seventhВҰ35073 day, so that's why \add *he\add* blessedВҰ35077 the rest day and made it sacredВҰ35083.\x + \xo 20:11: \xt Gen 2:1-3; Exo 31:17.\x*
\li1
\v 12 HonourВҰ35089 your father and your motherВҰ35092, so that \add вүҲyou'll have a longВҰ35094 life\add* on the land that your godВҰ35101 YahwehВҰ35100 is aboutВҰ35102 to giveВҰ35102 you.\x + \xo 20:12: a \xt Deu 27:16; Mat 15:4; 19:19; Mrk 7:10; 10:19; Luk 18:20; Eph 6:2; \xo b \xt Eph 6:3.\x*
\li1
\v 13 You mustn't murderВҰ35108.\x + \xo 20:13: \xt Gen 9:6; Lev 24:17; Mat 5:21; 19:18; Mrk 10:19; Luk 18:20; Rom 13:9; Jam 2:11.\x*
\li1
\v 14 You mustn't commitВҰ35114 adulteryВҰ35114.\x + \xo 20:14: \xt Lev 20:10; Mat 5:27; 19:18; Mrk 10:19; Luk 18:20; Rom 13:9; Jam 2:11.\x*
\li1
\v 15 You mustn't stealВҰ35120.\x + \xo 20:15: \xt Lev 19:11; Mat 19:18; Mrk 10:19; Luk 18:20; Rom 13:9.\x*
\li1
\v 16 You mustn't \add вүҲlie in court\add*.\x + \xo 20:16: \xt Exo 23:1; Mat 19:18; Mrk 10:19; Luk 18:20.\x*
\li1
\v 17 You mustn't covet your neighbour'sВҰ35147 houseВҰ35134 or spouse, or their male or femaleВҰ35142 servants, or their animals, or anything else they own.\x + \xo 20:17: \xt Rom 7:7; 13:9.\x*
\s1 The people are afraid of God
\rem /s1 The People's Fear
\r (Deu. 5:22-33)
\p
\v 18 All of the people could hear and see the thunderВҰ35156 and the lightningВҰ35159, the soundВҰ35161 of the horn, and the mountainВҰ35165 smokingВҰ35166. They trembledВҰ35169 \add when\add* \add *they\add* saw it, and they \add remained\add* standing at a distanceВҰ35171.\x + \xo 20:18-19: \xt Heb 12:18-19.\x*
\v 19 They \add begged\add* MoshehВҰ35176, вҖңYou be the one to speak to us, andВҰ35173 we'll listenВҰ35181, but don'tВҰ35182 let GodВҰ35186 speak \add directly\add* to us, in case we dieВҰ35189.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңDon'tВҰ35202 be afraidВҰ35198,вҖқ MoshehВҰ35192 respondedВҰ35191, вҖңbecause GodВҰ35204 has comeВҰ35203 to test you so that the fearВҰ35207 of him \add вүҲwill remain with you\add* so that you all won'tВҰ35196 \add вүҲdisobey him\add*.вҖқ
\v 21 SoВҰ35214 the peopleВҰ35215 stoodВҰ35214 \add вүҲat a good distanceВҰ35216\add* \add while\add* MoshehВҰ35217 approached toward the thickВҰ35221 darknessВҰ35221 whereВҰ35222 GodВҰ35225 was.
\s1 Instructions about altars
\rem /s1 The Law concerning the Altar; Proper Use of Altars; Idols and Altars; Laws about Altars
\p
\v 22 Then Yahweh told MoshehВҰ35232, вҖңThis is what you need to tell the IsraelisВҰ35238: вҖҳYou yourselves have seenВҰ35240 that I, \add Yahweh,\add* have talked with you from heavenВҰ35244.
\v 23 You all mustn't make gods out of silverВҰ35252 or gold for yourselvesВҰ35257 to have alongsideВҰ35250 me.
\v 24 You need to make an altarВҰ35259 for me out of dirt, and then you can sacrificeВҰ35264 your burntВҰ35268 offerings and peace offerings, and your sheepВҰ35274 and cattle, on it. \add вүҲI'll inform you about every placeВҰ35280 whereВҰ35281 I want to be worshipped\add* and I'll comeВҰ35286 to you and will blessВҰ35288 you \add there\add*.
\v 25 IfВҰ35300 you do make me an altarВҰ35292 with stones, you mustn't use cut stones to buildВҰ35299 it because moving your tools over it will defile it.\x + \xo 20:25: \xt Deu 27:5-7; Josh 8:31.\x*
\v 26 And don'tВҰ35308 use stepsВҰ35311 to get up to the altarВҰ35314 because youВҰ35310 might expose your \add вүҲprivate parts\add* \add under your robes\add*.
\c 21
\s1 Rules about slaves
\rem /s1 The Law concerning Slaves; The Treatment of Slaves; Fair Treatment of Slaves
\r (Deu. 15:12-18)
\p
\v 1 These are the rules thatВҰ35325 youВҰ35326 must present to them:
\s2 Hebrew slaves
\rem /s1 Hebrew Servants
\v 2 If you buy a HebrewВҰ35332 slaveВҰ35331, he should serveВҰ35335 for sixВҰ35333 yearsВҰ35334, then in the seventhВҰ35336 year he must be set free withoutВҰ35339 having to pay you anything.\x + \xo 21:2-6: \xt Lev 25:39-46.\x*
\v 3 If he came by himself, he can go free by himself. If he's married with a wife, then his wife must be set free with him.
\v 4 If his master gave him a wife and she bore him sons or daughtersВҰ35368, then the wife and her childrenВҰ35370 are her master's, and only the husband must be set free.
\v 5 \add ButВҰ35377\add* if \add *he\add* plainly says, вҖңI loveВҰ35382 my masterВҰ35385, my wifeВҰ35388, andВҰ35389 my childrenВҰ35391 so I \add voluntarily\add* choose not to be set free,вҖқ
\v 6 thenВҰ35396 his master must take him to \add the place of worship\add*. HeВҰ35411 must bring him to a doorВҰ35404 or to a doorpostВҰ35408, andВҰ35396 his master must bore a hole his earВҰ35413 with an awl. ThenВҰ35396 he must serveВҰ35415 him \add for life\add*.
\p
\v 7 AndВҰ35423 if a manВҰ35422 sells his daughterВҰ35425 as a female slaveВҰ35426, sheВҰ35428 \add вүҲwon'tВҰ35427 be sent away\add* \add after six years\add* like the maleВҰ35430 slavesВҰ35430.
\v 8 If the man who bought her \add вүҲwanted her to become his slave-wife\add*, but \add later\add* \add вүҲhe isn'tВҰ35445 pleased with her behaviour\add*, he must allow her to be bought back by her \add вүҲrelatives\add*. He has no authority to sell her on to outsiders, because that would \add вүҲbreak the understanding of proper treatment\add* of her.
\v 9 Or if he selected her \add вүҲto become his son's slave-wife\add*, thenВҰ35453 he must treat her \add вүҲlike a daughterВҰ35458 would expect to be treated\add*.
\v 10 If he \add вүҲgo on to takeВҰ35466 anotherВҰ35465 slave-wife\add*, he mustn't reduceВҰ35473 \add @the first one's\add* food or clothingВҰ35470, or herВҰ35469 maritalВҰ35471 rightsВҰ35471,
\v 11 \add but\add* if heВҰ35481 doesn't provide theseВҰ35479 threeВҰ35477 things to her, thenВҰ35475 she can goВҰ35483 free withoutВҰ35484 \add вүҲhaving to pay anything\add*.
\s1 Rules about violence to others
\rem /s1 The Law concerning Violence; Laws about Violent Acts; Cases of Personal Injury; Personal Injuries
\p
\v 12 Whoever strikesВҰ35489 \add #someone\add* andВҰ35491 \add #that person\add* diesВҰ35491, must definitely be put to deathВҰ35493.\x + \xo 21:12: \xt Lev 24:17.\x*
\v 13 ButВҰ35495 if \add вүҲit wasn't premeditated\add*вҖ”if GodВҰ35498 had let it happenВҰ35499 as an accidentвҖ”thenВҰ35495 I'll assign a placeВҰ35503 whereВҰ35504 \add @the one who hit them\add* can flee to.\x + \xo 21:13: \xt Num 35:10-34; Deu 19:1-13; Josh 20:1-9.\x*
\v 14 \add However,\add* if \add #someone\add* \add вүҲhad schemed to trap andВҰ35509\add* killВҰ35516 \add #their\add* neighbourВҰ35515, then \add even if the killer clings to\add* my altarВҰ35519, you must takeВҰ35520 \add #them\add* for execution.
\p
\v 15 Anyone who strikesВҰ35524 \add #their\add* fatherВҰ35525 or motherВҰ35526 must certainly be put to deathВҰ35528.
\p
\v 16 Anyone who abducts another personвҖ”either to sell or to keep \add as a slave\add*вҖ”\add @that person\add* must certainly be put to deathВҰ35536.\x + \xo 21:16: \xt Deu 24:7.\x*
\p
\v 17 Anyone who cursesВҰ35539 \add #their\add* fatherВҰ35540 or motherВҰ35541 must certainly be put to deathВҰ35543.\x + \xo 21:17: \xt Lev 20:9; Mat 15:4; Mrk 7:10.\x*
\p
\v 18 IfВҰ35553 \add #two people\add* fight and \add #one\add* hits \add #their\add* neighbourВҰ35555 with a stoneВҰ35556 or with \add #their\add* fist, and \add #the injured one\add* doesn't dieВҰ35560 but is bedridden,
\v 19 if \add #that person\add* \add eventually\add* rises and can walk about outsideВҰ35568 using a staffВҰ35571, then the \add #person who struckВҰ35573 them\add* is free, other than \add вүҲreimbursing the costs of their lost work and their medical expenses\add*.
\p
\v 20 If a \add #master\add* hits \add #their\add* male or femaleВҰ35591 slave with a staff and \add @the slave\add* dies, then the death must certainlyВҰ35596 be avengedВҰ35596.
\v 21 HoweverВҰ35608, if \add @the slave\add* is able to stand within a couple of daysВҰ35604, then the \add owner\add* won'tВҰ35606 be \add вүҲpunished\add* because \add @the slave\add* is \add #their\add* propertyВҰ35609.
\p
\v 22 If \add #two people\add* fight togetherВҰ35615 and strike a pregnantВҰ35619 woman and \add вүҲcause herВҰ35621 to deliver the baby\add*, if there's no serious injury, then he must certainlyВҰ35625 be finedВҰ35626 whatever the husbandВҰ35630 of the woman \add вүҲdemands\add* and the judgesВҰ35633 allow.
\v 23 ButВҰ35635 if there's serious injury, thenВҰ35635 you must give a life for a life,
\v 24 an eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth, a hand for a hand, a foot for a foot,\x + \xo 21:24: \xt Lev 24:19-20; Deu 19:21; Mat 5:38.\x*
\v 25 a burn for a burn, a wound for a wound, and a bruise for a bruise.
\p
\v 26 If a \add #master\add* hits \add #their\add* male or femaleВҰ35681 slave's eye and damages it, \add #they\add* must let \add @the slave\add* go free in compensation for the eye.
\v 27 \add Or\add* if the \add #master\add* knocksВҰ35697 out a tooth of a male or femaleВҰ35696 slave, \add #they\add* must let \add @the slave\add* go free in compensation for the tooth.
\s1 Rules about property
\rem /s1 Laws concerning Property; The Responsibility of Owners
\p
\v 28 If a bull gores a man or a womanВҰ35714 and \add #they\add* die, the bull must certainlyВҰ35716 be \add вүҲkilled by throwing rocks at it\add*. The ownerВҰ35724 of the animal is \add to be considered\add* innocent, \add but\add* its meat mustn't be eatenВҰ35720.
\v 29 ButВҰ35728 if the bull had a habit of goring in the past and its owner was warnedВҰ35734 but didn'tВҰ35736 keep it \add fenced\add* in, and it killsВҰ35738 a man or a womanВҰ35741, thenВҰ35728 the bull must be \add вүҲkilled by throwing rocks at it\add* and its owner must also be put to death.
\v 30 If a ransom payment is demanded instead, \add @the owner\add* may buy back \add #their\add* lifeВҰ35756 by paying the full amount demanded.
\v 31 Those rules also apply if the bull gores a \add person's\add* son or daughterВҰ35769.
\v 32 If the bull gores a male or femaleВҰ35782 slave, \add @its owner\add* must give thirtyВҰ35785 silverВҰ35783 shekelsВҰ35786 to the \add slave owner\add* and the bull must be \add вүҲkilled by throwing rocks at it\add*.
\p
\v 33 IfВҰ35799 \add #someone\add* uncovers a \add pit for storage\add*, or digs a \add new one\add* and leaves it uncovered, and a cowВҰ35809 or a donkeyВҰ35811 fallsВҰ35806 into it,
\v 34 the owner of the pit must pay compensationВҰ35815. \add @The pit owner\add* must pay in cash, \add but\add* the deadВҰ35819 animal will then belongВҰ35820 to them.
\v 35 If \add #one person's bull\add* attacks \add someone else's\add* bull and itВҰ35827 diesВҰ35835, then they should sell the liveВҰ35840 animal and divide the money as well as dividing up the deadВҰ35848 animal.
\v 36 \add ButВҰ35853\add* if it was knownВҰ35852 that the bull had a habit of goring in the past and its owner hadn't kept it \add fenced\add* in, then \add @that owner\add* must certainlyВҰ35862 give a live bull for the dead one, \add but\add* the dead animal will become \add #theirs\add*.
\c 22
\s1 Rules about loss of property or farm animals
\rem /s1 Laws of Restitution; Protection of Property; Laws about Repayment
\p
\v 1 If \add #someone\add* steals a cow or a sheep and slaughters it or sells it, he must compensate five cattle for the cow or four sheep for the sheep.
\p
\v 2 (If a thief is discovered \add at night\add* while breaking in, and is struck and dies, \add вүҲno one should be charged for murder\add*.
\v 3 But if it'sВҰ35929 daylight already, then that person is guilty of murder.)
\p \add @A thief\add* who's caught must make restitutionВҰ35941, but if \add #they're\add* unable to pay, then \add @the thief\add* must be sold \add to cover it\add*.
\v 4 IfВҰ35954 a thief is found in the possession of a stolen animal, be it a cow or a donkey or a sheep, then \add #they\add* must pay back anotherВҰ35960 matching animal as well.\f + \fr 22:4 \ft Or possibly, must pay back \bd two\bd* additional animals.\f*
\p
\v 5 IfВҰ35984 a person releases their livestock to graze \add their own\add* field or vineyard, and it \add ends up\add* grazing in the someone else's field, \add @the owner of the animal\add* must compensate from the best of their field and from the best of their vineyard.
\p
\v 6 IfВҰ35990 a fire breaks out and spreads in \add вүҲthe bush\add*, and grain that's already stacked or is still in the field gets burnt up, the person who started the fire must certainly pay compensation.
\p
\v 7 IfВҰ36024 \add #anyone\add* gives their neighbour money or goods for safekeeping, and if it is stolen from the neighbour's houseВҰ36021, if the thiefВҰ36017 is foundВҰ36016, \add #they\add* must pay double in compensation.
\v 8 If the thief can't be found, then the owner of the house must be brought to \add вүҲthe judgesВҰ36072 for God's decision\add* as to whether or not \add #they\add* have \add вүҲimproperly handled\add* \add #their\add* neighbour'sВҰ36075 property.
\p
\v 9 Concerning every other squabble about any cattle or a donkeyВҰ36086 or sheepВҰ36092, or about clothing or any lost property that's under dispute, both parties must go to \add вүҲthe judges for God's decision\add*вҖ”anyoneВҰ36082 who God declares to be guilty must pay his neighbourВҰ36085 double as compensation.
\p
\v 10 IfВҰ36109 anyone gives \add #their\add* neighbourВҰ36119 a donkey or a cow or a sheep or any animal to look after, and it dies or is injured or disappears without anyone seeing,
\v 11 both of them must declare in front of Yahweh as to whether or not they \add вүҲimproperly handled\add* \add #their\add* neighbour's property. The ownerВҰ36132 must accept \add <the sworn statement\add* andВҰ36126 no compensation is required,
\v 12 \add but\add* if it was truly stolen from \add @the neighbour\add*, \add #they\add* must pay compensation to the owner.
\v 13 If it was truly \add вүҲkilled by a some other animal\add*, \add @the neighbourВҰ36152\add* must bring \add @the remains\add* as evidence, and no compensation is required.
\p
\v 14 If anyone borrows \add <an animalВҰ36173\add* from \add #their\add* neighbour and it gets injured or dies without the ownerВҰ36167 being with it, \add @the person who borrowed it\add* must pay compensation,
\v 15 \add but\add* if its owner was \add there\add* with it, no compensation is requiredвҖ”if it was for hire, then that was included in its hiring fee.
\s1 More rules about everyday life
\rem /s1 Social and Religious Laws; Moral and Religious Laws; Social Responsibility
\p
\v 16 If a man entices a young woman who's not engaged, and sleeps with her, he must certainly pay the brideВҰ36206 price \add to her fatherВҰ36201\add* for her to become his wife.\x + \xo 22:16-17: \xt Deu 22:28-29.\x*
\v 17 If her father absolutely refuses to give her to him, \add @the man\add* must \add still\add* pay the normal bride price in cash.
\p
\v 18 You must execute any woman who practices sorcery.\x + \xo 22:18: \xt Deu 18:10-11.\x*
\p
\v 19 AnyoneВҰ36232 who has sex with an animal must be executed.\x + \xo 22:19: \xt Lev 18:23; 20:15-16; Deu 27:21.\x*
\p
\v 20 You must execute anyone who offers a sacrifice to any god other than Yahweh.\x + \xo 22:20: \xt Deu 17:2-7.\x*
\p
\v 21 You mustn't disadvantage or oppress any \add вүҲforeigner staying in your country\add*, because you were \add вүҲforeigners staying\add* in the land of Egypt.\x + \xo 22:21-22: \xt Exo 23:9; Lev 19:33-34; Deu 24:17-18; 27:19.\x*
\v 22 YouВҰ36270 mustn't mistreat any widow or any fatherless child,
\v 23 \add because\add* if youВҰ36277 \add *do\add* and theyВҰ36279 ask me to help them, I'llВҰ36277 help them
\v 24 and get angry. I'll cause you all to die in battle, and your wives will become widows and your \add #children\add* will become fatherless.
\p
\v 25 If you loan money to any my people who are poor, you mustn't act like an \add impartial\add* creditor to \add #them\add*вҖ”you mustn't charge \add #them\add* interest.\x + \xo 22:25: \xt Lev 25:35-38; Deu 15:7-11; 23:19-20.\x*
\v 26 IfВҰ36344 you actually take the your neighbour's \add вүҲcloakВҰ36331\add* as a security, you must return it to \add #them\add* by sunset,\x + \xo 22:26-27: \xt Deu 24:10-13.\x*
\v 27 because it's \add #their\add* only covering. What else could \add #they\add* cover themselves with when \add #they\add* try to sleep? If \add #they\add* cry out to me, I'll \add вүҲact on it\add*, because I'm compassionate.
\p
\v 28 You mustn't insult God, and don'tВҰ36359 curse your leaders.\x + \xo 22:28: \xt Acts 23:5.\x*
\p
\v 29 You mustn't \add fail to give\add* me the best parts of the grain that you harvest, or \add the best\add* olive oil or wine that you produce.
\p You must give your firstborn sons to me,
\v 30 plus you must do the same with your cattle and your sheep and goats. TheВҰ36398 young must stay seven days with \add #their\add* mothers, then you must give \add #them\add* to me on the eighth day.
\p
\v 31 You must be \add вүҲdifferent from others because you're dedicated to me\add*. \add So\add* you mustn't eat the meat of animals that are mauled in the countrysideвҖ”throw it to the dogs \add instead\add*.\x + \xo 22:31: \xt Lev 17:15.\x*
\c 23
\s1 Rules about honesty and kindness
\rem /s1 Justice for All; Justice and Fairness; Laws of Justice and Mercy; A Call for Justice
\p
\v 1 You mustn't present a false statement. Don't conspire with a wickedВҰ36411 \add >person\add* to give false evidence.\x + \xo 23:1: \xt Exo 20:16; Lev 19:11-12; Deu 5:20.\x*
\v 2 Don't \add just\add* follow the crowd into doing what's wrongВҰ36423, andВҰ36424 don'tВҰ36417 \add just\add* say what others say in court \add if it's untrue\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ36435 don'tВҰ36436 \add automatically\add* favour the poor in court either.\x + \xo 23:3: \xt Lev 19:15.\x*
\p
\v 4 IfВҰ36441 you come across your enemy'sВҰ36444 cowВҰ36443 or donkeyВҰ36446 going astray, you must certainlyВҰ36448 takeВҰ36449 it back to \add #them\add*.\x + \xo 23:4-5: \xt Deu 22:1-4.\x*
\v 5 IfВҰ36453 you seeВҰ36455 that the donkeyВҰ36456 of someone who hatesВҰ36457 you has fallen to the ground underВҰ36459 its load, you mustn't \add вүҲjust walk way\add*вҖ”you must certainlyВҰ36464 help \add #them\add* \add вүҲwith it\add*.
\p
\v 6 You mustn't deny justiceВҰ36471 to the poor in \add #their\add* lawsuitsВҰ36473.\x + \xo 23:6-8: \xt Lev 19:15; Deu 16:19.\x*
\v 7 Stay far way from deceptive words. You mustn't killВҰ36483 innocent or honest \add >people\add* because I won'tВҰ36481 \add allow\add* wickedВҰ36488 \add >people\add* to be declaredВҰ36487 innocent.
\v 8 YouВҰ36493 mustn't accept \add #bribes\add*, because \add #bribes\add* \add вүҲstop people from being unbiased\add* andВҰ36497 \add #they\add* undermine the wordsВҰ36498 of \add вүҲhonest\add* \add >people\add*.
\p
\v 9 YouВҰ36506 mustn't oppressВҰ36503 \add #foreigners\add* since you \add #yourselves\add* know \add вүҲhow that feels\add* because you all were foreigners in EgyptВҰ36515.\x + \xo 23:9: \xt Exo 22:21; Lev 19:33-34; Deu 24:17-18; 27:19.\x*
\s1 The seventh year and the seventh day
\rem /s1 Sabbath Laws; Sabbatical Year and Sabbath; The Seventh Year and the Seventh Day
\p
\v 10 You should plant yourВҰ36522 land andВҰ36517 gatherВҰ36523 itsВҰ36526 produce for sixВҰ36517 yearsВҰ36518,\x + \xo 23:10-11: \xt Lev 25:1-7.\x*
\v 11 \add but\add* in the seventhВҰ36528 \add >year\add* you must let \add @the harvest\add* drop and \add just\add* leaveВҰ36534 it there and \add allow\add* the poor peopleВҰ36533 to eat it. ThenВҰ36528 the animalsВҰ36536 in the countrysideВҰ36537 can eat the reminder. You must \add also\add* do that to your vineyardsВҰ36541 and your oliveВҰ36542 orchards.
\p
\v 12 Six days You should work for six days, then on the seventhВҰ36549 \add >day\add* you must rest so that your cowВҰ36553 and your donkeyВҰ36554 can rest, and the \add #children\add* of your \add #slaves\add* and the foreigner \add staying in your land\add* can be refreshedВҰ36555.\x + \xo 23:12: \xt Exo 20:9-11; 31:15; 34:21; 35:2; Lev 23:3; Deu 5:13-14.\x*
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲTake careful notice of\add* everything that I've told you all. You all mustn't \add invoke\add* otherВҰ36569 godsВҰ36568вҖ”\add in fact\add* \add вүҲdon'tВҰ36570 even mention their names\add*.
\s1 Three compulsory celebrations each year
\rem /s1 Three Annual Festivals; The Annual Festivals; The Three Great Festivals; The Three Annual Festivals
\r (Exo. 34:18-26; Deu. 16:1-17)
\p
\v 14 You must celebrateВҰ36580 me three times every yearВҰ36582.
\v 15 \add 1/\add* You must observe the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it*. You must eatВҰ36591 unleavened breadВҰ36587 for sevenВҰ36589 daysВҰ36590 as I commandedВҰ36594 you, in late March or early April because that's when you cameВҰ36601 out from EgyptВҰ36602. You mustn't come without an offering.\x + \xo 23:15: \xt Exo 12:14-20; Lev 23:6-8; Num 28:17-25.\x*
\p
\v 16 \add 2/\add* You must observe the \it \add Spring\add* Harvest Celebration\it*, bringing the firstВҰ36611 portion of your harvests from what you planted.
\p \add 3/\add* You must observe the \it \add Finished\add* Harvest Celebration\it* at the endВҰ36618 of the yearВҰ36619, after you've finished harvesting \add вүҲeverything you planted\add*.
\v 17 \add So\add* all yourВҰ36634 malesВҰ36634 must gather in front of the masterВҰ36638 YahwehВҰ36640 three timesВҰ36629 each yearВҰ36630.
\p
\v 18 You mustn't sacrifice the bloodВҰ36648 of my sacrifices together with bread \add вүҲthat's been risen\add*, andВҰ36651 all the fat \add must be burnt during the night\add* so that none remainsВҰ36653 in the morningВҰ36659.
\p
\v 19 You must bringВҰ36664 the \add вүҲbest\add* of the firstfruitsВҰ36661 of your \add вүҲharvests\add* to the houseВҰ36665 of YahwehВҰ36666 your godВҰ36667.
\rem /s1 The Conquest of Canaan Promised; A Promise of the Lord's Presence; Promises and Instructions; God's Angel to Prepare the Way
\p You mustn't boil a young goat in its mother'sВҰ36673 milk.\x + \xo 23:19: \xt Deu 26:2; Exo 34:26; Deu 14:21.\x*
\s1 Promises and teachings
\p
\v 20 Listen, I'm aboutВҰ36678 to sendВҰ36678 a messengerВҰ36679 \add вүҲin front of you\add* to guardВҰ36681 you on the wayВҰ36682, and to take you to the placeВҰ36686 thatВҰ36687 I have preparedВҰ36688.
\v 21 \add вүҲStay behind him\add* and listenВҰ36692 to \add вүҲwhat he says\add*. Don't \add вүҲannoy\add* him because he won'tВҰ36694 \add вүҲput up with disobedience\add* because \add вүҲhe represents my authority\add*.
\v 22 \add But\add* if you \add вүҲtake carefulВҰ36709 notice of his words\add* and do everything that I sayВҰ36715, then I'll be an enemyВҰ36716 to your enemiesВҰ36719 and I'll be against those who are against you.
\v 23 My messengerВҰ36728 will goВҰ36727 \add вүҲahead of you\add* and take you to \add faceВҰ36729\add* the AmoritesВҰ36733, the HittitesВҰ36734, the PerizzitesВҰ36735, the CanaanitesВҰ36736, the HivitesВҰ36737, and the YebusitesВҰ36738, and then I'll annihilate them.
\v 24 YouВҰ36750 mustn't serveВҰ36746 or bow down to their godsВҰ36744, and you mustn't do \add @what those people\add* do, because you must completely overthrow them and completely smash their \add sacredВҰ36755\add* stone pillarsВҰ36755.
\v 25 You all must worship your godВҰ36760 YahwehВҰ36759, and he'll blessВҰ36761 your food and your waterВҰ36767. I'll keep sicknessВҰ36769 away from youВҰ36770
\v 26 \add and\add* there won't be \add #any miscarriagesВҰ36774\add* or \add #women\add* in your land that can't conceive. I'llВҰ36781 ensure \add вүҲthat you live your full\add* numberВҰ36779 of daysВҰ36780.
\p
\v 27 I'll \add вүҲgoВҰ36795 ahead of you and will terrify\add* and confuseВҰ36788 all of the peopleВҰ36793 \add groups\add* \add вүҲwhose lands you'll enter\add*, and I'll \add вүҲcause them to flee from you in battle\add*.
\v 28 I'll sendВҰ36806 hornetsВҰ36809 \add вүҲahead of you\add* and \add #they'll\add* driveВҰ36811 out the HivitesВҰ36814, the CanaanitesВҰ36817, and the HittitesВҰ36820 \add вүҲbeforeВҰ36821 you get there\add*.
\v 29 I won't driveВҰ36824 them out \add вүҲmore than a yearВҰ36826 ahead of you\add* in case the area becomesВҰ36830 desolate and the \add вүҲwild animalsВҰ36835 proliferate too much\add* in the countrysideВҰ36836.
\v 30 I'llВҰ36846 driveВҰ36840 them out little by little \add вүҲahead of you\add* untilВҰ36842 \add вүҲyourВҰ36841 numbers increase\add* and you takeВҰ36845 over the land.
\v 31 ThenВҰ36850 I'll \add вүҲhelp you establish\add* yourВҰ36873 bordersВҰ36853 from the Red Sea to the Mediterranean, and from the wildernessВҰ36861 to the \add Euphrates\add* riverВҰ36864, because I'll \add вүҲhelp you defeat the existing\add* inhabitantsВҰ36870 of the land and so you'll driveВҰ36872 them right out.
\v 32 You mustn't make any agreement with \add @those people\add* or with theirВҰ36879 godsВҰ36879.
\v 33 They mustn't live in your land, in case they causeВҰ36887 you to sinВҰ36887 against me. Their godsВҰ36894 would certainly becomeВҰ36897 a trap for you, and then you'd \add end up\add* worshipping them.
\c 24
\s1 The people confirm their agreement
\rem /s1 Israel Accepts the Lord's Covenant; The Covenant Is Sealed; The Blood of the Covenant; The Covenant Confirmed
\p
\v 1 Then \add @Yahweh\add* told MoshehВҰ36904, вҖңCome up \add the mountain\add* to \add *me\add*вҖ”you, AharonВҰ36911, NadabВҰ36912, AbihuВҰ36913 and seventyВҰ36914 of the IsraeliВҰ36916 eldersВҰ36915, and you must \add stay\add* at a distanceВҰ36918 to worshipВҰ36917.
\v 2 ThenВҰ36925 MoshehВҰ36921 aloneВҰ36922 must approach \add *me\add*, \add but\add* \add @the others\add* mustn't come near, andВҰ36920 \add also\add* the peopleВҰ36929 mustn't come up with him.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add SoВҰ36934\add* MoshehВҰ36935 wentВҰ36934 andВҰ36934 explained to the people \add вүҲeverything that Yahweh had said, including\add* all the regulations. ThenВҰ36934 all of the people answeredВҰ36947 \add вүҲin unison\add*, вҖңWe'll do everything that Yahweh has \add вүҲtold us to do\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 \add SoВҰ36963\add* MoshehВҰ36964 wroteВҰ36963 \add вүҲdown everything that YahwehВҰ36969 had instructed\add*. ThenВҰ36963 he got up earlyВҰ36970 in the morningВҰ36971 and builtВҰ36972 an altarВҰ36973 at the bottom of the mountainВҰ36975 and \add set up\add* twelve stone pillarsВҰ36978 for the twelve tribesВҰ36981 of YisraelВҰ36982,
\v 5 and he sentВҰ36984 some young menВҰ36987 to offer burntВҰ36991 offerings and to sacrificeВҰ36992 some bullsВҰ36996 as peaceВҰ36994 offerings to YahwehВҰ36995.
\v 6 MoshehВҰ36999 took half of the blood \add from the sacrifices\add* andВҰ36998 put it into basinsВҰ37003. He sprinkledВҰ37006 \add the other\add* half of the blood onto the altarВҰ37009.
\v 7 ThenВҰ37011 he tookВҰ37011 the scroll with the agreement \add written on it\add* and read it out loud to the peopleВҰ37016, and they \add вүҲrespondedВҰ37017\add*, вҖңWe'll obeyВҰ37024 everything that YahwehВҰ37022 has instructed.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ37026 MoshehВҰ37027 took the blood \add in the bowls\add* andВҰ37026 sprinkledВҰ37031 it onto the peopleВҰ37034, telling \add <them\add*, вҖңLook. \add This is\add* the blood \add confirming\add* the agreement thatВҰ37040 YahwehВҰ37042 has made with you according to \add вүҲwhat you just heard\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 24:8: a \xt Mat 26:28; Mrk 14:24; Luk 22:20; 1Cor 11:25; Heb 10:29; \xo b \xt Heb 9:19-20.\x*
\rem /s1 On the Mountain with God
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ37050 MoshehВҰ37051, AharonВҰ37052, NadabВҰ37053, AbihuВҰ37054, andВҰ37050 seventyВҰ37055 IsraeliВҰ37057 eldersВҰ37056 climbed up \add the mountain\add*
\v 10 andВҰ37059 theyВҰ37059 sawВҰ37059 the godВҰ37061 of YisraelВҰ37062. UnderВҰ37060 his feetВҰ37064 was something like a tile made of sapphireВҰ37067 that \add вүҲlooked so pure that it was as clearВҰ37070\add* as the sky.
\v 11 ThoseВҰ37076 IsraeliВҰ37075 leaders sawВҰ37080 GodВҰ37083 and \add вүҲyet they weren't harmed by him.\add*. ThenВҰ37072 they ateВҰ37084 and drankВҰ37085 \add together\add*.
\s1 Mosheh's long stay on Mt. Sinai
\rem /s1 Moses on Mount Sinai
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ37089 told MoshehВҰ37092, вҖңCome up to me on the mountainВҰ37095 and \add wait\add* thereВҰ37098, and I will giveВҰ37099 you some stoneВҰ37104 slabs with the rules and regulations thatВҰ37107 I have writtenВҰ37108 \add on them so you can\add* to teach them \add <to the people\add*.вҖқ
\v 13 \add SoВҰ37111\add* Mosheh and his assistantВҰ37114 Yehoshua set off, and Mosheh climbed up God's mountainВҰ37119.
\v 14 He had \add already\add* told the eldersВҰ37124, вҖңWait for us \add down here\add* in this place untilВҰ37130 weВҰ37133 returnВҰ37133 \add here\add* to you all. And see, AharonВҰ37136 andВҰ37122 HurВҰ37137 are with youвҖ”\add вүҲany leader judging mattersВҰ37142 requiring more wisdom can approach\add* them \add for help\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ37153 MoshehВҰ37147 went to \add the base of\add* the mountain andВҰ37151 a cloudВҰ37152 coveredВҰ37151 \add over\add* \add *it\add*.
\v 16 Yahweh'sВҰ37160 \add вүҲradiance\add* settledВҰ37157 on MtВҰ37163. SinaiВҰ37164, andВҰ37157 the cloud coveredВҰ37165 it for sixВҰ37167 daysВҰ37168, thenВҰ37157 on the seventhВҰ37174 dayВҰ37173 he calledВҰ37169 to MoshehВҰ37172 from within the cloud.
\v 17 The appearanceВҰ37178 of Yahweh'sВҰ37180 \add вүҲradiance\add* was like a \add вүҲroaring\add* fireВҰ37181 on the top of the mountainВҰ37184 \add вүҲfrom what the IsraelisВҰ37187 below could see\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ37189 Mosheh entered \add into\add* the cloudВҰ37192 and continued up the mountain, and \add *he\add* remained up there for forty full days.\x + \xo 24:18: \xt Deu 9:9.\x*
\c 25
\s1 Contributions for God's tent
\rem /s1 Offerings for the Sacred Tent; Offerings for the Tabernacle
\r (Exo. 35:4-9)
\p
\v 1 YahwehВҰ37207 told MoshehВҰ37210,
\v 2 вҖңTell the IsraelisВҰ37217 that they should \add вүҲraise funds\add* for me. You should collect a contributionВҰ37221 from everyВҰ37223 \add #family\add* that's willing to donate.
\v 3 You should accept contributionsВҰ37235 of goldВҰ37239, silverВҰ37240, or bronzeВҰ37241,
\v 4 as well as yarn \add dyed\add* blue, purpleВҰ37244, or crimsonВҰ37245, plus finely-spun linenВҰ37247 andВҰ37243 \add spun\add* goatВҰ37248 hair,
\v 5 and red-dyed ram skinsВҰ37250, fine leatherВҰ37253, and acaciaВҰ37256 timber.
\v 6 \add Also\add* lamp oil, spicesВҰ37260 for \add making\add* anointingВҰ37262 oil andВҰ37263 fragrantВҰ37264 incenseВҰ37263,
\v 7 onyx and \add other\add* gemstones for settingВҰ37270 into the apron and the breastplateВҰ37272.
\v 8 ThenВҰ37274 they should make me a residence \add so\add* I can live \add in it\add* among them,
\v 9 according to the \add #patterns\add* that I'll show youВҰ37284 for the residence and for all of itsВҰ37292 utensils. You all must make \add вүҲall of it exactly to plan\add*.
\s1 The box to hold the stone slabs
\rem /s1 Plans for the Ark; The Ark of the Covenant; The Covenant Box; The Ark
\r (Exo. 37:1-9)
\p
\v 10 They must make a wooden chestВҰ37298 from acaciaВҰ37300 wood. It should be 125cm longВҰ37303, with the width and the height being 75cm.
\v 11 ItВҰ37312 must be overlaid with pure gold \add sheeting\add* on the outsideВҰ37316 and the insideВҰ37315, and have a gold mouldingВҰ37320 \add fitted\add* all aroundВҰ37322 it.
\v 12 FourВҰ37326 goldВҰ37328 rings must be cast andВҰ37324 attached to the four feetВҰ37332вҖ”two rings on each side.
\v 13 MakeВҰ37351 two \add carrying\add* polesВҰ37347 from acaciaВҰ37349 wood andВҰ37350 overlayВҰ37350 them with goldВҰ37352 \add sheeting\add*.
\v 14 Those polesВҰ37357 will be inserted through the ringsВҰ37358 on the sidesВҰ37360 of the chestВҰ37361 so it can be \add picked up andВҰ37354\add* carried on them.
\v 15 The polesВҰ37371 must be kept in the ringsВҰ37368 on the chestВҰ37369вҖ”they mustn't be removedВҰ37373.
\v 16 The \add вүҲtwo stone slabs thatВҰ37382 I'll giveВҰ37383 youВҰ37384 with our agreement inscribed on them\add* must be placed inside the chestВҰ37379.
\p
\v 17 You must make a lid the same length and width as the chest. It must be made of pure goldВҰ37388 \add and will be known as\add* вҖҳthe atonementВҰ37387 platformвҖҷ.\x + \xo 25:17: \xt Heb 9:5.\x*
\v 18 ThenВҰ37403 make a pair of winged-creatures from goldВҰ37400 that's hammeredВҰ37401 from the two endsВҰ37405 of the atonement platform.
\v 19 \add YesВҰ37422,\add* make one winged-creature from each end of the gold lid material.
\v 20 \add *Their\add* up-lifted wings should spreadВҰ37432 out coveringВҰ37435 the atonement platform andВҰ37430 they should be facing each other across the top of the platform.
\v 21 When I giveВҰ37468 you the stone slabs, put them inside the boxВҰ37458 andВҰ37452 thenВҰ37452 fasten the atonement platform on top to form the lid.
\v 22 ThenВҰ37471 I'll meet with you thereВҰ37473, and from the atonement platform betweenВҰ37478 the twoВҰ37479 winged-creatures and aboveВҰ37482 the stone slabs, I'll be able to tell you my commandsВҰ37490 to pass on to the IsraelisВҰ37495.
\s1 The bread-offering table
\rem /s1 The Table for the Bread of the Presence; Plans for the Table; The Table for the Bread Offered to God; The Table
\r (Exo. 37:10-16)
\p
\v 23 You must make a tableВҰ37499 from acaciaВҰ37501 wood: one metre longВҰ37503, 500cm wideВҰ37505, and 750cm highВҰ37508.
\v 24 OverlayВҰ37511 it with pure gold andВҰ37510 have a gold mouldingВҰ37516 fitted all aroundВҰ37518 it.
\v 25 Make an 8cm wide rim around it andВҰ37520 fit a goldВҰ37528 mouldingВҰ37526 onto the rim.
\v 26 MakeВҰ37538 four goldВҰ37536 rings andВҰ37532 attach them near the legs on the four cornersВҰ37543 \add of the table\add*
\v 27 near the rim. \add @The ringsВҰ37551\add* are so polesВҰ37553 can be inserted in order to carryВҰ37554 the tableВҰ37557.
\v 28 Make \add two\add* polesВҰ37562 out of acaciaВҰ37564 wood andВҰ37559 overlaidВҰ37565 them with goldВҰ37567 for carryingВҰ37568 the tableВҰ37573.
\v 29 \add InВҰ37586 addition,\add* make the necessary platesВҰ37576 and pans, and the pitchersВҰ37578 and bowlsВҰ37579 to be used for pouring out \add <the wine offerings\add*вҖ”all from pure goldВҰ37583.
\v 30 You must keep sacred breadВҰ37592 on the tableВҰ37591 continuallyВҰ37595 in front of me.\x + \xo 25:30: \xt Lev 24:5-8.\x*
\s1 The lampstand
\rem /s1 The Lampstand; Plans for the Lampstand
\r (Exo. 37:17-24)
\p
\v 31 You must make a lampstand from pure gold. The base and shaftВҰ37606 are to be hammeredВҰ37602 out \add of one piece of gold\add* as well as its cups and \add decorative\add* buds and flowers.
\v 32 There must be six branches extending from the shaftвҖ”three on each side.
\v 33 ThreeВҰ37629 cups shaped like almond flowers must be on each branchВҰ37645 along with a bud and petals.
\v 34 The \add centre\add* shaft must have fourВҰ37652 cups like almondВҰ37654 flowers along with a bud andВҰ37651 petalsВҰ37656.
\v 35 For each of the three pairs of branches \add (one branch out each side in each pair)\add*, make a bud \add on the centre shaft\add* so each pair of branches appear to be growing out of it.
\v 36 These buds and their branchesВҰ37682 must all be hammeredВҰ37686 out from \add that\add* single piece of pure goldВҰ37688.
\v 37 Make sevenВҰ37695 lamps andВҰ37691 set them up on it to giveВҰ37700 lightВҰ37700 out from the frontВҰ37704 of it,
\v 38 and make all the utensils and dishes for the lamps from pure goldВҰ37708.
\v 39 This can all be made from 35kg of pure goldВҰ37712
\v 40 andВҰ37723 be sure to make it all like the patternВҰ37724 thatВҰ37725 you'reВҰ37727 beingВҰ37728 shownВҰ37728 on the mountainВҰ37729.\x + \xo 25:40: \xt Acts 7:44; Heb 8:5.\x*
\c 26
\s1 Plans for the sacred residence
\rem /s1 Plans for the Tabernacle; The Tabernacle; The Tent of the Lord's Presence
\r (Exo. 36:8-38)
\p
\v 1 You must make \add &my\add* residence with tenВҰ37736 fabric panels formed by a skilledВҰ37746 craftsman. They must be made from twistedВҰ37739 finely-spun linenВҰ37738, with winged-creatures \add embroidered on them using\add* blue, purpleВҰ37741, and scarlet thread.
\v 2 The hanging panels must all be the same size: 14.5m long and two metresВҰ37756 wide.
\v 3 Five of the panels will be coupled together \add as one set\add* andВҰ37776 the other fiveВҰ37776 as another.
\v 4 For each set, make loopsВҰ37785 of blue cloth andВҰ37793 fasten them along the outerВҰ37797 edge of each of the endВҰ37791 panelsвҖ”
\v 5 place fiftyВҰ37806 loops on the end of each set so thatВҰ37811 the loops are oppositeВҰ37814 each other.
\v 6 You'llВҰ37827 also need to make fiftyВҰ37822 goldВҰ37824 clips to join the two sets together to make a single walled structure.
\p
\v 7 YouВҰ37852 must make eleven panels with goats' hairВҰ37842 to form a tentВҰ37846 over the residence.
\v 8 Each of the eleven panels must be the same size: 15m long andВҰ37860 two metresВҰ37859 wide.
\v 9 You must join fiveВҰ37874 panels into a set, andВҰ37871 sixВҰ37879 panels into the other set so that the sixthВҰ37886 panel can be doubledВҰ37882 over at the frontВҰ37889 of the tent.
\v 10 You must make 50 loops to go onto the end of one set, andВҰ37902 another 50 for the edge of the other set.
\v 11 You'll also need to make fiftyВҰ37913 bronzeВҰ37912 clips to join the two sets togetherВҰ37919 to make the tent cover.
\v 12 Let the extra half panel hang over the back of the residence.
\v 13 The half metre of extra lengthВҰ37943 on each side that extends beyond the linen sets will hang \add evenly\add* over the sidesВҰ37950.
\p
\v 14 You must make a covering of rams hides dyed red to go over the tent, thenВҰ37956 another covering sea-cow hides to go over that.
\s2 The wooden frames
\rem /s1 The Framework
\p
\v 15 You must make framesВҰ37971 for \add &my\add* residence from acaciaВҰ37974 wood. They'll standВҰ37975 uprightВҰ37975
\v 16 \add and\add* each one must be five metresВҰ37978 high and 0.75m wide.
\v 17 Each frame must have two protrusions so it can be connected to the frame next to it.
\v 18 AssembleВҰ38004 twentyВҰ38008 framesВҰ38006 for the south side of the residence
\v 19 along with fortyВҰ38014 silverВҰ38017 bases to go underneath themвҖ”two bases supporting each frame, andВҰ38014 each frame having two protrusions at the bottom to go into the bases.
\v 20 For the northВҰ38043 side, assemble twentyВҰ38044 framesВҰ38045
\v 21 along with fortyВҰ38047 silverВҰ38049 basesвҖ”two under each frame.
\v 22 For the rear of the residence facing west, assemble sixВҰ38065 framesВҰ38066
\v 23 plus two extra framesВҰ38069 for \add bracing\add* the two back cornersВҰ38071вҖ”
\v 24 they must be joined \add on\add* at the bottomВҰ38077 andВҰ38075 thenВҰ38075 both of them have theirВҰ38090 tops attached to a ring.
\v 25 ThenВҰ38095 assemble eightВҰ38096 frames with theirВҰ38098 sixteen silverВҰ38099 basesвҖ”two bases supporting each frame.
\p
\v 26 Make crossbars from acaciaВҰ38117 woodвҖ”fiveВҰ38118 of them to go across the framesВҰ38119 on the northern side,
\v 27 five for the south side, andВҰ38125 five for the frames at the rear of the residence on the western side.
\v 28 The middle crossbar in the centre of the framesВҰ38143 will go right throughВҰ38144 from one end to the other.
\v 29 Overlay the framesВҰ38154 and the crossbars with gold, and make the ringsВҰ38159 for holding the crossbars with gold.
\v 30 ThenВҰ38171 you must assemble \add &my\add* residence exactly as per the plan thatВҰ38175 you were shownВҰ38176 on the mountainВҰ38177.
\s2 The curtain
\rem /s1 The Curtain
\p
\v 31 YouВҰ38191 must have a skillfulВҰ38189 workman make a curtainВҰ38181 from twistedВҰ38187 finely-spun linenВҰ38186, with winged-creatures \add embroidered on them using\add* blue, purpleВҰ38183, and scarlet thread.
\v 32 HangВҰ38195 it from gold clips on four pillarsВҰ38199 made from acaciaВҰ38200 wood overlaidВҰ38201 with gold on four silverВҰ38210 basesВҰ38208.
\v 33 Hang the curtain underВҰ38216 the clips, thenВҰ38212 bringВҰ38218 the boxВҰ38223 that contains the agreement insideВҰ38220 the curtain. That curtain will separateВҰ38225 for youВҰ38227 between the sacred section andВҰ38212 the \em very\em* sacred interior.\x + \xo 26:33: \xt Heb 6:19; 9:3-5.\x*
\v 34 InstallВҰ38235 the atonement platform as the lid on the boxВҰ38239 there in the very sacredВҰ38241 interior.
\v 35 Set the table up outsideВҰ38248 the curtainВҰ38249 on the northВҰ38264 side, with the lampstandВҰ38252 on the southВҰ38258 side oppositeВҰ38253 the table.
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ38266 make a curtain out of twistedВҰ38275 finely-spun linenВҰ38274 for the entranceВҰ38268 of the tent. It should be embroidered with blue, purpleВҰ38271 andВҰ38266 scarlet yarn.
\v 37 Make five pillarsВҰ38282 for the curtain from acaciaВҰ38283 wood overlaidВҰ38284 with gold. The hooksВҰ38287 on them must be made of gold, andВҰ38279 theirВҰ38287 five basesВҰ38292 must be cast with bronzeВҰ38293.
\c 27
\s1 The altar for burnt offerings
\rem /s1 Plans for the Altar of Burnt Offering; The Altar of Burnt Offering; The Altar
\r (Exo. 38:1-7)
\p
\v 1 MakeВҰ38297 an altar from acaciaВҰ38301 wood that's 2.5m squareВҰ38308 and 1.5m highВҰ38313
\v 2 andВҰ38323 as part of that same piece of wood, include \add a carved projection like\add* a horn on each of the top cornersВҰ38319 of the altar. OverlayВҰ38324 \add @the altar\add* with bronzeВҰ38325.
\v 3 Make pots for the ashesВҰ38329 out of bronzeВҰ38338, along with the necessary shovelsВҰ38330, sprinkling bowls, meat forksВҰ38332, andВҰ38327 fire-trays.
\v 4 ThenВҰ38340 make a bronze gratingВҰ38342 for it with four ringsВҰ38351 of bronze on the four cornersВҰ38355.
\v 5 FitВҰ38358 it down onto a ledgeВҰ38360 inside the altar so that it sits inside the altar about halfway up.
\v 6 \add AlsoВҰ38376,\add* make poles from acaciaВҰ38374 wood for the altarВҰ38371 andВҰ38375 overlayВҰ38375 them with bronzeВҰ38377.
\v 7 They'll be able to be put into ringsВҰ38383 on twoВҰ38388 sidesВҰ38389 of the altarВҰ38390 for carryingВҰ38391 it.
\v 8 The altar should be hollow in the middle and made from \add wooden\add* planks just like you were shown on the mountainВҰ38401.
\s1 The courtyard around the sacred tent
\rem /s1 Plans for the Courtyard; The Enclosure for the Tent of the Lord's Presence; The Courtyard; The Court and Its Hangings
\r (Exo. 38:9-20)
\p
\v 9 Make curtains of twistedВҰ38417 finely-spun linenВҰ38416 \add to form\add* a courtyardВҰ38408 \add around\add* the residence. The south side will require fifty metresВҰ38419 of curtain
\v 10 with twenty \add bronzeВҰ38428\add* pillars and their twenty basesВҰ38426. The hooksВҰ38429 on the pillars and the clips must be made of silverВҰ38432.
\v 11 Similarly on the northВҰ38436 side, \add another\add* fifty metres of curtainВҰ38438 with twenty pillars and their basesВҰ38444 and their hooksВҰ38447 and clips.
\v 12 The west side will require twenty-five metres of curtainВҰ38457 with ten pillarsВҰ38460 andВҰ38452 basesВҰ38462.
\v 13 The east side of the courtyardВҰ38466 must also be twenty-five metres wide.
\v 14 Only side side of the gate, the curtainВҰ38476 will be 7.5m long with three pillarsВҰ38478 andВҰ38473 basesВҰ38480,
\v 15 andВҰ38491 the same on the other side.
\v 16 The entrance curtain must be made of twistedВҰ38505 finely-spun linenВҰ38504. It'll be ten metres wide and hang on four pillarsВҰ38508 with their basesВҰ38510, and must be embroidered with blue, purpleВҰ38501, and scarlet yarn.
\v 17 All the pillarsВҰ38515 for the courtyardВҰ38516 must have silver decorations aroundВҰ38517 them, as well as their silver hooksВҰ38520 and bronzeВҰ38523 basesВҰ38522.
\v 18 \add So\add* the courtyardВҰ38526 will be fifty metres by twenty-five metres and the curtain enclosure will be 2.5m high. All the curtains will be made of finely-spun linenВҰ38536, and the basesВҰ38538 under all the pillars will be bronzeВҰ38539.
\v 19 All the equipment for the operation of the residence and all the tentВҰ38543 pegs and pegs for the courtyardВҰ38552 must be made of bronzeВҰ38553.
\s1 The oil for the lamps
\rem /s1 Oil for the Lampstand; The Oil for the Lamp; Taking Care of the Lamp
\r (Lev. 24:1-4)
\p
\v 20 OrderВҰ38559 the IsraelisВҰ38562 to bringВҰ38563 you pure, pressedВҰ38568 oliveВҰ38566 oil for the lamps so they can be kept burning continuallyВҰ38572.
\v 21 In the outer portion of the sacred tent (outsideВҰ38576 the curtainВҰ38577 where the sacred box is kept), AharonВҰ38584 andВҰ38585 his sonsВҰ38585 must attend to the lampstand in frontВҰ38590 of YahwehВҰ38591 from eveningВҰ38586 to morningВҰ38589. This regulationВҰ38592 will apply continually to all future generationsВҰ38594 of IsraelisВҰ38597.
\c 28
\s1 The priests' uniform
\rem /s1 Vestments for the Priesthood; The Priestly Garments; Garments for the Priests; Clothing for the Priests
\r (Exo. 39:1-7)
\p
\v 1 \add Now,\add* have your brotherВҰ38606 Aharon and his sons brought to you from amongВҰ38611 the IsraelisВҰ38613. Aharon, NadabВҰ38618, AbihuВҰ38619, EleazarВҰ38620, and IthamarВҰ38621 will become my priestsВҰ38614.
\v 2 Make sacredВҰ38628 clothes for AharonВҰ38629вҖ”they must be \add uniquely\add* beautifulВҰ38632
\v 3 \add so\add* speakВҰ38635 to all the \add вүҲskilledВҰ38640 craftsmen who've been givenВҰ38644\add* the spiritВҰ38645 of wisdomВҰ38646, andВҰ38634 they can make Aharon'sВҰ38648 clothes to \add вүҲdedicate him as\add* my priestВҰ38653.
\v 4 These are the clothes thatВҰ38659 they'll need to make: a small pouch to hang around the neck and an apron, a robeВҰ38663 and a tunicВҰ38664 of woven workВҰ38665, and a turbanВҰ38666 and a waistband. They must make \add those\add* sacredВҰ38671 clothes for your brotherВҰ38673 AharonВҰ38672 and for his sonsВҰ38674 to serveВҰ38675 as my priestsВҰ38675.
\v 5 \add @The skilled craftsmen\add* must \add вүҲbe given\add* goldВҰ38683 \add wire\add* and blue, purpleВҰ38689, and scarletВҰ38692 yarn, and finely-spun linenВҰ38696.
\rem /s1 The Ephod; Design of the Ephod
\p
\v 6 TheyВҰ38700 must make the sacred apron from twistedВҰ38709 finely-spun linenВҰ38708 with goldВҰ38703 \add wire\add* and blue, purpleВҰ38705, scarlet yarn embroidered onto it by a skilledВҰ38711 craftsman.
\v 7 It should have two shoulder pieces attached to \add the top\add* two corners so it can be fastened.
\v 8 ThenВҰ38725 the waistband for the apron shall be made with similar workmanshipВҰ38729 from twistedВҰ38738 finely-spun linenВҰ38737 with goldВҰ38732 \add wire\add* and blue, purpleВҰ38734, and scarlet yarn skillfullyВҰ38726 embroidered into it.
\v 9 ThenВҰ38740 get twoВҰ38743 onyx stonesВҰ38744 andВҰ38747 engraveВҰ38747 the namesВҰ38749 of Yisra'el'sВҰ38751 \add twelve\add* sonsВҰ38750 onto themвҖ”
\v 10 six names on one stone and six on the other, in their birthВҰ38767 orderВҰ38767.
\v 11 AВҰ38783 stoneВҰ38771 craftsman with experience at making signet rings should do the engravingsВҰ38770, and then mount the twoВҰ38777 stonesВҰ38778 in decorative goldВҰ38786 settingsВҰ38785.
\v 12 ThenВҰ38790 attach the two stones to the shoulder pieces of the apron as a reminder about Yisra'el's sonsВҰ38800. That way AharonВҰ38803 will carry theirВҰ38806 namesВҰ38806 on his two shoulders as a reminder \add every time\add* he goes to faceВҰ38807 YahwehВҰ38808.
\v 13 Make the decorative settingsВҰ38817 for the \add two\add* stones from goldВҰ38818,
\v 14 andВҰ38829 thenВҰ38820 make twoВҰ38820 twistedВҰ38824 chains of pure goldВҰ38822 like a cord that youВҰ38825 can attach to the decorative settingsВҰ38836.
\s1 The chestpiece
\rem /s1 Design of the Chestpiece; The Breastpiece; The Breastplate
\r (Exo. 39:8-21)
\p
\v 15 Make a \bd sacred chest pouch\bd* for \add вүҲimportant decision making\add*. A skilledВҰ38843 craftsman should make it from twistedВҰ38853 finely-spun linenВҰ38852 like the apron, embroidered with goldВҰ38847 \add wire\add* and blue, purpleВҰ38849, and scarlet yarn.
\v 16 It needs to be 23cm square when foldedВҰ38859 over doubleВҰ38859,
\v 17 andВҰ38865 it will have fourВҰ38869 rows of \add three\add* gemstones on it: a \add red\add* ruby, a \add yellow\add* topazВҰ38874, a \add green\add* emeraldВҰ38875,
\v 18 thenВҰ38879 a turquoiseВҰ38881, a \add blue\add* sapphireВҰ38882, a diamondВҰ38883,
\v 19 thenВҰ38885 a \add red\add* jacinthВҰ38887, a \add white\add* agateВҰ38888, a \add purple\add* amethystВҰ38889,
\v 20 and in the last row, a \add yellow\add* beryl, an onyx, and a \add green\add* jasperВҰ38895. All those stones must be mounted in decorative goldВҰ38897 settingsВҰ38899,
\v 21 andВҰ38901 \add so\add* they'll represent the twelve tribesВҰ38923 of YisraelВҰ38908. The names of the twelve sons must be engravedВҰ38914 on the stonesВҰ38901 similar to how signet rings \add are made\add*.
\v 22 Make two twistedВҰ38930 chainsВҰ38929 of pure goldВҰ38933 like a cord that you can attach to the pouch,
\v 23 thenВҰ38936 make two goldВҰ38942 rings andВҰ38936 attach them to the two \add top\add* corners of the pouch.
\v 24 AttachВҰ38955 the two goldВҰ38959 chains to the ringsВҰ38963 on the corners
\v 25 with the other endsВҰ38971 fastened to the two decorative settingsВҰ38978 \add around the stones\add* andВҰ38969 thenВҰ38969 attached to the frontВҰ38986 side of the shoulderВҰ38982 straps.
\v 26 MakeВҰ38994 two more goldВҰ38992 ringsВҰ38991 andВҰ38989 attach them on the inside to the two \add bottom\add* corners of the pouch,
\v 27 andВҰ39010 another two goldВҰ39013 ringsВҰ39012 to be attached to the bottom of the two shoulder pieces near where the shoulder straps join the apron just aboveВҰ39026 the crafted waistbandВҰ39027.
\v 28 ThenВҰ39031 tie the rings on the sacred pouch to the rings on the apron with a blue cord so that the pouch sits above the waistband andВҰ39047 can'tВҰ39047 come loose from the apron.
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ39054 \add whenever\add* AharonВҰ39055 enters the sacred inner room \add to stand\add* in frontВҰ39072 of \add *me\add*, he'll be carrying the namesВҰ39058 of Yisra'el's sonsВҰ39059 over his heartВҰ39066 on the sacred pouch that'll be used for making decisions.
\v 30 ThenВҰ39077 place the вҖҳUrimвҖҷ andВҰ39077 the вҖҳTummimвҖҷ\f + \fr 28:30 \ft These two objects appear abruptly in the textвҖ”they haven't been described previouslyвҖ”in fact, they're not described anywhere, so we don't really know much about them except that it seems they were used somehow to indicate Yahweh's decision on important matters. Although we presume that Mosheh must have already been familiar with them, sadly we're unable to translate these two Hebrew words, because we're not.\f* in the sacred pouch so they'll be over Aharon's heart when he goes in before Yahweh, thus Aharon will continuallyВҰ39109 bear the decisions of the IsraelisВҰ39103 over his heart before Yahweh.\x + \xo 28:30: \xt Num 27:21; Deu 33:8; Ezr 2:63; Neh 7:65.\x*
\s1 The other parts of the uniform
\rem /s1 Additional Clothing for the Priests; Other Priestly Vestments; Other Priestly Garments; The Other Priestly Garments
\r (Exo. 39:22-31)
\p
\v 31 MakeВҰ39113 the \bd robeВҰ39115\bd* \add to be worn under\add* the sacred apron entirelyВҰ39117 from blue material
\v 32 with an opening for his head in the middleВҰ39124 of it. A border will be needed aroundВҰ39128 the opening so it can'tВҰ39136 tearвҖ”this should be woven like openings in regular clothes.
\v 33 ThenВҰ39139 on the bottom hem, make \add decorations that look like\add* pomegranatesвҖ”they must be made from blue, purpleВҰ39145, andВҰ39139 scarlet yarn. Gold bellsВҰ39152 should hang in between the pomegranates
\v 34 so as you go aroundВҰ39167 the hem of the robe there'll be a gold bell, then a pomegranate, then a gold bell, then a pomegranate, etc.
\v 35 AharonВҰ39172 must wear this robe when he's serving, so when he goesВҰ39176 into \add *my\add* presence in the sacred inner room, I'llВҰ39181 hear the bells when he enters andВҰ39169 when he leaves, so he won'tВҰ39183 dieВҰ39184.
\p
\v 36 Make a \add вүҲplateВҰ39188\add* from pure goldВҰ39189 and engraveВҰ39191 вҖҳDedicated to YahwehВҰ39196вҖҷ on it like you would on a signet ring.
\v 37 AttachВҰ39199 it to the frontВҰ39210 of the turban using a blue cord
\v 38 \add so\add* it'll be on Aharon's forehead. \add In this way,\add* it'll bear the \add deficiencies of human\add* sinfulness when IsraelisВҰ39230 \add attempt\add* to make sacred objects and \add attempt\add* to make sacred offerings. Thus it'll be on his forehead continuallyВҰ39239 so thatВҰ39227 \add *I\add* will \add see it and\add* acceptВҰ39240 those thingsВҰ39226.
\p
\v 39 The \bd tunicВҰ39246\bd* must be woven from finely-spun linen, andВҰ39245 similarly for the \bd turbanВҰ39249\bd*. An embroiderer must make the \bd waistband\bd*.
\p
\v 40 You must \add also\add* make tunicsВҰ39259, waistbands and headbands for Aharon's sonsВҰ39256 so they'll \add look\add* splendid and beautifulВҰ39267.
\v 41 Put these clothes on your brotherВҰ39274 AharonВҰ39273 and his sonsВҰ39277, thenВҰ39269 anointВҰ39279 them \add with oil\add* and ordainВҰ39281 and consecrateВҰ39285 them as priestsВҰ39287 to me.
\v 42 Make \bd underwearВҰ39292\bd* out of linenВҰ39294 to coverВҰ39295 their bare fleshВҰ39296 from the waistВҰ39298 to the thighsВҰ39301вҖ”
\v 43 they must wear it whenever they enter the sacredВҰ39323 tentВҰ39323 and whenever they approachВҰ39318 the altarВҰ39321 to offer sacrifices so they won'tВҰ39324 be disobeying and dieВҰ39328. AharonВҰ39307 and his descendantsВҰ39332 must obey that rule forever.
\c 29
\s1 Consecrating the priests
\rem /s1 Instructions for Ordaining Aaron and His Sons as Priests; The Ordination of the Priests; Dedication of the Priests; Consecration of the Priests
\r (Lev. 8:1-36)
\p
\v 1 Now this is how youВҰ39340 should consecrateВҰ39342 them to be priestsВҰ39344 to me: Take a young bullВҰ39347 from the herd and twoВҰ39353 rams withoutВҰ39354 defectsВҰ39354.
\v 2 \add AlsoВҰ39369,\add* using finely-ground wheatВҰ39367 flourВҰ39366, \add bake\add* flat breadВҰ39356, flat cakesВҰ39358 with \add olive\add* oil in them, andВҰ39356 flat wafersВҰ39362 sprinkled with \add olive\add* oil.
\v 3 Put \add @the baking\add* into a basket, and bringВҰ39377 the basket \add to me\add* along with the bullВҰ39382 and twoВҰ39384 rams.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ39387 take AharonВҰ39389 and his sonsВҰ39392 near to the entranceВҰ39396 of the sacredВҰ39397 tent and wash them with waterВҰ39401.
\v 5 Take the clothes and dress AharonВҰ39410 in the tunicВҰ39413 and the robeВҰ39415 that goes with the apron, thenВҰ39403 the sacred apron and the sacred pouch, and tie the waistband around the apron.
\v 6 PutВҰ39434 the turban on his head andВҰ39433 attach the sacredВҰ39437 \add gold\add* ornament to it,
\v 7 thenВҰ39442 takeВҰ39442 the anointingВҰ39446 oil andВҰ39442 pour it over his head to dedicate him.
\v 8 \add Next,\add* bringВҰ39457 his sonsВҰ39456 andВҰ39458 put tunicsВҰ39459 on them
\v 9 and wrap waistbands around them and tie on their headbands. TheyВҰ39462 \add and their descendants\add* will be priestsВҰ39471 forever, and you must ordainВҰ39474 \add both\add* AharonВҰ39464 and his sons.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ39482 bringВҰ39482 the bull to the frontВҰ39486 of the sacredВҰ39487 tent and get AharonВҰ39490 and his sons to put theirВҰ39494 handsВҰ39494 on its head,
\v 11 thenВҰ39500 slaughterВҰ39500\f + \fr 29:11 \ft The throat will be cut with a sharp knife, and the blood will be caught in a bowl.\f* the bullВҰ39503 before \add *me\add* at the entranceВҰ39506 of the sacredВҰ39507 tent.
\v 12 TakeВҰ39519 some of that blood andВҰ39510 smear it on the top projections of the altar with your fingerВҰ39518, thenВҰ39510 pour the rest of it \add on the ground\add* at the base of the altar.
\v 13 Take all the fat coveringВҰ39536 the innards including the lobe above the liverВҰ39544, as well as both kidneysВҰ39547 and the fat on them, and burnВҰ39553 it all on the altarВҰ39554,
\v 14 but the bull's meat and hide and intestines must be burnt outsideВҰ39568 the camp. Sacrificing \add the bull's fat like that\add* is an act of purification.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ39573 takeВҰ39577 one of the rams and have AharonВҰ39579 and his sonsВҰ39580 place theirВҰ39583 handsВҰ39583 on \add *its\add* head,
\v 16 thenВҰ39589 slaughterВҰ39589 it. \add Catch\add* the bloodВҰ39596 andВҰ39589 sprinkleВҰ39597 it all over \add the sides of\add* the altarВҰ39600.
\v 17 ThenВҰ39603 cut the ram into pieces and wash its innards and its legs, and put \add @those bits\add* \add together\add* with the head and the \add other\add* pieces.
\v 18 ThenВҰ39619 burnВҰ39619 \add *it\add* all on the altarВҰ39625. That will be a burntВҰ39626 offering to \add *me\add*вҖ”a pleasingВҰ39630 aromaВҰ39629 \add from\add* the offering by fireВҰ39631.\x + \xo 29:18: \xt Eph 5:2; Php 4:18.\x*
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ39635 takeВҰ39635 the secondВҰ39638 ram, and have AharonВҰ39640 and his sonsВҰ39641 place theirВҰ39644 handsВҰ39644 on \add *its\add* head,
\v 20 thenВҰ39650 slaughterВҰ39650 it. \add Catch\add* the blood and smear some of it on the tip of AharonВҰ39661 and his sons' right ears and on their right thumbsВҰ39670 and big toes. ThenВҰ39650 sprinkleВҰ39678 the rest all over \add the sides of\add* the altarВҰ39684.
\v 21 Take some of the bloodВҰ39690 that is on the altarВҰ39694 and some of the anointingВҰ39696 oil, and sprinkleВҰ39697 that on Aharon and his clothes, and on his sons and their clothes. That will consecrateВҰ39712 Aharon and his sons and their \add priestly\add* clothes.
\p
\v 22 Take the fat of \add that second\add* ram, and its fat tail, the fat coveringВҰ39730 its innards and the lobe above the liverВҰ39736, the twoВҰ39739 kidneysВҰ39740 and that fat that's on them, and the rightВҰ39748 thighВҰ39747, \add because\add* this ram is for consecration.
\v 23 \add AlsoВҰ39767\add* take one \add round\add* bread loaf, one cake of bread made with oil in it, andВҰ39754 one waferВҰ39761 from that basketВҰ39763 of flat breads that's \add offered to\add* \add *me\add*.
\v 24 PutВҰ39781 all those into the hands of AharonВҰ39773 and his sonsВҰ39776, and \add they\add* must wave them before \add *me\add* as a wave offering.
\v 25 ThenВҰ39783 takeВҰ39783 them from theirВҰ39785 handsВҰ39785 and burnВҰ39786 them completely on the altarВҰ39787 on top of the burntВҰ39790 offering. That also will be a fireВҰ39795 offering to \add *me\add*, and its aromaВҰ39791 will please \add *me\add*.
\p
\v 26 TakeВҰ39811 the breastВҰ39802 meat of the ram (\add the second one\add* for the consecration of AharonВҰ39806) and wave it as a wave offering before \add *me\add*. ThenВҰ39799 after thatВҰ39805 it will be your share \add to cook and eat\add*.
\p
\v 27 \add SoВҰ39816\add* you should consecrate the breastВҰ39819 of the wave offeringВҰ39820 and the thighВҰ39822 of the contributionВҰ39823 from the ram of consecration for AharonВҰ39831 and his sonsВҰ39833.
\v 28 Those will belong to AharonВҰ39836 andВҰ39835 his sonsВҰ39837 as their regular portionВҰ39838 from the IsraelisвҖ”it will be a contribution from the Israelis from their peace offerings to \add *me\add*.
\p
\v 29 TheВҰ39870 sacredВҰ39859 clothes thatВҰ39860 belongВҰ39862 to AharonВҰ39861 will be used for his male descendants to wear \add in turn\add* when they're anointedВҰ39865 andВҰ39858 consecrated.
\v 30 The priestВҰ39877 who succeedsВҰ39878 himВҰ39878 from among his sonsВҰ39879, who comes into the sacred tentВҰ39887 to serve in the sacred inner room must wear them for seven daysВҰ39875.
\p
\v 31 Take the ram of consecration andВҰ39893 boil itsВҰ39896 meat in a sacredВҰ39898 placeВҰ39897,
\v 32 thenВҰ39900 AharonВҰ39901 andВҰ39900 his sonsВҰ39902 should eat the meat of the ram as well as the breadsВҰ39909 thatВҰ39910 are in the basketВҰ39911 at the entranceВҰ39912 to the tent.
\v 33 They must eat those thingsВҰ39933 used to make atonementВҰ39919 for them andВҰ39916 to consecrateВҰ39925 them. No one else can eat them, because they've been made sacredВҰ39933.
\v 34 IfВҰ39948 any meat of the consecration or any of the breadВҰ39943 remains untilВҰ39944 the morningВҰ39946, thenВҰ39936 you must burnВҰ39947 the remainderвҖ”it can'tВҰ39952 be eatenВҰ39953 because it's been made sacredВҰ39956.
\p
\v 35 \add SoВҰ39959\add* that's what you must do for AharonВҰ39960 andВҰ39959 his sonsВҰ39961, just like I've commandedВҰ39966 you. You'll consecrate them for sevenВҰ39968 daysВҰ39969,
\v 36 and each day you must sacrifice a bullВҰ39973 to purifyВҰ39980 the altar and compensate for the altar's imperfections. YouВҰ39987 must also anointВҰ39986 it \add each day with olive oil\add* to make it sacred.
\v 37 AfterВҰ39997 making atonementВҰ39992 for the altar and making it sacred for seven daysВҰ39991, it will then be so sacred that anything that touchesВҰ40004 it will also become sacred.
\s1 The daily sacrifices
\rem /s1 The Daily Offerings
\r (Num. 28:1-8)
\p
\v 38 \add After all thatВҰ40010,\add* youВҰ40011 must continuallyВҰ40021 offerВҰ40011 twoВҰ40019, year-old lambsВҰ40015 every dayВҰ40020вҖ”
\v 39 one in the morningВҰ40028 andВҰ40029 the other around twilightВҰ40034.
\v 40 With the \add вүҲmorning\add* lamb, \add also\add* offerВҰ40043 2kg of finely-ground wheat flourВҰ40037 mixedВҰ40038 with a litre of pressedВҰ40040 olive oil andВҰ40043 a litre of wine.
\v 41 With the twilightВҰ40055 lamb, offer the same grainВҰ40056 offering as in the morningВҰ40057, and the same drinkВҰ40058 offering. That will be a fireВҰ40064 offering to \add *me\add* and the aromaВҰ40062 will please me.
\v 42 This must be a continualВҰ40068 offeringВҰ40067 to \add *me\add* at the entranceВҰ40070 of the sacredВҰ40071 tent \add even\add* in following generationsВҰ40069, and I'll meet with you all there to speakВҰ40080 to you there
\v 43 and I'll meet with the IsraelisВҰ40087 thereВҰ40085, and my splendour will sanctify it.
\v 44 I'll consecrate the sacredВҰ40094 tent and the altarВҰ40098, and I'll sanctify AharonВҰ40101 and his sonsВҰ40104 to be my priestsВҰ40106.
\v 45 ThenВҰ40109 I'll live \add there\add* among the IsraelisВҰ40112 andВҰ40113 I will be their godВҰ40115,
\v 46 andВҰ40117 they will knowВҰ40117 that I'm their god Yahweh, who broughtВҰ40123 them out of EgyptВҰ40126 so I could live among them. I am Yahweh their god.
\c 30
\s1 The incense altar
\rem /s1 The Altar for Burning Incense; The Altar of Incense; Plans for the Incense Altar
\r (Exo. 37:25-28)
\p
\v 1 YouВҰ40141 must make an altarВҰ40135 out of acaciaВҰ40139 word for burning incenseВҰ40137 on.
\v 2 It should be squareВҰ40147вҖ”half a metre on each sideвҖ”and a metre highВҰ40150. Make projections that look like hornsВҰ40152 on top out of that same block of wood.
\v 3 It must be overlaidВҰ40154 with pure goldвҖ”its top and all around its sidesВҰ40163 and its projectionsвҖ”plus you shall make a gold mouldingВҰ40170 all around it.
\v 4 MakeВҰ40195 two goldВҰ40176 ringsВҰ40175 andВҰ40174 attach them to the altar below the mouldingВҰ40182вҖ”one on each side to hold the polesВҰ40193 for carryingВҰ40194 it with.
\v 5 Make the two polesВҰ40201 from acaciaВҰ40203 wood andВҰ40204 overlayВҰ40204 them with goldВҰ40206.
\v 6 Put this incense altar outside the curtainВҰ40211 thatВҰ40212 hangs in front of the sacred chestВҰ40215вҖ”the boxВҰ40215 containing the stone slabs andВҰ40208 with a platform on it whereВҰ40223 I will meet with you.
\p
\v 7 AharonВҰ40236 must burn fragrant incenseВҰ40231 on this altar every morning when he looks after the lampsВҰ40238
\v 8 andВҰ40241 again every evening when he \add вүҲlights\add* the lampsВҰ40245, \add so\add* incenseВҰ40249 must be continuallyВҰ40250 burning before \add *me\add* throughoutВҰ40253 your generationsВҰ40253.
\v 9 Don't offer up any incenseВҰ40259 or burntВҰ40261 offering or grainВҰ40262 offering on it that's different from these instructions, and don'tВҰ40264 pour a drinkВҰ40263 offering on it.
\v 10 Once a year, AharonВҰ40269 must take the purifying bloodВҰ40275 from the annual atonement sacrifice andВҰ40268 put it on the projections of the altar to compensate for the altar's imperfection. Each high priest will cover the altar's flaws this way throughoutВҰ40282 all future generationsВҰ40282. \add @The altar\add* will be very sacredВҰ40283вҖ”dedicated to \add *me\add*.
\s1 The tax for making the tent
\rem /s1 The Tax for the Tent of the Lord's Presence; Money for the Tabernacle; The Half Shekel for the Sanctuary; Atonement Money
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ40291 told MoshehВҰ40294:
\v 12 WheneverВҰ40304 youВҰ40298 \add вүҲtake a census of the IsraeliВҰ40302 men\add*, each man must pay a ransomВҰ40309 to YahwehВҰ40311 for his lifeВҰ40310 when they're counted, and then the counting won'tВҰ40314 cause a plagueВҰ40318 among them.
\v 13 As each man crossesВҰ40327 over to stand with those who've been counted, he must pay give a half-shekel coin as an offering to \add *me\add*. (That's half of the official shekel weight of 12 grams.)\x + \xo 30:13: \xt Exo 38:25-26; Mat 17:24.\x*
\v 14 EveryВҰ40354 man who's twentyВҰ40349 or older must pay this contributionВҰ40353 to \add *me\add* when he's countedвҖ”
\v 15 the wealthyВҰ40356 aren'tВҰ40357 expected to pay more, andВҰ40360 the poor must not pass less than this amount when they pay this ransom to \add *me\add* to make atonementВҰ40370 for yourВҰ40373 livesВҰ40373.
\v 16 ThenВҰ40375 you must takeВҰ40375 that moneyВҰ40378 from the IsraelisВҰ40382 andВҰ40375 use it for workВҰ40387 on the sacredВҰ40388 tentвҖ”it will be a reminder to \add *me\add* that you all have made atonement for your livesВҰ40399.
\s1 The washbasin
\rem /s1 Basin for Washing; Plans for the Washbasin; The Bronze Basin
\p
\v 17 The YahwehВҰ40403 told MoshehВҰ40406:
\v 18 Make a bronze washbasin with a bronze base. Place it between the sacredВҰ40419 tent and the altarВҰ40422, and fill it with waterВҰ40425\x + \xo 30:18: \xt Exo 38:8.\x*
\v 19 and AharonВҰ40428 and his sonsВҰ40429 must wash their handsВҰ40433 and feetВҰ40436 in it.
\v 20 BeforeВҰ40456 they goВҰ40438 into the sacredВҰ40441 tent, they must wash with waterВҰ40445 so that won'tВҰ40446 dieВҰ40447, and \add also\add* when they're going to the altarВҰ40452 to burn offeringsВҰ40455 to \add *me\add*вҖ”
\v 21 they must wash their handsВҰ40459 and feetВҰ40460 so they won'tВҰ40461 dieВҰ40462. This will be a rule for them and for all their descendantsВҰ40469 throughoutВҰ40470 the generationsВҰ40470.
\s1 The anointing oil
\rem /s1 The Anointing Oil; The Anointing Oil and Incense; Anointing Oil
\p
\v 22 Then YahwehВҰ40474 told MoshehВҰ40477:\x + \xo 30:22-38: \xt Exo 37:29.\x*
\v 23 ThenВҰ40480 you yourselfВҰ40483 must collect these spicesВҰ40484: 6kg of \add fragrant sap\add* named myrrhВҰ40486, thenВҰ40480 3kg of fragrant cinnamonВҰ40491, 3kg of fragrant cane,
\v 24 andВҰ40508 6kg of fragrant casia bark. (Use the official weight for everything.) Also, four litres of oliveВҰ40509 oil.
\v 25 GetВҰ40513 a professional perfumerВҰ40521 to make this into a sacredВҰ40517, fragrant, anointing oil.
\v 26 Use it to anointВҰ40528 the sacredВҰ40532 tent andВҰ40534 the boxВҰ40535 containing the stone slabs,
\v 27 as well as the tableВҰ40540 and all its utensils, the lampstandВҰ40548 and its utensils, the incenseВҰ40554 altarВҰ40553,
\v 28 the altarВҰ40558 for burntВҰ40559 offeringsВҰ40559 and all its equipment, and the basinВҰ40567 and its base.
\v 29 ThatВҰ40573 will make them sacred and dedicated to me, and anything that touchesВҰ40579 them will also become sacred.
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ40583 anointВҰ40589 AharonВҰ40585 and his sonsВҰ40588, and dedicate them to become my priestsВҰ40592.
\v 31 Approach the IsraelisВҰ40598 andВҰ40595 tell them, вҖңThis \add recipe\add* will be my sacredВҰ40604 anointingВҰ40602 oil for all generationsВҰ40608.
\v 32 It must not be pouredВҰ40615 on anyone's bodyВҰ40612, and you all must not use any similar recipe \add for yourselves\add*вҖ”it's sacredВҰ40620 and \add вүҲmust be treated as such\add*.
\v 33 AnyoneВҰ40626 who mixes together anything like thatВҰ40630, or who puts any of it on a strangerВҰ40635, must be \add вүҲexpelled from the community\add*.
\s1 The incense
\rem /s1 The Incense; Incense
\p
\v 34 Then YahwehВҰ40641 told MoshehВҰ40644: Collect equal amountsВҰ40657 of stacteВҰ40649, onychaВҰ40651, and galbanumВҰ40652 spices, and pure frankincenseВҰ40654,
\v 35 and get a professional ointmentВҰ40663 mixer to add salt and make it into pureВҰ40668 incenseВҰ40662 that will be sacredВҰ40668.
\v 36 Pulverise some of it into a fine powder andВҰ40670 put it in frontВҰ40675 of the box containing the stone slabs inside the sacred tent. This incense must be regarded as being very sacred.
\v 37 NoВҰ40698 one else should make any incenseВҰ40688 for yourselvesВҰ40697 with this same recipeвҖ”itВҰ40696 must be regarded as sacredВҰ40695 to \add *me\add*.
\v 38 AnyoneВҰ40700 who makes anything similar for its fragrance must be \add вүҲexpelled from the community\add*.
\c 31
\s1 Bezalel and Oholiab
\rem /s1 Craftsmen for the Tent of the Lord's Presence; Bezalel and Oholiab; Craftsmen: Bezalel and Oholiab
\r (Exo. 35:30вҖ“36:1)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ40712 told MoshehВҰ40715:
\v 2 Listen, I've chosen a man named BezalelВҰ40721 (son of UriВҰ40724, son of HurВҰ40727, from Yehudah'sВҰ40729 descendants)
\v 3 and I'veВҰ40732 filledВҰ40731 him with \add *my\add* spiritВҰ40733 with wisdomВҰ40735, abilityВҰ40736, knowledgeВҰ40737, and general craftsmanship.
\v 4 \add He's capable of\add* designingВҰ40743 and creating goldВҰ40745, silverВҰ40746, and bronzeВҰ40747 works,
\v 5 as well as cuttingВҰ40749 and settingВҰ40751 gemstones, wood-carving, and other crafts.
\v 6 And what's more, I've appointedВҰ40761 OholiabВҰ40764 (son of AhisamakВҰ40767, from Dan'sВҰ40770 descendants) to help him, andВҰ40759 I've \add also\add* given special ability to other skilledВҰ40774 \add >men\add* so that they can make everythingВҰ40772 that I've instructedВҰ40784 youВҰ40784:
\li1
\v 7 the sacred tent,
\li1 the boxВҰ40792 containing the stone slabs with the atonement platform on top of it,
\li1 all the equipment for inside the sacred tent,
\li1
\v 8 the tableВҰ40807 and its utensils,
\li1 the gold lampstandВҰ40813 and all its utensils,
\li1 the altarВҰ40821 for \add burning\add* incenseВҰ40822,
\li1
\v 9 the altarВҰ40826 for the burntВҰ40827 offeringsВҰ40827 andВҰ40824 all its utensilsВҰ40832,
\li1 the washbasin with its base,
\li1
\v 10 the wovenВҰ40842 clothes: the sacredВҰ40846 clothes for AharonВҰ40847 the priestВҰ40848 andВҰ40840 his sonsВҰ40852,
\li1
\v 11 the anointingВҰ40857 oil, andВҰ40858
\li1 the fragrantВҰ40861 incenseВҰ40860 for the sacredВҰ40862 tentВҰ40862.
\m \add @Those craftsmen\add* must make everything \add exactly\add* accordingВҰ40863 to my instructions.
\s1 The rest day
\rem /s1 Instructions for the Sabbath; The Sabbath; Sabbath, the Day of Rest; The Sabbath Law
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ40871 told MoshehВҰ40874:
\v 13 Tell the IsraelisВҰ40882 that you all must certainly observeВҰ40888 the \add weekly\add* rest day because \add @the rest day\add* is a signВҰ40890 between me andВҰ40893 you all throughoutВҰ40894 yourВҰ40899 generationsВҰ40894, so that you will knowВҰ40895 that I am YahwehВҰ40898, who \add вүҲwants to distinguish you from other nations\add*.
\v 14 \add SoВҰ40901\add* you all must observeВҰ40901 the rest day because it's sacredВҰ40906 for you. Anyone who \add вүҲtreats it as an ordinary day\add* must be put to deathВҰ40911. Anyone who works on it must be \add вүҲexpelled from the community\add*.
\v 15 There's six daysВҰ40925 for working, and then the seventhВҰ40929 is a rest dayвҖ”\add вүҲdedicated\add* to \add *me\add*. Anyone who works on it must certainly be put to deathВҰ40941.\x + \xo 31:15: \xt Exo 20:8-11; 23:12; 34:21; 35:2; Lev 23:3; Deu 5:12-14.\x*
\v 16 The IsraelisВҰ40946 must observeВҰ40943 the rest day for all future generationsВҰ40954. There's no ending to this agreement
\v 17 betweenВҰ40959 me and the IsraelisВҰ40961. It'sВҰ40970 a never-ending signВҰ40962 that \add *I\add* made the heavensВҰ40973 and the earthВҰ40976 in sixВҰ40967 daysВҰ40968, and then restedВҰ40979 on the seventhВҰ40978 dayВҰ40977 and was refreshedВҰ40980.\x + \xo 31:17: \xt Exo 20:11.\x*
\rem /s1 The Two Tablets of the Covenant
\p
\v 18 When \add @Yahweh\add* finishedВҰ40987 speakingВҰ40988 to \add @Mosheh\add*, he gaveВҰ40983 Mosheh the twoВҰ40992 stoneВҰ40996 slabs with the transcriptВҰ40994 that he had engraved on them with his own fingerВҰ40998.
\c 32
\s1 The gold bull idol
\rem /s1 The Gold Bull-Calf; The Golden Calf; The Calf of Gold
\r (Deu. 9:6-29)
\p
\v 1 \add Meanwhile,\add* the people had noticed that Mosheh \add вүҲhad been up on the mountainВҰ41010 for a long time\add*, \add so\add* \add *they\add* gatheredВҰ41011 themselves around AharonВҰ41015 andВҰ41001 told him, вҖңCome on. Make \add +some\add* godsВҰ41023 for us that can go ahead of us, because we don'tВҰ41037 know what's happenedВҰ41041 to that MoshehвҖ”the manВҰ41032\f + \fr 32:1 \ft The way that the people speak of Mosheh here suggests that maybe they never really ever regarded him as being one of themвҖ”remember, he did grow up in an Egyptian palace.\f* who broughtВҰ41034 us out of EgyptВҰ41036.вҖқ\x + \xo 32:1: \xt Acts 7:40.\x*
\p
\v 2 AharonВҰ41046 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңGo and get the goldВҰ41049 earrings off your wivesВҰ41052 and your sonsВҰ41053 and daughtersВҰ41054, and bringВҰ41055 them to me.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ41062\add* the peopleВҰ41061 tookВҰ41058 off all theirВҰ41067 goldВҰ41065 earrings andВҰ41068 broughtВҰ41068 them to AharonВҰ41071,
\v 4 and he tookВҰ41073 them and smelted and crafted the gold into the form of a young bull. ThenВҰ41073 \add @the people\add* saidВҰ41081, вҖңThese are yourВҰ41083 gods,\f + \fr 32:4 \ft After crafting the gold into the form of a young bull (which wasn't necessarily solid but may have had an internal wooden frame or a clay centre), it's not clear here why the text refers to plural вҖҳgodsвҖҷ.\f* YisraelВҰ41084, who broughtВҰ41086 youВҰ41086 out of EgyptВҰ41088.вҖқ\x + \xo 32:4: \xt 1Ki 12:28; Acts 7:41.\x*
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲWhen\add* AharonВҰ41091 sawВҰ41090 \add <that\add*, he builtВҰ41092 an altarВҰ41093 in frontВҰ41094 of the bull andВҰ41090 announced, вҖңTomorrow will be a festivalВҰ41098 to \add honour\add* YahwehВҰ41099.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ41102\add* they got up earlyВҰ41102 the next dayВҰ41103 and offered burntВҰ41105 offerings and brought peaceВҰ41107 offerings. ThenВҰ41102 the peopleВҰ41109 satВҰ41108 down to eatВҰ41110 and drinkВҰ41111, thenВҰ41102 stood up to \add вүҲmake merry\add*.\x + \xo 32:6: \xt 1Cor 10:7.\x*
\p
\v 7 Then YahwehВҰ41117 \add вүҲtold\add* MoshehВҰ41120, вҖңGo on down because yourВҰ41126 peopleВҰ41126 thatВҰ41127 youВҰ41128 broughtВҰ41128 out of EgyptВҰ41130 have gone badвҖ”
\v 8 they've quicklyВҰ41133 deviated from what I instructedВҰ41138 them. They've made a metalВҰ41142 bull for themselves and have bowed down to it and sacrificedВҰ41146 to it and they've saidВҰ41149, вҖҳYisraelВҰ41152, theseВҰ41150 are your godsВҰ41151 thatВҰ41137 broughtВҰ41154 you out of EgyptВҰ41156.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 9 ThenВҰ41158 YahwehВҰ41159 said to MoshehВҰ41162, вҖңI'veВҰ41163 seen this people, andВҰ41158 look, \add вүҲthey're so stubborn\add*.
\v 10 \add SoВҰ41176\add* leaveВҰ41177 me aloneВҰ41177 now and let my angerВҰ41181 rage against them. IВҰ41185 will destroyВҰ41183 them and make youВҰ41185 into a greatВҰ41187 nationВҰ41186.вҖқ
\v 11 ButВҰ41189 MoshehВҰ41190 pleaded with his godВҰ41195 Yahweh and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңYahweh, why \add вүҲare you angry at\add* your peopleВҰ41201 thatВҰ41202 you have broughtВҰ41203 out of EgyptВҰ41205 with \add вүҲyour incredible powerВҰ41206 and actions\add*?\x + \xo 32:11-14: \xt Num 14:13-19.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲIf you did that,\add* the Egyptians would say, вҖҳ\add Ha,\add* he broughtВҰ41216 them out with evil plans to killВҰ41217 them in the mountainsВҰ41219 and to destroy them from \add вүҲoff the earth\add*.вҖҷ Turn from your angerВҰ41226 and repent from \add any idea of doing\add* evil to your peopleВҰ41231.
\v 13 RememberВҰ41233 AbrahamВҰ41234 and Yitshak and Yisra'elвҖ”your servantsВҰ41237 thatВҰ41254 you sworeВҰ41239 to them yourself and told them, вҖҳI will cause your descendants to increaseВҰ41244 like the starsВҰ41248 in the sky, and I will giveВҰ41256 your descendants all this land whichВҰ41254 I told you about, and they will inheritВҰ41258 it forever.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 32:13: \xt Gen 22:16-17; Gen 17:8.\x*
\v 14 \add SoВҰ41261\add* YahwehВҰ41262 repented from the evil thatВҰ41266 he'd said he'd do to his peopleВҰ41269.
\p
\v 15 Then MoshehВҰ41274 turnedВҰ41272 and went down the mountainВҰ41277 carrying the twoВҰ41278 tablets with the transcriptВҰ41280. The tablets were engraved on both sidesВҰ41285вҖ”front and back.
\v 16 \add *They\add* were God's workВҰ41292вҖ”it was \add *his\add* writing andВҰ41291 he had inscribed it on the tablets.
\v 17 \add As theyВҰ41310 descended,\add* Yehoshua heard the sounds of peopleВҰ41309 shoutingВҰ41310 andВҰ41312 saidВҰ41312 to MoshehВҰ41315, вҖң\add вүҲIt sounds like a war going on down there\add* in the camp!вҖқ
\v 18 \add вүҲBut\add* \add @Mosheh\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ41321\add*, вҖңIt's not a victory march, and it's not \add вүҲmoans of defeat\add*вҖ”it's singing that I can hearВҰ41333!вҖқ
\v 19 ThenВҰ41335 as \add #they\add* approached the camp, \add #they\add* sawВҰ41341 the bull and the dancingВҰ41345, and MoshehВҰ41349 \add вүҲgot very angry\add* and threwВҰ41350 the tabletsВҰ41355 \add вүҲdown at the bottom of the mountainВҰ41359 and they shattered\add*.
\v 20 He tookВҰ41361 the bull they had made and burntВҰ41367 it in the fireВҰ41368, thenВҰ41361 he groundВҰ41369 it \add down\add* untilВҰ41370 it was powder and sprinkled it on top of \add pots of\add* waterВҰ41378 and made the IsraelisВҰ41383 drinkВҰ41379 it.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ41385 MoshehВҰ41386 \add вүҲdemanded from\add* AharonВҰ41389, вҖңWhat did \add #these\add* peopleВҰ41394 do to you to make you bring such a terrible sinВҰ41400 on them?вҖқ
\v 22 AharonВҰ41404 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ41403\add*, вҖңDon't \add вүҲbe angry with me\add*, my masterВҰ41409. You knowВҰ41411 the peopleВҰ41414вҖ”\add вүҲthey're intent on\add* evilВҰ41416.
\v 23 They \add вүҲinsisted, saying\add*, вҖҳMake a god for us \add вүҲto lead us\add*. As for that MoshehВҰ41432вҖ”the manВҰ41433 that broughtВҰ41435 us out of EgyptВҰ41437вҖ”weВҰ41439 don'tВҰ41438 knowВҰ41439 what's happenedВҰ41442 to him.вҖҷ
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ41445\add* I \add вүҲtold\add* them, вҖҳAnyone who has goldВҰ41448 \add jewellery\add*, take it off yourselfВҰ41449,вҖҷ and they gaveВҰ41450 it to me and I threwВҰ41453 it into the fireВҰ41454, and this bull came out.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 MoshehВҰ41460 sawВҰ41459 that the peopleВҰ41463 \add вүҲwere out of controlВҰ41469\add* because AharonВҰ41470 had let \add вүҲthem go wild\add*, \add andВҰ41459 now they were subject\add* to mockery \add вүҲfrom any group that stood up\add* against them.
\v 26 ThenВҰ41474 MoshehВҰ41475 stoodВҰ41474 at the camp entranceВҰ41476 andВҰ41474 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңAnyone who's for YahwehВҰ41480, \add вүҲcome\add* to me.вҖқ And all the \add men from the\add* clan of LeviВҰ41487 gatheredВҰ41482 around him.
\v 27 ThenВҰ41489 he \add вүҲtold\add* them, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ41494, the godВҰ41495 of YisraelВҰ41496, saysВҰ41493: вҖҳEach man \add вүҲmust strap\add* his swordВҰ41500 on his side. Pass through and return from gate to gate in the camp and killВҰ41509 \add вүҲthe unfaithful menвҖ”even if it's your\add* brother, or friend, or neighbourВҰ41518.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 28 The Levite men did what MoshehВҰ41529 orderedВҰ41528 andВҰ41530 they killed aboutВҰ41536 threeВҰ41536 thousandВҰ41537 Israeli men that dayВҰ41534.
\v 29 ThenВҰ41540 MoshehВҰ41541 \add вүҲtold\add* \add <them\add*, вҖң\add вүҲConsecrate yourselves to\add* YahwehВҰ41545 today, because any man who \add stood\add* against his son or his brotherВҰ41549 today \add has\add* placed a blessingВҰ41553 on \add #himself\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Moses Intercedes for Israel
\p
\v 30 The next dayВҰ41556, MoshehВҰ41558 \add вүҲtold\add* the peopleВҰ41561, вҖңYou all have committed a terrible sin, \add вүҲbut\add* now I will go up to YahwehВҰ41570вҖ”perhapsВҰ41571 I can atoneВҰ41572 for your sin.вҖқ
\v 31 \add вүҲSoВҰ41576\add* MoshehВҰ41577 returnedВҰ41576 to YahwehВҰ41580 and saidВҰ41581, вҖңPlease, \add #these peopleВҰ41584 have\add* committed a terrible sinВҰ41586 and made godsВҰ41590 for themselves out of goldВҰ41591.
\v 32 \add вүҲButВҰ41593\add* now, \add вүҲmaybe you'll\add* forgiveВҰ41596 theirВҰ41597 sinВҰ41597, but if not, pleaseВҰ41602 blot me out of yourВҰ41603 book thatВҰ41604 you've writtenВҰ41605.вҖқ\x + \xo 32:32: \xt Psa 69:28; Rev 3:5.\x*
\v 33 \add вүҲButВҰ41607\add* YahwehВҰ41608 saidВҰ41607 to MoshehВҰ41611, вҖңIt's anyoneВҰ41613 who sinnedВҰ41614 against me that I'll blot out of my book.
\v 34 \add вүҲSoВҰ41620\add* go now \add andВҰ41620\add* lead the peopleВҰ41626 to whereВҰ41628 I've spokenВҰ41630 to you. See, my angelВҰ41633 will go \add вүҲahead of you, but\add* on the dayВҰ41636 \add вүҲthat I settle accounts\add*, thenВҰ41620 I'll punish them for theirВҰ41640 sinВҰ41640.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ41642 YahwehВҰ41643 sentВҰ41642 a plagueВҰ41642 on the peopleВҰ41646 because theyВҰ41649 had got AharonВҰ41655 to make the \add gold\add* bull.
\c 33
\s1 God tells them to leave Mt. Sinai
\rem /s1 The Command to Leave Sinai; The Lord Orders Israel to Leave Mount Sinai
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ41659 \add вүҲtold\add* MoshehВҰ41662, вҖңGo \add and\add* pack up from here, you and the peopleВҰ41667 that you broughtВҰ41669 out of EgyptВҰ41671. Go to the land which I promised to AbrahamВҰ41677, to Yitshak, and to YacobВҰ41679, \add вүҲwhen I told them that\add* I'd giveВҰ41682 it to \add вүҲtheir descendantsВҰ41681\add*.\x + \xo 33:1: a \xt Gen 12:7; \xo b \xt Gen 26:3; \xo c \xt Gen 28:13.\x*
\v 2 I'll sendВҰ41684 an angelВҰ41686 \add вүҲahead of you\add*, and I'll driveВҰ41687 out the CanaanitesВҰ41690, the AmoritesВҰ41691, the HittitesВҰ41692, the PerizzitesВҰ41693, the HivitesВҰ41694, and the Yebusites.
\v 3 \add It's\add* a land flowingВҰ41700 with milk and honeyВҰ41702, but I won'tВҰ41704 \add вүҲstay among you\add* in case I \add decide to\add* destroyВҰ41716 you on the wayВҰ41717 because you're \add вүҲstubborn\add* peopleВҰ41708.вҖқ\x + \xo 33:3 \xt 32:9.\x*
\p
\v 4 \add WhenВҰ41721\add* the peopleВҰ41720 heard this \add вүҲangry comment\add*, they mournedВҰ41726 and none of them put on \add вүҲanything fancy\add*.\f + \fr 33:4 \ft But they didn't mourn enough to wear sackcloth and throw ashes on themselves.\f*
\v 5 YahwehВҰ41735 \add had\add*\f + \fr 33:5 \ft Assumed.\f* \add вүҲtold\add* MoshehВҰ41738, вҖңTell the IsraelisВҰ41744, вҖҳYou're all \add вүҲstubborn\add* people. If I went with you for \add even\add* one momentВҰ41751, then I'd destroyВҰ41755 you. \add вүҲSoВҰ41734\add* now, take off yourВҰ41754 \add вүҲjewellery and anything fancy that you're wearing\add*, and then I'll know what I'll do to you.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ41766\add* from Mt. Sinai \add onwards\add*, the IsraelisВҰ41769 strippedВҰ41766 themselves of theirВҰ41772 \add вүҲjewellery andВҰ41766 fancy things\add*.
\s1 The tent for meeting God
\rem /s1 The Tent of Meeting; The Tent of the Lord's Presence; The Tent outside the Camp
\p
\v 7 \add FromВҰ41778 that day onwards,\add* MoshehВҰ41776 would take a tent andВҰ41776 would put it up at a distanceВҰ41787 outside the campвҖ”he calledВҰ41791 it вҖҳthe tent of meetingвҖҷ. ThenВҰ41776 anyoneВҰ41798 \add вүҲwho wanted a decision from\add* YahwehВҰ41799 would go out to that tent of meeting outside the camp.
\v 8 Whenever Mosheh went out to the tent, all the peopleВҰ41818 would standВҰ41819 up at the entrance of their own tents, andВҰ41809 they would watchВҰ41823 Mosheh go out untilВҰ41826 he went into the tent.
\v 9 Once \add *he\add* enteredВҰ41832 the tent, the pillarВҰ41836 of cloudВҰ41837 would come down and standВҰ41838 at the entrance of the tent, and \add @Yahweh\add* would speakВҰ41841 with \add *him\add*.
\v 10 \add WhenВҰ41850\add* all the people saw the pillarВҰ41852 of cloudВҰ41853 standingВҰ41854 at the entrance of the tent, \add *they\add* would get up andВҰ41846 bow down at the entrance of \add #their\add* \add own\add* \add #tents\add*.
\v 11 YahwehВҰ41868 would speak to Mosheh face to face like someone speaks to \add #their\add* friend. ThenВҰ41867 Mosheh would returnВҰ41882 to the camp, but his servant Yehoshua (a youngВҰ41891 man who was the son of NunВҰ41890) would not leave the insideВҰ41894 of the tent.
\s1 Mosheh sees the master's splendour
\rem /s1 Moses and the Glory of the Lord; Moses Sees the Lord's Glory; The Lord Promises to Be with His People; Moses' Intercession
\p
\v 12 Then MoshehВҰ41899 said to YahwehВҰ41902, вҖңListen, you've been sayingВҰ41905 to me, вҖҳTake \add #these\add* peopleВҰ41910 \add вүҲonwards\add*,вҖҷ but you haven't let me know who you'll send with me, although you have said, вҖҳI know you by nameВҰ41923, and you've also foundВҰ41926 favourВҰ41927 in my \add вүҲsightВҰ41928\add*.вҖҷ
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ41930\add* now please, if I've foundВҰ41934 favour in your \add вүҲsight\add*, please \add вүҲhelp\add* me to know your waysВҰ41941. ThenВҰ41930 I'll know you so that I can find favour in your \add вүҲsight\add*. And \add don't forget\add* that this nationВҰ41951 is \em your\em* peopleВҰ41950.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add @Yahweh\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңMy \add вүҲpresenceВҰ41955\add* will goВҰ41956 \add with you\add* andВҰ41957 I will \add вүҲhelp\add* you \add to be able to\add* rest.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add @Mosheh\add* \add вүҲreplied\add* to him, вҖңIf yourВҰ41965 \add вүҲpresenceВҰ41965\add* isn'tВҰ41964 \add вүҲcoming with us\add*, thenВҰ41960 don'tВҰ41964 \add вүҲmake us leave\add* here.
\v 16 \add вүҲHow would anyone know\add* that I've foundВҰ41978 favourВҰ41979 in your \add вүҲsightВҰ41980\add*вҖ”me and your people \add that is\add*вҖ”if you didn'tВҰ41983 \add вүҲcome\add* with us? \add вүҲHow could\add* I and your people be distinguishedВҰ41986 from all the \add other\add* people \add groups\add* \add вүҲin the world\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 17 YahwehВҰ42001 \add вүҲreplied\add* to MoshehВҰ42004, вҖң\add Okay,\add* I'll also do \add вүҲwhat you've asked\add* because you've foundВҰ42015 favourВҰ42016 in my \add вүҲsightВҰ42017\add* and I knowВҰ42018 you by nameВҰ42019.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ42021 \add @Mosheh\add*, вҖңPleaseВҰ42024 show me yourВҰ42026 splendour.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 Yahweh \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI myself will causeВҰ42030 all my goodnessВҰ42033 to passВҰ42030 over \add вүҲin front of you\add*, and I will \add вүҲsay\add* \add *my\add* nameВҰ42038 of Yahweh \add вүҲin front of you\add*. I will favourВҰ42045 \add вүҲanyone I want\add*, and I'll be compassionate to \add вүҲwhoever I want\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 33:19: \xt Rom 9:15.\x*
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ42052\add* he saidВҰ42052, вҖңYouВҰ42056 won'tВҰ42053 be able to see my faceВҰ42058, because no humanВҰ42063 can see me andВҰ42052 \add still\add* liveВҰ42064.вҖқ
\v 21 \add *He\add* \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ42066\add*, вҖңLookВҰ42067, there's a placeВҰ42069 near me where you can \add вүҲstandВҰ42071 there\add* on the rockВҰ42074.
\v 22 ThenВҰ42076 while my splendour passesВҰ42077 over, I'll put you in a crevice in the rockВҰ42081, andВҰ42076 my handВҰ42083 will coverВҰ42082 you untilВҰ42085 I've gone past.
\v 23 ThenВҰ42089 I'll take my handВҰ42092 away andВҰ42089 you'll be able to seeВҰ42093 my back, but \add вүҲyou mustn't try to look at\add* my faceВҰ42097.вҖқ
\c 34
\s1 The replacement stone slabs
\rem /s1 A New Copy of the Covenant; The Second Set of Stone Tablets; The New Stone Tablets; Moses Makes New Tablets
\r (Deu. 10:1-5)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ42103 \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ42102\add* speaking to MoshehВҰ42106, вҖңCarve twoВҰ42110 slabs of stoneВҰ42113 for yourselfВҰ42109 just like the first \add >ones\add*. Then the wordsВҰ42121 that were on the first tablets that youВҰ42129 brokeВҰ42129, I'll writeВҰ42115 them \add again\add* on the slabs.
\v 2 Be ready by morning, and in the morning comeВҰ42134 up to MtВҰ42138. SinaiВҰ42139, and presentВҰ42140 yourself thereВҰ42142 to me up on the top.
\v 3 Don't bring anyone with youВҰ42152, and also don't let anyone be on the mountain at allвҖ”don't even let their flocksВҰ42164 and herdsВҰ42165 grazeВҰ42168 \add вүҲat the base\add* of that mountain.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ42175\add* \add @Mosheh\add* carved out two slabs of stone like the firstВҰ42180 \add >ones\add*, and \add *he\add* got up earlyВҰ42181 in the morningВҰ42183 and went up to MtВҰ42182. SinaiВҰ42188 as YahwehВҰ42191 had commandedВҰ42190 him, carrying up the two slabs of stone.
\v 5 ThenВҰ42199 Yahweh came down in the cloudВҰ42201 and stoodВҰ42202 with him thereВҰ42204, and he pronounced \add вүҲhis\add* nameВҰ42206 вҖҳYahwehвҖҷ.
\v 6 Yahweh passedВҰ42209 over above his face and proclaimed, вҖңI am Yahweh, a compassionateВҰ42220 and graciousВҰ42221 GodВҰ42219, \add вүҲslow to get angry but exuding\add* faithfulnessВҰ42227 and trustworthiness.\x + \xo 34:6-7: \xt Exo 20:5-6; Num 14:18; Deu 5:9-10; 7:9-10.\x*
\v 7 \add I\add* display faithfulness to thousandsВҰ42232 \add ?of generations\add*вҖ”forgivingВҰ42233 disobedience, transgressionВҰ42235, and sin. But \add вүҲI\add* certainly won'tВҰ42238 let the guilty \add вүҲget away with it\add*вҖ”visitingВҰ42240 the iniquity of the \add вүҲparentsВҰ42243\add* onto the \add вүҲchildren\add* and onto the \add вүҲgrandchildren\add*вҖ”to the thirdВҰ42253 and the fourthВҰ42256 \add generations\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 MoshehВҰ42259 hurried and bowedВҰ42260 to the ground and worshippedВҰ42262 \add <Yahweh\add*
\v 9 and said, вҖңPlease, if I have foundВҰ42268 favourВҰ42269 in your \add вүҲsightВҰ42270\add*, my master, please go with us, because \add #these\add* are \add вүҲstubborn\add* peopleВҰ42278. And forgiveВҰ42284 our disobedience and our sin and \add вүҲtake us as your inheritance\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Covenant Is Renewed; The Covenant Renewed
\rem /r (Exodus 23.14-19; Deuteronomy 7.1-5; 16.1-17)
\p
\v 10 \add @Yahweh\add* said, вҖңListen, I'm about to make an agreement in front of all your people.\f + \fr 34:10 \ft Because there's no punctuation in the original Hebrew, it's not certain if вҖҳin front of all your peopleвҖҷ goes with what it follows (as the \em OET-RV\em* has chosen), or with what follows it (as in several other translations).\f* I will do miracles that have not been \add вүҲdone beforeВҰ42294\add* anywhere on the earthВҰ42306 or in any country \add of the world\add*. All the people that you're among will see \add *my\add* work, because what I'm going to do with you is \add вүҲawe-inspiring\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲBe sure to obey\add* what I'm telling you today. See, I'm aboutВҰ42340 to force the AmoritesВҰ42344, the CanaanitesВҰ42345, the HittitesВҰ42346, the PerizzitesВҰ42347, the HivitesВҰ42348, and the Yebusites out of the land ahead of you.
\v 12 \add вүҲBe very careful\add* not to make any treaties with any of the \add current\add* inhabitantsВҰ42357 of the land thatВҰ42359 you'reВҰ42360 aboutВҰ42361 to enter, in case it ends up trapping you.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhat you must do instead is to\add* break down their altarsВҰ42372 and smashВҰ42377 their pillarsВҰ42376, and cut down the polesВҰ42380 \add used to worship their god\add* Asherah.\x + \xo 34:13: \xt Deu 16:21.\x*
\v 14 You must not bow down to any other god because YahwehВҰ42389 is a jealous GodВҰ42386вҖ”jealous \add to protect\add* his name.
\v 15 So don't make an agreement with the \add #inhabitants\add* of the land, \add because when\add* they prostituteВҰ42402 \add <themselves\add* to their gods and sacrifice to \add *them\add*, and then \add #they\add* inviteВҰ42408 you \add to join them\add* and you eat some of \add #their\add* sacrifice,
\v 16 then \add you'll end up by\add* allowing your sons to marry their daughters who'll prostitute \add <themselves\add* to their gods, andВҰ42413 then your sons \add вүҲwill do the same\add*.
\p
\v 17 Don't make cast metalВҰ42428 godsВҰ42427 for yourselvesВҰ42432.\x + \xo 34:17: \xt Exo 20:4; Lev 19:4; Deu 5:8; 27:15.\x*
\p
\v 18 You must observe the Flat Bread Celebration \add every year\add* as I instructedВҰ42444 you. For sevenВҰ42439 daysВҰ42440 you must eatВҰ42441 \add only\add* breadВҰ42437 that hasn't been risen, at the appointedВҰ42445 timeВҰ42445 in late March or early April because that's when you cameВҰ42451 out of EgyptВҰ42452.\x + \xo 34:18: \xt Exo 12:14-20; Lev 23:6-8; Num 28:16-25.\x*
\v 19 All of your eldest male offspring belong to me, \add including your sons\add* and the first males born from your cattle and sheepВҰ42465 and goats.\x + \xo 34:19: \xt Exo 13:2.\x*
\v 20 If it's a male donkey, a lamb can be given as a ransom instead, but if you don'tВҰ42473 pay a ransom thenВҰ42467 you must kill the donkey. \add вүҲIt's compulsory to\add* ransom your eldest sons. \add вүҲDon't come to worship me without bringing something\add*.\x + \xo 34:20: \xt Exo 13:13.\x*
\p
\v 21 \add Each week,\add* you should only work for six daysВҰ42487, then you must rest on the seventhВҰ42490 dayВҰ42489вҖ”\add even\add* during ploughing and harvestВҰ42493 times.\x + \xo 34:21: \xt Exo 20:9-10; 23:12; 31:15; 35:2; Lev 23:3; Deu 5:13-14.\x*
\p
\v 22 \add In the spring\add* when you begin to harvestВҰ42501 the firstВҰ42500 wheatВҰ42502 crop, you must have a \it Celebration of Weeks\it*, andВҰ42496 at the end of the yearВҰ42506 \add in the autumn\add*, have a \it \add Finished\add* Harvest Celebration\it*.\x + \xo 34:22: a \xt Exo 23:16; Lev 23:15-21; Num 28:26-31; \xo b \xt Lev 23:39-43.\x*
\p
\v 23 ThreeВҰ42508 timesВҰ42509 everyВҰ42512 yearВҰ42510, all yourВҰ42514 men must presentВҰ42511 themselves before meвҖ”Isra'el'sВҰ42522 godВҰ42521, the masterВҰ42518 YahwehВҰ42520.
\v 24 I will drive out the people groups ahead of you and expand your borders, and no one will \add вүҲthink of taking\add* your land \add when they know that\add* you presentВҰ42544 yourselves to \add *me\add* threeВҰ42547 timesВҰ42548 a yearВҰ42549.
\p
\v 25 Don't \add wave bread\add* \add вүҲthat's been risen\add* when offering a sacrifice. Don't allow any part of the sacrifice for the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration to \add вүҲstill be there in\add* the morningВҰ42563.\x + \xo 34:25: \xt Exo 12:10.\x*
\p
\v 26 You must bringВҰ42571 the best of the firstВҰ42568 parts of your harvests to \add *my\add* residence.\x + \xo 34:26: a \xt Deu 26:2; \xo b \xt Deu 14:21.\x*
\p Don't boil a young goat in its mother'sВҰ42580 milk.
\p
\v 27 YahwehВҰ42584 \add вүҲtold\add* MoshehВҰ42587, вҖңWrite down these words for yourselfВҰ42590, because \add вүҲit's in accordance with\add* these words that I've made an agreement with youВҰ42603 and with YisraelВҰ42607.вҖқ
\v 28 \add @Mosheh\add* was thereВҰ42611 with YahwehВҰ42614 for forty days and nightsВҰ42618, and \add during that time\add* he didn'tВҰ42620 eat or \add even\add* drink waterВҰ42622, and he wroteВҰ42625 the tenВҰ42632 commandsВҰ42633 of the agreement on the \add stone\add* slabs.
\rem /s1 The Shining Face of Moses; Moses Goes Down from Mount Sinai; The Radiant Face of Moses
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ42635 when\add* Mosheh came down from MtВҰ42649. SinaiВҰ42639, he was carrying the two \add stone\add* slabs with the transcriptВҰ42642 \add of the ten commands\add*, \add вүҲbut\add* what he didn'tВҰ42651 know as he descended was that the skin on his face was shining after his talkingВҰ42658 with \add @Yahweh\add*.\x + \xo 34:29-35: \xt 2Cor 3:7-16.\x*
\v 30 \add вүҲWhenВҰ42667\add* AharonВҰ42662 and the IsraelisВҰ42666 sawВҰ42661 MoshehВҰ42669, wow, \add вүҲhis face radiated light\add* and they were afraidВҰ42674 to go close to him.
\v 31 \add вүҲButВҰ42678\add* Mosheh calledВҰ42678 them \add over\add*, and AharonВҰ42683 and all of the communityВҰ42687 leadersВҰ42686 returnedВҰ42681 back to him, and \add *he\add* spokeВҰ42688 with them.
\v 32 After that, the IsraelisВҰ42699 came closer, andВҰ42700 \add @Mosheh\add* gave them all the instructions that YahwehВҰ42706 had told him on Mt. SinaiВҰ42709.
\v 33 \add вүҲThenВҰ42712 when\add* \add *he'd\add* finished talkingВҰ42713 to them, \add @Mosheh\add* put a veil over his face,
\v 34 andВҰ42721 whenever \add *he\add* would go in to speakВҰ42725 with YahwehВҰ42724, he would removeВҰ42727 the veil untilВҰ42731 he came out. \add вүҲWheneverВҰ42722\add* he did come out, he'd tell the IsraelisВҰ42739 what he'd been instructedВҰ42742,
\v 35 andВҰ42744 \add *they\add* would see how \add *his\add* face shoneВҰ42753. ThenВҰ42744 Mosheh would put the veil back over his face untilВҰ42765 he went in \add the next time\add* to speakВҰ42768 with \add @Yahweh\add*.
\c 35
\s1 Instructions for the rest day
\rem /s1 Regulations for the Sabbath; Sabbath Regulations; Instructions for the Sabbath
\p
\v 1 MoshehВҰ42773 assembledВҰ42772 all the IsraelisВҰ42780 and told them, вҖңThese are the thingsВҰ42784 thatВҰ42785 YahwehВҰ42788 has instructedВҰ42787 you to do.
\v 2 \add Every week\add*, you can work for six daysВҰ42793, but the seventhВҰ42797 day will be a sacredВҰ42800 rest day, \add dedicated to\add* YahwehВҰ42803. Anyone who works on that day must be put to deathВҰ42809.\x + \xo 35:2: \xt Exo 20:8-11; 23:12; 31:15; 34:21; Lev 23:3; Deu 5:12-14.\x*
\v 3 Don't light a fireВҰ42814\f + \fr 35:3 \ft This is effectively a command not to do any \bd cooking\bd* on the rest day.\f* in any of yourВҰ42816 homes on the rest days.вҖқ
\s1 The offering for Yahweh
\rem /s1 Preparations for Making the Tabernacle; Offerings for the Sacred Tent; Materials for the Tabernacle; Gifts for the Tabernacle
\r (Exo. 25:1-9)
\p
\v 4 Then MoshehВҰ42822 told all the assembled IsraelisВҰ42830, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ42837 instructedВҰ42836:
\v 5 Take up an offering for YahwehвҖ”everyoneВҰ42844 \add вүҲwho wants to participate should\add* bringВҰ42847 to Yahweh their contribution of goldВҰ42851, silverВҰ42852, bronzeВҰ42853,
\v 6 blue, purpleВҰ42856, or scarlet yarn, finely-spun linenВҰ42859 andВҰ42855 goats' hair,
\v 7 reddened ram skinsВҰ42862, sea-cow hides, andВҰ42862 acaciaВҰ42868 wood,
\v 8 \add olive\add* oil for the lamps and spicesВҰ42873 to make the anointingВҰ42875 oil and the fragrantВҰ42877 incenseВҰ42876,
\v 9 and onyx and other gemstones for the \add priest's\add* sacred apron and chest pouch.
\s1 The equipment for the holy tent
\rem /s1 Articles for the Tent of the Lord's Presence
\r (Exo. 39:32-43)
\p
\v 10 EveryoneВҰ42895 among youВҰ42892 all who's \add вүҲhighly skilledВҰ42889\add* shouldВҰ42893 comeВҰ42893 andВҰ42894 make everything that YahwehВҰ42900 has instructedВҰ42899вҖ”
\v 11 the tentВҰ42904 for the residence and its coveringВҰ42910, its claspsВҰ42913 and framesВҰ42916, its bars, pillarsВҰ42923, and basesВҰ42926,
\v 12 the boxВҰ42930 with itsВҰ42933 polesВҰ42933 and the atonement platform \add to go on top\add*, the curtainВҰ42938 for screeningВҰ42939 \add <it\add*,
\v 13 the tableВҰ42943 and its polesВҰ42946 and all its utensilsВҰ42951 and the sacred breadВҰ42953,
\v 14 the lampstand for light with its lamps and utensilsВҰ42962 and oil \add вүҲto burn\add*,
\v 15 the incense altarВҰ42972 and itsВҰ42976 polesВҰ42976, the anointingВҰ42979 oil and fragrantВҰ42982 incense, the curtain for the entrance of the residence,
\v 16 the altarВҰ42992 for the burntВҰ42993 offeringsВҰ42993 with its bronzeВҰ42997 grate, its polesВҰ43003 and all of its utensilsВҰ43008, the washbasin with its base,
\v 17 the courtyard curtains with their pillarsВҰ43021 and basesВҰ43024, and the curtain for the courtyard gate,
\v 18 the tentВҰ43033 pegs and ropesВҰ43040 for the residence and the courtyardВҰ43037,
\v 19 the finely-woven clothing for serving in the Holy Place, the sacredВҰ43051 clothes for AharonВҰ43052 the priest, andВҰ43054 the clothes for his sonsВҰ43057 to serveВҰ43058 as priestsВҰ43058.вҖқ
\s1 The people's offerings
\rem /s1 The People Bring Their Offerings; Offerings for the Tabernacle
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ43060 all the IsraelisВҰ43066 who'd been assembled in front of MoshehВҰ43068 wentВҰ43060 away,
\v 21 and everyoneВҰ43071 who \add вүҲfelt to do so\add* cameВҰ43070 \add back\add* bringing their contributionsВҰ43086 to YahwehВҰ43087 for the workВҰ43093 on the sacred tent and all its components, and for the sacred clothes.
\v 22 This included both men and womenВҰ43101 who were \add вүҲwanting to contribute\add*, and they broughtВҰ43106 necklaces and earringsВҰ43108 and ornamentsВҰ43110вҖ”all made of gold. They held them up high as a raised offering of gold to YahwehВҰ43122.
\v 23 \add вүҲMany people\add* who had blue or purpleВҰ43132 or scarlet yarn, or finely-spun linenВҰ43135 or goats' hair, reddened ram skinsВҰ43137 or sea-cow hides broughtВҰ43142 \add <them\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲOthersВҰ43151 who could,\add* brought a contributionВҰ43146 of silverВҰ43148 or bronzeВҰ43149 to YahwehВҰ43153, and thoseВҰ43146 with acaciaВҰ43159 wood brought \add <it\add* for all the \add вүҲconstruction of the tent components\add*.
\v 25 All the women who were \add вүҲskilledВҰ43169 at making cloth\add* broughtВҰ43174 blue, purpleВҰ43181, or scarletВҰ43184 yarn andВҰ43166 fine, hand-spun linenВҰ43188 thread,
\v 26 andВҰ43190 all those womenВҰ43192 who \add вүҲfelt to do so\add* spun goats' hair.
\v 27 The leadersВҰ43203 broughtВҰ43204 onyx stones and other gemstones to be mounted on the sacred apron and for the sacred pouch,
\v 28 along with the spicesВҰ43216 and \add olive\add* oil to be used for the maps, the anointingВҰ43222 oil, and the fragrantВҰ43224 incenseВҰ43223.
\v 29 \add Thus\add* the IsraelisВҰ43248 brought a voluntary offeringВҰ43249 to YahwehвҖ”every manВҰ43228 and woman who \add вүҲfelt to do so\add* brought something for all the work whichВҰ43238 Yahweh had instructedВҰ43239 them through MoshehВҰ43244 to do.
\s1 The skills of Bezalel and Oholiab
\rem /s1 Bezalel and Oholiab; Workers to Make the Tent of the Lord's Presence
\r (Exo. 31:1-11)
\p
\v 30 Then MoshehВҰ43254 saidВҰ43253 to the IsraelisВҰ43258, вҖңListen, YahwehВҰ43261 has calledВҰ43260 BezalelВҰ43263 by nameВҰ43262 (the son of Hur'sВҰ43269 son UriВҰ43266, from the tribeВҰ43270 of Judah)
\v 31 and he has filledВҰ43273 him with \add *his\add* spiritВҰ43275, with skill and understanding, and with knowledgeВҰ43279 and with all kinds of craftsmanship.
\v 32 \add He can\add* design designs, workВҰ43286 in goldВҰ43287, silverВҰ43288, andВҰ43284 bronzeВҰ43289,
\v 33 in cuttingВҰ43291 gemstones for settingВҰ43293, and in wood-carvingвҖ”to do all kinds of designВҰ43300 and crafting.
\v 34 \add @Yahweh\add* has also \add вүҲgiven him the desire\add* to teachВҰ43302, along with OholiabВҰ43306 (Ahisamak'sВҰ43309 son from the tribeВҰ43310 of DanВҰ43312).
\v 35 He'sВҰ43315 given them \add both\add* skills to do all the workВҰ43322 of craftsmen and of skillful workmenВҰ43336 and of embroiderersВҰ43326 in blue, purpleВҰ43328, and scarletВҰ43329 yarn, and in the fine linenВҰ43331 and of weaversВҰ43332вҖ”\add both\add* as designersВҰ43338 as well as the various, actual crafts.
\c 36
\nb
\v 1 BezalelВҰ43341 and OholiabВҰ43368 will do the workВҰ43362 of constructing all the components of the sacredВҰ43363 tentВҰ43363 along with any others who are \add вүҲlike-minded\add* and who have been given the necessary skillsВҰ43346 and understandingВҰ43353 by YahwehВҰ43351.вҖқ
\s1 More than enough materials donated
\rem /s1 The People Bring Many Gifts
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ43370\add* MoshehВҰ43371 summoned BezalelВҰ43374 and OholiabВҰ43400, as well as anyone else \add вүҲwho felt to help\add* and had been given the \add appropriate\add* skillsВҰ43383 by YahwehВҰ43388,
\v 3 andВҰ43402 they took \add away\add* all the contributionsВҰ43408 thatВҰ43409 the IsraelisВҰ43412 had brought to MoshehВҰ43404 to be used for the construction of the sacredВҰ43415 tentВҰ43415. \add вүҲHowever\add* \add @the peopleВҰ43411\add* \add stillВҰ43421\add* continued to bring voluntary offeringsВҰ43422 every morning.
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ43426\add* all those skilled \add people\add* came \add over\add* to \add start on\add* the work of \add making\add* the sacredВҰ43435 tentВҰ43435, Holy Place came, \add вүҲleaving behind\add* the work thatВҰ43440 they had been doing,
\v 5 andВҰ43445 theyВҰ43445 \add вүҲinformed\add* MoshehВҰ43448, вҖңTheВҰ43461 peopleВҰ43451 are bringingВҰ43452 way more than enough to use for the workВҰ43455 thatВҰ43456 YahwehВҰ43459 has instructedВҰ43458 us to do.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* with Mosheh'sВҰ43464 \add вүҲagreement\add*, they spread a message around the camp saying, вҖң\add вүҲPlease don'tВҰ43471 bring\add* any more contributions for the sacredВҰ43478 tentВҰ43478.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* the peopleВҰ43480вҖ”men andВҰ43463 womenвҖ”stopped bringingВҰ43481 \add <donations\add*
\v 7 as \add theyВҰ43485 had already collected\add* more than enoughВҰ43491 materialsВҰ43483 for all the workВҰ43488.
\s1 The construction of the tent
\rem /s1 Making the Tent of the Lord's Presence; Building the Tabernacle; Construction of the Tabernacle; The Tabernacle
\r (Exo. 26:1-37)
\p
\v 8 Then all the \add вүҲmost-skilled men\add* out of the workmen made the tenВҰ43505 \add strips of\add* curtainingВҰ43506 for the residence from twistedВҰ43508 finely-spun linenВҰ43507 and blue, purpleВҰ43510, scarlet yarn \add used to embroider\add* winged-creatures on them.
\v 9 Each \add вүҲstrip\add* was 14.5m long and two metresВҰ43524 wideвҖ”they were all the same size.
\v 10 FiveВҰ43537 \add вүҲstrips\add* were sewn together as one set, andВҰ43536 the other five as another set.
\v 11 \add #They\add*\f + \fr 36:11 \ft It's singular вҖҳheвҖҷ in the original, which is confusing after v8 mentioned a group of craftsmen. The \em OET-RV\em* has chosen to follow v8 (and change the pronoun to вҖҳtheyвҖҷ in this section), but other translations are divided in how they handle this dilemma.\f* made loopsВҰ43554 of blue on the edge of the firstВҰ43559 curtain at the edge of the set, and similarly for the secondВҰ43568 setвҖ”
\v 12 fiftyВҰ43575 \add matching\add* loops on the edge of each set so they were aligned with each other.
\v 13 \add #They\add* \add also\add* made fiftyВҰ43591 goldВҰ43593 clips andВҰ43590 used them to join the \add two\add* curtainВҰ43597 \add sets\add* to each other to make \add the wall of\add* the sacredВҰ43604 tentВҰ43604.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ43620 \add #they\add* made eleven goats' hairВҰ43610 curtain sections for the tarpaulin over the sacredВҰ43614 tentВҰ43614.
\v 15 All eleven \add вүҲsections\add* were the same size at fifteen metres long andВҰ43627 two metres wide,
\v 16 and they joinedВҰ43638 fiveВҰ43641 \add вүҲsections\add* to each other \add for one set\add* and sixВҰ43646 for the other.
\v 17 ThenВҰ43650 \add #they\add* \add вүҲattached\add* fifty \add blue\add* loops onto one edge of each of the two sets
\v 18 andВҰ43668 made fiftyВҰ43671 bronzeВҰ43670 clips for connecting them into one \add continuous\add* cover.
\v 19 \add #They\add* thenВҰ43679 made a tarpaulin from red rams skinsВҰ43686 to go over the tent, andВҰ43685 the top \add waterproof\add* tarpaulin of sea-cow hidesВҰ43682.
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ43692 \add #they\add* made \add forty-eight\add* uprightВҰ43698 framesВҰ43694 from acaciaВҰ43697 wood for the sacredВҰ43695 tentВҰ43695.
\v 21 Each frame was five metresВҰ43701 long and 0.75m wide
\v 22 with two protrusions on each frame for connecting them together, so all the frames were made in this way.
\v 23 \add #They\add* made twentyВҰ43731 frames for the southВҰ43734 side
\v 24 with their fortyВҰ43737 silverВҰ43740 basesвҖ”two bases under each frameВҰ43744 that two \add more\add* protrusions fitted \add down\add* into,
\v 25 thenВҰ43762 two \add more\add* for the northВҰ43766 side
\v 26 with theirВҰ43772 fortyВҰ43771 silverВҰ43773 basesвҖ”two bases under each frame.
\v 27 Six framesВҰ43790 were made for the west side
\v 28 as well as twoВҰ43792 framesВҰ43793 for the back cornersВҰ43795 of the sacredВҰ43796 tentВҰ43796.
\v 29 At the twoВҰ43815 cornersВҰ43816, \add @the frames\add* were connected together at the bottomВҰ43801, andВҰ43802 \add similarly\add* at the top before being attached to a single ring
\v 30 \add вүҲso\add* that made eightВҰ43819 frames with theirВҰ43821 sixteen silverВҰ43822 basesвҖ”two bases underВҰ43830 each frame.
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ43834 \add #they\add* made crossbars from acaciaВҰ43837 woodвҖ”fiveВҰ43838 for the framesВҰ43839 on the \add north\add* side of the sacredВҰ43842 tentВҰ43842,
\v 32 five for the \add вүҲsouth\add* side, andВҰ43845 five crossbars for the frames on the west \add side\add* along the back.
\v 33 TheВҰ43860 middle crossbar was made to pass throughВҰ43864 from \add one\add* end to \add вүҲthe other\add* in the centre of the framesВҰ43866,
\v 34 and the framesВҰ43876 were overlaid with gold. \add #They\add* thenВҰ43874 made gold ringsВҰ43881 to be the holdersВҰ43884 for the crossbars, and \add *they\add* \add too\add* were overlaid with gold.
\p
\v 35 \add #They\add* made a curtainВҰ43895 from twistedВҰ43901 finely-spun linenВҰ43900, andВҰ43892 a skillfulВҰ43903 workman embroidered winged creatures on them with blue, purpleВҰ43897, scarlet yarn.
\v 36 \add #They\add* made four pillarsВҰ43911 of acaciaВҰ43912 wood overlaidВҰ43913 with gold, as well as theirВҰ43915 gold hooksВҰ43915 andВҰ43908 four basesВҰ43920 cast from silverВҰ43922.
\v 37 \add #They\add* made a curtain for the tent entranceВҰ43926вҖ”an embroiderer made it from twistedВҰ43933 finely-spun linenВҰ43932 and blue, purpleВҰ43929, and scarlet yarn,
\v 38 along with it's five pillarsВҰ43939 and their hooksВҰ43943. The tops of the pillars were overlaidВҰ43944 with goldВҰ43947, and their five basesВҰ43948 \add were made of\add* bronzeВҰ43950.
\c 37
\s1 Making the sacred box
\rem /s1 Making the Covenant Box; Making the Ark of the Covenant; The Ark; Building the Ark
\r (Exo. 25:10-22)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ43955 BezalelВҰ43954 made the sacred chestВҰ43957 from acaciaВҰ43959 woodвҖ”it was 1.2m longВҰ43962, 0.75m wideВҰ43965, and 0.75m highВҰ43968.
\v 2 He overlaidВҰ43970 \add both\add* the insideВҰ43973 and the outsideВҰ43974 with pure gold, and made a gold mouldingВҰ43977 all aroundВҰ43979 it,
\v 3 and he cast four rings of goldВҰ43985 \add and attached them\add* to its four feetВҰ43988вҖ”two rings on each one side.
\v 4 HeВҰ44007 made \add two\add* acaciaВҰ44005 wood polesВҰ44003 andВҰ44006 overlaidВҰ44006 them with goldВҰ44008,
\v 5 andВҰ44010 he put the polesВҰ44013 into the ringsВҰ44014 on the sidesВҰ44016 of the boxВҰ44017 for carryingВҰ44018 it.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ44023 he made the atonementВҰ44024 platform from pure goldВҰ44025 \add to fit\add* as the lid for the box, \add so\add* it was \add also\add* 1.2m longВҰ44029 andВҰ44023 0.75m wideВҰ44032,
\v 7 thenВҰ44034 from the endsВҰ44042 of the lid, he hammeredВҰ44038 the goldВҰ44037 to form two winged creatures.
\v 8 ThereВҰ44059 was a winged creature sitting on each end of the atonement platform made from its two endsВҰ44063,
\v 9 andВҰ44066 they were spreadingВҰ44068 theirВҰ44072 wings upwardsВҰ44070 to coverВҰ44071 over the platform. They faced each other, \add вүҲlooking down towards\add* the atonement platform.
\s1 Making the bread table
\rem /s1 Making the Table for the Bread of the Presence; Making the Table for the Bread Offered to God; The Table; Building the Table
\r (Exo. 25:23-30)
\p
\v 10 HeВҰ44090 made \add the bread\add* tableВҰ44092 from acaciaВҰ44094 woodвҖ”one metre longВҰ44096, half a metre wideВҰ44098, and three-quarters of a metre highВҰ44101.
\v 11 ItВҰ44104 was overlaidВҰ44103 with pure gold andВҰ44103 had a gold mouldingВҰ44109 all aroundВҰ44111 it.
\v 12 He made an 8cm wide rim all around it, andВҰ44113 a goldВҰ44121 mouldingВҰ44119 around the rim.
\v 13 He moulded four gold rings from gold andВҰ44125 attached them to the four cornersВҰ44136 of the table. Each ring was close to each table leg
\v 14 near the rim to hold the polesВҰ44146 for carryingВҰ44147 the tableВҰ44150.
\v 15 He made \add two\add* acaciaВҰ44157 wood polesВҰ44155 andВҰ44158 overlaidВҰ44158 them for goldВҰ44160вҖ”they were for carryingВҰ44161 the tableВҰ44164.
\v 16 He \add also\add* made the utensils thatВҰ44171 would be on the tableВҰ44174вҖ”its platesВҰ44177 and pans, and its bowlsВҰ44182 and pitchersВҰ44185 to be used for pouring out \add <the wine offerings\add*вҖ”all made from pure goldВҰ44189.
\s1 Making the lampstand
\rem /s1 Building the Lampstand; The Lampstand; Making the Lampstand
\r (Exo. 25:31-40)
\p
\v 17 Then he made the lampstand from pure goldВҰ44197. The base and shaftВҰ44205 of the lampstand were hammeredВҰ44199 \add вүҲinto shape\add*, along with its cups, and its buds and blossoms.
\v 18 There were six branches goingВҰ44214 out from the shaft of the lampstandвҖ”three on each side.
\v 19 Each branch had threeВҰ44235 gold cups on it that looked like almond flowers with buds and petals. It was the same for each of the lampstand'sВҰ44248 six branchesВҰ44244.
\v 20 On the lampstandВҰ44250 \add shaft\add* there were fourВҰ44251 cups that also looked like almondВҰ44253 blossomsВҰ44253, each one with flower buds andВҰ44250 petalsВҰ44255.
\v 21 He made one flower bud beneath every pair of branches \add (that were going out from opposite sides)\add*. The bud was attached to each pair of branches as if they were growing out of itвҖ”all six lampstand branches were attached like that.
\v 22 The buds andВҰ44279 the branchesВҰ44279 coming out of them were all hammeredВҰ44283 out of one piece of pure goldВҰ44285.
\v 23 ThenВҰ44289 he made the sevenВҰ44292 lampsВҰ44291 out of pure goldВҰ44295, along with the tongs andВҰ44288 traysВҰ44294.
\v 24 He made \add @the lampstand\add* and tongs and trays using 33kg of pure goldВҰ44299.
\s1 Making the incense altar
\rem /s1 Building the Incense Altar; Making the Altar of Incense; Making the Altar for Burning Incense
\r (Exo. 30:1-5)
\p
\v 25 Then he made the altarВҰ44312 \add for burning\add* incenseВҰ44313 out of acaciaВҰ44315 wood. It was squareВҰ44320вҖ”half a metre on each sideвҖ”and one metre highВҰ44322. Its projections \add on the top four corners\add* were part of it.
\v 26 He overlaidВҰ44327 it with pure goldвҖ”all four sidesВҰ44336 including the projectionsвҖ”andВҰ44327 put a gold mouldingВҰ44343 all around it.
\v 27 ThenВҰ44365 he made two goldВҰ44349 ringsВҰ44348 \add andВҰ44347 attached them\add* below the mouldingВҰ44355вҖ”two on each side for holding the polesВҰ44363 for carryingВҰ44364 \add @the altar\add*.
\v 28 The \add two\add* polesВҰ44371 were made from acaciaВҰ44373 wood andВҰ44374 thenВҰ44368 overlaidВҰ44374 with goldВҰ44376.
\rem /s1 Making the Anointing Oil and the Incense
\rem /r (Exodus 30.22-38)
\v 29 He got a \add professional\add* ointment maker to make the sacredВҰ44383 anointingВҰ44382 oil andВҰ44384 the pureВҰ44383, fragrantВҰ44387 incenseВҰ44386.\x + \xo 37:29: \xt Exo 30:22-38.\x*
\c 38
\s1 Making the altar for burning sacrifices
\rem /s1 The Altar of Burnt Offering; Building the Altar of Burnt Offering; Making the Altar for Burning Offerings; Making the Altar of Burnt Offering
\r (Exo. 27:1-8)
\p
\v 1 Then \add @Bezalel\add* made the altarВҰ44396 for burning offeringsВҰ44397 from acaciaВҰ44399 wood. It was squareВҰ44407вҖ”2.5m on each sideвҖ”and 1.5m tall.
\v 2 \add вүҲFromВҰ44421 the same piece of wood\add*, he made horn-like projections for each of the fourВҰ44415 cornersВҰ44416, thenВҰ44412 he overlaidВҰ44420 it all with bronzeВҰ44422.
\v 3 He made all the utensilsВҰ44448 for the altarВҰ44430: the pots and shovelsВҰ44436, basinsВҰ44439 and meat-forks, and the firepansВҰ44445вҖ”all made from bronzeВҰ44450.
\v 4 He made a gratingВҰ44454 for the altarвҖ”a bronzeВҰ44457 lattice \add that fitted\add* \add вүҲdown in the middle of the altar\add*,
\v 5 andВҰ44465 he cast the gratingВҰ44470 with ringsВҰ44467 on the four cornersВҰ44469 as holdersВҰ44472 for the \add carrying\add* polesВҰ44473.
\v 6 He made the acaciaВҰ44480 wood polesВҰ44478 andВҰ44481 overlaidВҰ44481 them with bronzeВҰ44483
\v 7 andВҰ44485 he put the polesВҰ44488 into the ringsВҰ44489 on the sidesВҰ44491 of the altar so they could carryВҰ44493 it with them. He made \add @the altar\add* hollowВҰ44496 using boardsВҰ44497.
\s1 Making the washbasin
\rem /s1 Basin for Washing; Building the Washbasin; Making the Bronze Basin
\r (Exo. 30:18)
\p
\v 8 Then he made a bronze washbasin and base. \add They were made\add* with the bronze from the mirrorsВҰ44509 of the serving womenВҰ44510 who servedВҰ44512 at the entranceВҰ44513 of the sacredВҰ44514 tent.\x + \xo 38:8: \xt Exo 30:18.\x*
\s1 Making the courtyard
\rem /s1 Making the Court of the Tabernacle; The Enclosure for the Tent of the Lord's Presence; The Courtyard; Building the Courtyard
\r (Exo. 27:9-19)
\p
\v 9 Then \add @Bezalel\add* worked on the courtyard. For the southВҰ44524 side, the courtyard curtainsВҰ44526 were fifty metresВҰ44531 of twistedВҰ44529 finely-spun linenВҰ44528
\v 10 with their twenty \add bronzeВҰ44537\add* pillars and their basesВҰ44535. The hooksВҰ44538 on the pillars and their rings were made of silverВҰ44541.
\v 11 On the northВҰ44544 side, there were fifty metresВҰ44546 of curtains with their twenty bronzeВҰ44551 pillars and basesВҰ44549, and their silverВҰ44555 hooksВҰ44552 and rings.
\v 12 On the west side, there were twenty-five metresВҰ44562 of curtainsВҰ44560 with their ten pillars and basesВҰ44565, and their silverВҰ44570 hooksВҰ44567 and rings,
\v 13 andВҰ44572 \add another\add* twenty-five metres on the east side.
\v 14 The curtains for \add one\add* side \add of the entrance\add* were 7.5m long with their three pillarsВҰ44586 and their basesВҰ44588.
\v 15 On the \add вүҲother\add* side, opposite the courtyardВҰ44596 entrance, the curtainsВҰ44597 were 7.5m long with their three pillarsВҰ44601 andВҰ44591 their basesВҰ44603.
\v 16 All of the courtyardВҰ44609 curtainsВҰ44608 were made with twistedВҰ44612 finely-spun linenВҰ44611.
\v 17 The basesВҰ44614 for the pillars were bronzeВҰ44616, \add вүҲbut\add* the hooksВҰ44617 on them andВҰ44614 their rings were silver. All of the courtyardВҰ44629 pillars had decorative silver caps fitted to their tops.
\v 18 The curtain for the courtyard gate was done by an embroiderer. It was made from twistedВҰ44641 finely-spun linenВҰ44640 \add embroidered\add* with blue, purpleВҰ44637, and scarlet yard. The curtain was ten metresВҰ44648 long and 2.5m highВҰ44645, just like the other courtyard curtains
\v 19 with its four bronzeВҰ44657 pillarsВҰ44653 and their basesВҰ44655 and their silver hooksВҰ44658 and rings, and with silver caps.
\v 20 All the tent pegs for the sacredВҰ44668 tent andВҰ44669 for aroundВҰ44670 the courtyardВҰ44669 were made with bronzeВҰ44671.
\s1 List of metals used
\rem /s1 The Materials Used; Materials of the Tabernacle; Metals Used in the Tent of the Lord's Presence; Inventory of Materials
\p
\v 21 These are the records \add from making\add* the sacred tentВҰ44676 (where the \add stone\add* transcriptsВҰ44678 were kept). They were recorded by the LevitesВҰ44686 according to Mosheh'sВҰ44684 instructions \add and supervised by\add* IthamarВҰ44688 (a son of AharonВҰ44691 the priestВҰ44692).
\p
\v 22 Bezalel (son of UriВҰ44697 son of HurВҰ44700, from the tribeВҰ44701 of Judah) made everything that YahwehВҰ44710 had instructedВҰ44709 MoshehВҰ44713 \add <to make\add*.
\v 23 OholiabВҰ44716 (son of AhisamakВҰ44719, from the tribeВҰ44720 of DanВҰ44722) worked with himвҖ”he was an engraverВҰ44723 and a designerВҰ44724 and an embroidererВҰ44725 in blue, purpleВҰ44727, and scarletВҰ44728, and in fine linenВҰ44730.
\p
\v 24 The gold that they used for the construction of the sacred tent was measured at 965kg. This was the gold from the wave offeringВҰ44744 and was weighed using the official standard weights.
\v 25 The silverВҰ44755 contributed by the people was measured at 3,420kg \add also\add* using the official weights.\x + \xo 38:25-26: \xt Exo 30:11-16.\x*
\v 26 \add During the census,\add* every male who was twentyВҰ44781 years old or older paid a 5g silver coinвҖ”a total of 603,550 men.\x + \xo 38:26: \xt Mat 17:24.\x*
\v 27 They'd used 3,400kg of silverВҰ44797 to make the bases under the pillars that supported the sacred tent's curtainsВҰ44804 (34kg for each of one hundred bases)
\v 28 and the other twenty kilograms were used for the hooksВҰ44820 for the pillarsВҰ44821 and for the caps on the tops of them.
\v 29 The bronzeВҰ44827 from the wave offeringВҰ44828 came to 2,400kg
\v 30 and it was used to make the basesВҰ44841 \add for the pillars\add* at the tent entranceВҰ44842 and for the altar and its gratingВҰ44850 and all the utensils,
\v 31 and for the bases \add for the posts\add* for \add the curtains\add* around the courtyard and at the entrance, and for the tentВҰ44875 pegs for the \add вүҲmain structure\add* and around the courtyard.
\c 39
\s1 Making the priests' uniforms
\rem /s1 Making the Vestments for the Priesthood; The Priestly Garments; Clothing for the Priests; Making the Garments for the Priests
\r (Exo. 28:1-14)
\p
\v 1 They used the blue, purpleВҰ44887, andВҰ44884 scarletВҰ44888 \add cloth\add* to make the sacred clothes to be used in the sacred tentВҰ44895. They made Aharon's clothes just as YahwehВҰ44905 had instructedВҰ44904 MoshehВҰ44908.
\s2 The sacred apron
\rem /s1 The Ephod; Making the Ephod
\p
\v 2 \add @Bezalel\add* made the sacred apron from twistedВҰ44921 finely-spun linenВҰ44920 \add embroidered with\add* goldВҰ44915 \add wire\add*, and blue, purpleВҰ44917, and scarlet yarn.
\v 3 TheyВҰ44924 hammeredВҰ44923 thin sheets of goldВҰ44927 and he cut them into threadВҰ44929 of wire for a skillfulВҰ44941 craftsman to \add вүҲembroider\add* into the fine linenВҰ44939 along with the blue, purpleВҰ44934, and scarletВҰ44936 yarn.
\v 4 They made joined shoulder pieces for itвҖ”joined on twoВҰ44950 corners
\v 5 and the skillfullyВҰ44955 wovenВҰ44955 waistband whichВҰ44957 is attached to the apron was made of the same material of twistedВҰ44968 finely-spun linenВҰ44967, and had similar embroidery using goldВҰ44962 \add wire\add*, and blue, purpleВҰ44964, and scarlet yarn, just as YahwehВҰ44971 had instructedВҰ44970 MoshehВҰ44974.
\v 6 They cut \add two\add* onyx stonesВҰ44979 andВҰ44976 mounted them in decorative goldВҰ44983 settingsВҰ44982. The namesВҰ44989 of the \add twelve\add* sonsВҰ44990 of Yisra'el were engraved on \add them\add* similar to how a signet ring is engraved,
\v 7 andВҰ44993 he put them on the shoulderВҰ44996 pieces of the sacred apron as stonesВҰ44998 of reminder for the sonsВҰ45000 of Yisra'elВҰ45001, as YahwehВҰ45004 had instructedВҰ45003 MoshehВҰ45007.
\s1 Making the sacred pouch
\rem /s1 Making the Breastpiece; The Breastpiece; Making the Chestpiece
\r (Exo. 28:15-30)
\p
\v 8 Then he made the sacred chest pouch which took the work of a skilledВҰ45015 craftsman like making the sacred apron. It too was made of twistedВҰ45024 finely-spun linenВҰ45023 and embroidered with goldВҰ45018 \add wire\add*, and blue, purpleВҰ45020, and scarlet yarn.
\v 9 WhenВҰ45030 the material was folded over double, itВҰ45027 made a square pouch that was 23cm longВҰ45034 andВҰ45035 23cm wideВҰ45036,
\v 10 and they attached fourВҰ45042 rows of gemstones onto the front. The first row had a \add red\add* ruby, a \add yellow\add* topazВҰ45047, and a \add red\add* garnet.
\v 11 The secondВҰ45053 row had a \add green\add* emerald, a \add blue\add* sapphireВҰ45055, andВҰ45056 a diamondВҰ45056.
\v 12 The thirdВҰ45059 row had a \add red\add* jacinthВҰ45060, a \add white\add* agateВҰ45061, andВҰ45062 a \add purple\add* amethystВҰ45062.
\v 13 The fourthВҰ45065 row had a \add yellow\add* beryl, an onyx, andВҰ45068 a \add green\add* jasperВҰ45068. \add @All the stones\add* were mounted in decorative goldВҰ45071 settings.
\v 14 The gemstones were engraved with the names of the twelve sons of Yisra'el similar to how a signet ring is engraved, andВҰ45074 they represented the twelve tribesВҰ45095.
\v 15 They \add attached two\add* twistedВҰ45102 chainsВҰ45101 of pure goldВҰ45105 crafted like a cord onto the pouch,
\v 16 and made two decorative gold settingsВҰ45110 and two gold rings, and attached them to the \add вүҲupper corners\add* of the sacred pouch.
\v 17 They attached one end of each goldВҰ45129 chain to one of the ringsВҰ45133 on the \add вүҲtop corner\add* of the pouch,
\v 18 andВҰ45139 they attachedВҰ45149 the other end of each chain to the two decorative settingsВҰ45148 that enclose the stones. ThenВҰ45139 they put those on the frontВҰ45156 side of the shoulderВҰ45152 straps of the sacred apron.
\v 19 ThenВҰ45159 they made two \add more\add* goldВҰ45162 ringsВҰ45161 andВҰ45159 attached them to the \add вүҲlower corners\add* of the sacred pouch on the insideВҰ45177 edges next to the sacred apron.
\v 20 They made two more goldВҰ45182 ringsВҰ45181 andВҰ45179 attachedВҰ45183 them to the lowerВҰ45189 part of the frontВҰ45190 of the shoulder straps near where the shoulder straps join with the sacred apron just aboveВҰ45194 the waistbandВҰ45195.
\v 21 They tied the rings on the sacred pouch to the rings on the sacred apron with a blue cord, so that the sacred pouch was above the waistband andВҰ45214 would not come loose from the apron. They did these things exactly as YahwehВҰ45222 had instructedВҰ45221 MoshehВҰ45225 \add <to do\add*.
\s1 Making the other clothes
\rem /s1 Additional Clothing for the Priests; Other Priestly Garments; Making the Other Priestly Garments
\r (Exo. 28:31-43)
\p
\v 22 \add @Bezalel\add* had a weaverВҰ45233 make the robeВҰ45230 \add that would be worn under\add* the sacred apron entirelyВҰ45234 from blue \add material\add*.
\v 23 It opened down the middle like other clothes andВҰ45237 had a border aroundВҰ45245 this opening so that it wouldn't tear,
\v 24 and the bottom hem had \add decorative\add* pomegranatesВҰ45254 on it that were made from blue, purpleВҰ45256, and scarlet yarn.
\v 25 TheyВҰ45266 \add also\add* made \add small\add* bells from pure goldВҰ45263 andВҰ45265 attached them between the pomegranates aroundВҰ45275 the bottom of the robeВҰ45274,
\v 26 so it alternated between a bell and a pomegranate going aroundВҰ45287 the hem, just as YahwehВҰ45291 had instructedВҰ45290 MoshehВҰ45294.
\p
\v 27 A weaverВҰ45303 made tunicsВҰ45300 for AaronВҰ45304 and his sonsВҰ45305 from fine linenВҰ45301,
\v 28 along with the turbanВҰ45308 andВҰ45307 caps from fine linen, the underwearВҰ45317 made from twistedВҰ45320 finely-spun linen,
\v 29 and the waistband from fine linenВҰ45325 with blue, purpleВҰ45328, and scarlet embroidery, just as YahwehВҰ45335 had instructedВҰ45334 MoshehВҰ45338.
\p
\v 30 They made a \add decorative\add* plateВҰ45344 (to represent a holy crownВҰ45345) from pureВҰ45347 goldВҰ45348 and theyВҰ45341 engravedВҰ45353 вҖҳDedicated to YahwehВҰ45356вҖҷ on it (like you'd do for a signet ring).
\v 31 TheyВҰ45370 put a blue cord on it to attach it to the front of the turbanВҰ45365, just as YahwehВҰ45369 had instructedВҰ45368 MoshehВҰ45372.
\s1 Mosheh inspects the finished components
\rem /s1 The Completion of the Work; Moses Inspects the Work; The Work Completed; Moses Inspects the Tabernacle
\r (Exo. 35:10-19)
\p
\v 32 AndВҰ45389 \add so\add* all the components of the residence, the tentВҰ45379 for meetingВҰ45381 \add <God\add*, were finishedВҰ45375вҖ”the IsraelisВҰ45384 had done just what YahwehВҰ45388 had instructedВҰ45387 MoshehВҰ45391.
\v 33 \add @The craftsmen\add* broughtВҰ45396 the \add disassembled\add* residence to MoshehВҰ45402вҖ”the tentВҰ45399 and all its equipment, the clips, the framesВҰ45412 with their bars, and the pillarsВҰ45415 with their basesВҰ45416,
\v 34 the reddened rams hide tarpaulin andВҰ45418 the top sea-cow hide tarpaulin, the curtainВҰ45430 for covering \add <the most sacred place\add*,
\v 35 the boxВҰ45435 for the transcriptВҰ45436 slabs and itsВҰ45439 polesВҰ45439, the atonement platform,
\v 36 the tableВҰ45445 with all itsВҰ45450 utensilsВҰ45450 andВҰ45451 the sacred breadВҰ45452 to presentВҰ45453 to God,
\v 37 the pure lampstand with its row of lamps and all its utensilsВҰ45468 and the lamp oil,
\v 38 the goldВҰ45475 \add incense\add* altarВҰ45474, the anointingВҰ45478 oil and the fragrantВҰ45481 incense, and the curtain for the tent entranceВҰ45484,
\v 39 the \add large\add* bronze altarВҰ45489 with its gratingВҰ45493, its polesВҰ45500, and all its utensilsВҰ45505, the washbasin with its base,
\v 40 the courtyard curtains with their pillarsВҰ45518 and basesВҰ45521, the courtyard gate curtain, \add all the\add* ropesВҰ45529 and tent pegs and all the items to serviceВҰ45535 the residence as the tent of meetingВҰ45538,
\v 41 and the finely-woven clothes for serving in the holy place, the sacredВҰ45549 clothes for AharonВҰ45550 the priest, and the clothes for his sonsВҰ45555 to \add serveВҰ45556 as\add* priestsВҰ45556.
\p
\v 42 The IsraelisВҰ45569 had done all the workВҰ45573 just as YahwehВҰ45562 had instructedВҰ45561 MoshehВҰ45565.
\v 43 Mosheh \add вүҲinspected\add* all the workВҰ45581, and wow, they had done it just as YahwehВҰ45587 had instructedВҰ45586 \add <them\add*, and Mosheh blessedВҰ45590 them.
\c 40
\s1 Erecting the sacred tent
\rem /s1 Setting Up the Tabernacle; The Tabernacle Erected and Its Equipment Installed; The Tabernacle Completed; Setting Up and Dedicating the Tent of the Lord's Presence
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ45596 told MoshehВҰ45599,
\v 2 вҖңOnВҰ45609 the first dayВҰ45602 of the first month, youВҰ45608 should set up the tentВҰ45611 \add вүҲwhere we'll meet\add*.
\v 3 Put the boxВҰ45618 for the transcriptВҰ45619 slabs in its place andВҰ45620 \add hang\add* the curtainВҰ45626 to screenВҰ45620 it \add from sight\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ45628 bring in the \add bread\add* tableВҰ45631 and arrangeВҰ45632 its utensils, and bring in the lampstand and set up the lamps,
\v 5 and put the goldВҰ45649 incenseВҰ45650 altarВҰ45648 in frontВҰ45651 of the sacred boxВҰ45652 and set up the entranceВҰ45658 curtain for the tentВҰ45659.
\v 6 PutВҰ45662 the altarВҰ45663 for burning sacrifices in frontВҰ45665 of the entranceВҰ45666 to the sacredВҰ45667 tentВҰ45667 \add вүҲwhere we'll meet\add*.
\v 7 PutВҰ45673 the washbasin between the sacredВҰ45678 tent and that altarВҰ45681, and fill it with waterВҰ45684.
\v 8 \add вүҲSet-up the curtains aroundВҰ45690 the outside to make the courtyard, andВҰ45691 also set up the courtyard's entrance curtain\add*.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ45698 takeВҰ45698 the \add sacred\add* anointingВҰ45702 oil and \add вүҲsmear\add* it on the sacred tentВҰ45706 and everything that's in it, thenВҰ45698 \add вүҲnone of those thingsВҰ45722 should be touched by others\add*вҖ”it will \add all\add* be sacred.
\v 10 \add вүҲAlso\add* anointВҰ45724 the altar for burntВҰ45728 offeringsВҰ45728 andВҰ45724 all itsВҰ45733 utensilsВҰ45733. After that, the altar \add вүҲshouldn't be touched by others\add*вҖ”itВҰ45738 will be \em very\em* sacredВҰ45740.
\v 11 Anoint the washbasin and itsВҰ45749 base, and thenВҰ45743 \add вүҲprohibit others from using\add* it.
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲNow\add* bringВҰ45753 AharonВҰ45756 and his sonsВҰ45759 to the entranceВҰ45762 of the sacredВҰ45763 tent and wash them with waterВҰ45767.
\v 13 ThenВҰ45769 put the sacred garmentsВҰ45774 on AharonВҰ45772 and anointВҰ45776 him and make him sacred, so he can \add now\add* serveВҰ45780 as a priestВҰ45780 to me.
\v 14 \add вүҲAlso\add* bringВҰ45786 his sonsВҰ45785 andВҰ45787 dress them in tunicsВҰ45789
\v 15 and anoint them like youВҰ45794 anointed their fatherВҰ45797, and they will serveВҰ45798 as priestsВҰ45798 to me. Their anointing will cause them to be a priesthood forever throughoutВҰ45806 their generationsВҰ45806.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ45814\add* MoshehВҰ45809 did \add everythingВҰ45810\add* that YahwehВҰ45813 had instructedВҰ45812 him \add <to do\add*.
\v 17 It was the first day of the first month of \add their\add* secondВҰ45823 yearВҰ45822 when they set up the sacredВҰ45827 tentВҰ45827.
\v 18 MoshehВҰ45830 set up the residence by setting out its basesВҰ45837 and standing up the framesВҰ45841 with their bars, and the pillarsВҰ45849.
\v 19 HeВҰ45870 spreadВҰ45851 the \add вүҲtwo tarpaulin layers\add* over the tentВҰ45857 just as YahwehВҰ45867 had instructedВҰ45866 \add *him\add*.
\v 20 Then he tookВҰ45873 the \add two stone slabs with the\add* transcriptВҰ45877 and put \add #them\add* into the box. He put the polesВҰ45884 \add into the rings\add* on the box and fitted the atonement platform on the top of the box \add as a lid\add*,
\v 21 andВҰ45897 broughtВҰ45897 the box into the residence. HeВҰ45917 set up the curtainВҰ45906 to conceal the box with the transcriptВҰ45911, just as YahwehВҰ45914 had instructedВҰ45913 \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 22 HeВҰ45921 put the tableВҰ45923 into the sacredВҰ45928 tentВҰ45928 on the northВҰ45929 side of the residence, outsideВҰ45930 the curtainВҰ45931,
\v 23 andВҰ45933 arrangedВҰ45933 the breadВҰ45936 on it \add вүҲto display it to\add* Yahweh, just as Yahweh had instructedВҰ45940 \add *him\add*.
\v 24 HeВҰ45948 put the lampstandВҰ45950 inside the sacredВҰ45957 tentВҰ45957 across from the tableВҰ45954, on the southВҰ45958 side of the residence,
\v 25 andВҰ45960 he placed the lampsВҰ45961 on it \add вүҲin Yahweh's presence\add*, just as Yahweh had instructedВҰ45965 \add *him\add*.
\v 26 ThenВҰ45973 he put the goldВҰ45976 \add incense\add* altarВҰ45975 inside the sacred tent in frontВҰ45979 of the curtainВҰ45980 \add that screened the sacred box from view\add*,
\v 27 andВҰ45982 burnt some fragrant incenseВҰ45984 on it, just as YahwehВҰ45988 had instructedВҰ45987 \add *him\add*,
\v 28 then he hung the curtain at the tentВҰ45999 entranceВҰ45998.
\v 29 HeВҰ46023 put the altarВҰ46002 for burning sacrifices at the gate of the sacredВҰ46006 tentВҰ46006 and offered the burnt offering and the grainВҰ46017 offering up on it, just as YahwehВҰ46020 had instructedВҰ46019 \add *him\add*.
\v 30 ThenВҰ46027 he placed the washbasin between the tent and the altarВҰ46035, and filled it with waterВҰ46038
\v 31 \add so that\add* MoshehВҰ46043, and AharonВҰ46044 and his sonsВҰ46045, could wash their handsВҰ46048 and feetВҰ46051 from it.
\v 32 Whenever they went into the sacredВҰ46056 tent or whenever they went near the altarВҰ46061, \add first\add* they would wash themselves, just as YahwehВҰ46065 had commandedВҰ46064 MosesВҰ46068.
\v 33 He erected the courtyard \add curtains\add* aroundВҰ46075 the residence and the altarВҰ46077, and he set up the courtyard gate curtain. And \add so\add* MoshehВҰ46085 finished the work.
\s1 Yahweh's splendour fills the tent
\rem /s1 The Cloud and the Glory; The Glory of the Lord; The Lord's Glory Fills the Tabernacle; The Cloud over the Tent of the Lord's Presence
\r (Num. 9:15-23)
\p
\v 34 Then a cloudВҰ46092 coveredВҰ46091 the sacredВҰ46102 tentВҰ46102 and Yahweh'sВҰ46098 \add вүҲpower and bright light\add* filledВҰ46099 the residence\x + \xo 40:34: \xt 1Ki 8:10-11; Isa 6:4; Eze 43:4-5; Rev 15:8.\x*
\v 35 and MoshehВҰ46107 was unable to enter the tentВҰ46123 because the cloudВҰ46117 had settledВҰ46115 on it and Yahweh'sВҰ46119 splendour had filledВҰ46120 the residence.
\v 36 \add From thenВҰ46125 onwards,\add* whenever the cloudВҰ46126 went up from over the residence, the IsraelisВҰ46131 would \add pack their camp andВҰ46125\add* set out on their travels,
\v 37 but while the cloud remained, theyВҰ46141 would stay in that place untilВҰ46142 the cloud lifted.
\v 38 Yahweh'sВҰ46149 cloudВҰ46148 would be there during the dayВҰ46153 \add вүҲbut\add* it would become fireВҰ46154 at nightВҰ46156, and so the IsraelisВҰ46163 \add вүҲcould always see it\add*.
